column8: Fugitive Jesse Pinkman attempts to outrun his past. Written and directed by "Breaking Bad" creator Vince Gilligan, starring Aaron Paul.
After his wife and injured daughter disappear from an ER, a man conducts a panicked search and becomes convinced the hospital is hiding something.
With a matriarch bent on having a lavish 51st birthday party, her family's debt is on the verge of exposure, threatening their business – and legacy.
A con man and a would-be filmmaking crew force themselves into the lives of two grief-scarred young women. But nothing is as it seems.
Back in her childhood home to help her sister care for their comatose mother, Alicia must face a dark force from her past that now threatens her child.
The level-headed owner of a struggling coffee shop finds his future at risk when his partner – a talented but cocky barista – makes a major bet.
Get an intimate look at four engaged citizens whose courage, sense of civic duty and ultimate sacrifice helped to transform Italian society.
Chef and food writer Samin Nosrat travels the world to explore four basic keys to wonderful cooking, serving up feasts and helpful tips along the way.
Amid the tumult following Egyptian President Morsi's ouster, demonstrators from divergent backgrounds are brought together inside a police truck.
Yearning to earn the title of world blading champion, a novice competitor must harness his untamed potential through training and tournaments.
Singer-songwriter Gen Hoshino takes the stage at the sold out Tokyo Dome in his highly anticipated 2019 Pop Virus dome tour.
Decades after the sudden birth of a new continent, a young rescuer-for-hire provides aid to adventurers exploring this dangerous, uncharted world.
After devastating terror attacks in Norway, a young survivor, grieving families and the country rally for justice and healing. Based on a true story.
An ambitious TV reporter uses risky and ethically questionable methods to report on gang wars and police corruption in the Amazon port of Belém, Brazil.
Buckle up for an anthology of socially conscious horror stories that focus on the perils of racial injustice and the price of ignorance.
Christina Pazsitzky hits Seattle with a biting dose of reality, telling truths about her childhood, getting older and the horrors of giving birth.
This series looks at how seasonal changes cause shifting weather patterns and ocean currents, creating the conditions for spectacular wildlife events.

column4: The Blue Planet: A Natural History of the Oceans
column8: David Attenborough narrates this definitive exploration of the marine world, from the familiar to the unknown, revealing the sea and its communities.

column4: Chelsea Handler: Uganda Be Kidding Me Live
column8: In her first Netflix stand-up comedy special, Chelsea Handler recounts her African adventures (and provides hilarious photographic evidence).
Hoping to help their dissident parents, two brothers sneak out of Poland and land as refugees in Denmark, where they are prevented from returning home.
After losing her mother, a teenage girl bonds with her phone’s artificial intelligence app, a relationship that soon takes a dark and violent turn.
When a girl is kidnapped from a prestigious prep school, a homicide detective takes the case, teaming up with young security agent.

column4: Alpha and Omega 2: A Howl-iday Adventure
column8: In this animated outdoor adventure, wolf couple Humphrey and Kate face a crisis when one of their three cubs disappears without explanation.
In this fast-paced actioner, two Miami narcotics cops are hot on the trail of a master crook who has snatched $100 million worth of heroin.
In this hyperkinetic sequel, a pair of Miami narcotics cops investigate a Cuban drug kingpin's connection to Florida's influx of Ecstasy.
Cocaine smuggler George rises from poverty to become one of the biggest drug dealers in America before his eventual downfall.
Grad student Helen Lyle unintentionally summons the Candyman, a hook-handed creature made flesh by other people's belief in him.
Three beauties use their looks, charm and martial-arts training to kick butt on the trail of stolen software in this reboot of the classic TV series.
In this reboot of the TV classic, the Angels are tasked with finding lost rings encoded with the personal information of people in witness protection.
In this adaptation of a popular webtoon, a poor student trying to navigate college life gains the attention of a wealthy upperclassman with a dark side.
A veterinarian and two writers have a mysterious connection to Korean independence fighters from the Japanese colonial period.
Three best friends look for love, laughs and some lifelong memories while attending college together.
In post-Sept. 11 Los Angeles, tensions erupt when the lives of people from all walks of life converge during a 36-hour period.

column4: Dumb and Dumberer: When Harry Met Lloyd
column8: This wacky prequel to the 1994 blockbuster goes back to the lame-brained title characters' days as classmates at a Rhode Island high school.
When a construction project begins in their neighborhood, four friends start receiving bizarre encoded text messages on their cell phones.
Three engineering students deal with dorm drama, date around, and do whatever it takes to make their dreams come true.
Artistic rebellion ignites at the movies when film characters suddenly speak freely to the audience, prompting a surly censor to combat the uprising.
Maverick cop Orin Boyd joins forces with an unlikely ally in gangster Latrell Walker to take down a group of dirty Detroit cops.
A starry-eyed employee of a hot cosmetics company hires a dreamy photographer who is secretly indebted to a major rival – her sketchy aunt.
Four girls from different backgrounds become unlikely friends when they move into a dormitory for female dental students.
Two L.A. teens with summer jobs at Good Burger try to save their small restaurant when a corporate giant burger franchise moves in across the street.
Every time Chuck breaks up with a girlfriend, she ends up engaged to her next boyfriend. Soon, women are dating Chuck in hopes of meeting Mr. Right.

column4: Harold & Kumar Escape from Guantanamo Bay
column8: Harold and Kumar jump on a plane to catch up with Harold's love interest but must change their plans when Kumar is accused of being a terrorist.
Determined to prove herself as a street dancer, Maria heads from juvie to a Bronx rec center where she's introduced to her dance idol, Honey Daniels.
A motivated teen strives to rise from dishwasher to waiter at a luxury hotel only to tread in the abusive tide of its workplace hierarchy.
A group of daring teens finds themselves in a fight for their lives inside a haunted house when a sinister spirit crashes their Halloween party.
While living under one roof, five close-knit 20-somethings maneuver the highs and lows of friendship, romantic entanglements and finding themselves.
Tormented by mistrust, a businessman hires a cagey tailor to track his wife's whereabouts with her doctor only to send his mind further down an abyss.
An MIT astrophysics professor and his son unearth a string of numbers from a time capsule that seem to reveal a cataclysm that will wipe out humanity.
This documentary follows eight women in India who struggle with self-confidence and society's expectations but rediscover themselves through running.
This compilation for preschoolers features a peppy young bus and his first life experiences where bumps in the road won't stop him from a fun ride.
In 1930s Poland, a powerful psychic steers a group of strangers toward a fated convergence that ensures survival for one and annihilation for others.
Will Smith and Tommy Lee Jones reprise their roles as two highly secretive and unofficial government agents dealing with all things evil and alien.

Nikki Glaser bares all in a blistering stand-up special about sex, sobriety and getting over her own insecurities. And she won't spare you the details.
Kate, an uptight chef, finds her life turned upside down when her sister dies in a car accident and she becomes her niece's sole guardian.
This entry in the all-star caper franchise finds debonair con man Danny Ocean and his gang taking revenge on a double-crossing Las Vegas kingpin.
Danny Ocean reunites with his old flame and the rest of his merry band of thieves in a caper covering three huge heists in Rome, Paris and Amsterdam.
Award-winning documentarian Morgan Spurlock turns his camera on boy band phenomenon One Direction in this combination concert film and backstage pass.
This gritty biopic of brutal boxer Jake LaMotta portrays a tormented soul rising to the top of his sport, only to be undone by his demons.
The Rugrats take to the big screen and visit Paris when Mr. Pickles gets summoned to fix a giant robot at the EuroReptarland theme park.
Gale has written a best-seller which has been turned into a film. As the movie premiere looms closer, the mysterious deaths begin again.
This fast-paced documentary profiles Ayrton Senna, one of the greatest drivers in the history of Formula One racing, and a hero in his native Brazil.
Communicating via a walkie-talkie that transcends time, a profiler from 2015 and a detective from 1989 join forces to tackle crimes and injustice.

A psychologist and her mute son confront evil forces at the site of a terrible tragedy involving an ancestral Ouija board and a demonic secret society.

When she loses her city's vital power supply, Kryptonian Kara follows it to Earth in the hopes of retrieving it. Although gifted with powers like her cousin Superman, Kara struggles to defeat the evil Selena, who now controls the mighty object.
When Superman returns to Metropolis, he finds that Lois Lane has moved on to another man and Lex Luthor is developing a new plan to rule the world.

Bounty hunter Milo Boyd finds his latest assignment downright satisfying as he learns that the bail-jumper he must chase down is his ex-wife, Nicole.
Two terminally ill men bust out of the cancer ward with a plan to experience life to the fullest before they kick the bucket.
When the captain of a pleasant cruise ship mistakes a mischievous stowaway the entertainment director, wild and wacky hijinks ensue.
When a pair of friends discovers a mystical sculpture in an abandoned shrine, good fortune is bestowed upon them – until luck starts running out.
The Flintstones hit the big screen in this live-action comedy that finds Fred and Barney struggling to cope with the pressures of work and family.

column4: The Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas
column8: Yabba-dabba-doo! Digital dinosaurs rule the day when Fred, Barney, Betty and Wilma take Vegas by storm in this prequel that posits their lives before marriage.
A fugitive soldier gets swept up in personal and political intrigue when he's hired as a bodyguard for the family of a presidential candidate.
A talented singer falls in love at first sight with a music prodigy who has an affinity for lies – and a knack for being a hit-making producer.
A priest's duties are tested when a young guerrilla asks for absolution while confessing his plans to murder a local man he believes is a traitor.
When Chris and his son are evicted, they face trying times as a desperate Chris accepts an unpaid internship at a stock brokerage firm.
When his baby brother Dil is born, Tommy Pickles and his pals decide that he's too much responsibility and try to return him to the hospital.
When an unbearable stranger arrives at a winter mountain resort and vanishes overnight, his dark past comes to light.
This insightful drama looks at the crumbling marriage between a self-centered novelist – whose career is waning – and his up-and-coming writer wife.
Due to a genetic disorder, handsome librarian Henry involuntarily zips through time, appearing at various moments in the life of his true love.
Renton and his mates cope with the gritty realities of heroin addiction. But when Renton gets clean, he can't get away from his friends' nasty habits.
The love-struck Prince Paris of Troy kidnaps beauty Helen from her husband, setting the two nations on a collision course for war.
While chasing a serial murderer, a detective ends up 30 years in the future, where he tries to solve the case alongside new partners.
Five disparate kids, snowed in at the airport on Christmas Eve, try to get back to their families and outsmart a disgruntled airport official.
A suburban teen goes hunting with his estranged father. When a mishap with a bear occurs, he must his use his survival skills to save them both.
When a delivery of coffins foreshadows a harsh winter, residents of a retirement home escape their confines and rediscover the world outside.
At the onset of World War II, a Polish infantry lacking firepower fight to build a strong defense and protect their peninsula against enemy forces.
Four brothers learn that they have inherited ancestral land, but must fight to claim it when a greedy feudal lord threatens to take it over.
Beatrix can't wait to be inducted as a witch, but an unfortunate incident threatens to take her pending title away if she doesn't act fast.
A film crew shooting in a remote forested location begins losing members one by one to a mysterious entity that they cannot see or hear.
Mild-mannered Krishna comes to Mumbai to search for his gang-leader brother, and quickly finds himself in way over his head.
An ambitious young athlete endeavors to revive his floundering running career after falling prey to negative influences.
Three cops find themselves hurtling toward the same crime scene on one fatal night in this tense, edge-of your-seat thriller.
Senator Ted Kennedy watches his future unravel in the wake of an infamous car crash as family and allies vie to protect his reputation.
Expanding Kenneth Clark's 1969 "Civilisation" series for a new generation, this reboot explores the art of cultures around the world, throughout time.
In the ancient walled city of Delhi, an American-born Indian finds himself on an unexpected inner journey as he learns about himself and his roots.
Because they come from different castes, the son of a tax collector and his true love are not allowed to marry, sending them down divergent paths.
Agam Singh's brothers mean everything to him, so while he promises not to marry, he tries to get them to marry – but they want him to marry first.
An Indian hotel waiter forms an unlikely bond with a Pakistani colleague when the establishment’s criminal owner threatens to ruin both their lives.

column4: Earth's Natural Wonders: Life at the Extremes
column8: From the Arctic to the Outback, humans battle the elements and use their ingenuity to survive in the most extreme environments in the world.
Bollywood stars Imran Khan and Kareena Kapoor pair up to play exceptionally dissimilar lovers in this lighthearted romantic comedy.
Harry Dean Stanton narrates this documentary that follows two modern-day cowboys as they welcome new calves at Montana's Fishtail Basin Ranch.
Jailed after becoming entangled in the murder of a cop, a prisoner assembles a team of inmates to hatch a plan for making a getaway.
When a man discovers that he can communicate with his grandfather's spirit, it leads to two love stories intertwining 50 years apart.
Three sisters seem to be ideal brides for three brothers. But when the girls' father won't allow the marriages, the boys use trickery to pull it off.
Against a backdrop of burgeoning social unrest, a neophyte filmmaker makes history in 1913 as the director of India's first feature-length film.
Interconnected sketches and performances skewer the madness and misunderstandings of modern relationships.
An eccentric, self-proclaimed detective goes on an action-packed hunt for his missing father, with an awkward but adventurous journalist by his side.
Shinda loves Laali but can't have her, so he and his friends come up with an elaborate plan to solve all their problems and win her.
In 16th-century India, what begins as a strategic alliance between a Mughal emperor and a Hindu princess becomes a genuine opportunity for true love.
Framed by a politician for committing murder, a lower-class boy hires the only counsel he can afford: a lawyer with no courtroom experience.
A young man pursues his dreams of wealth by breaking the law, while his twin brother tries to better his life through hard work and honesty.

column4: Kevin Hart: Laugh at My Pain
column8: Sometimes edgy and always hilarious, comedian Kevin Hart shines in this theatrical version of his record-breaking 2011 live tour.
With his unique hip-hop style delivery, African American stand-up comedian Kevin Hart expounds on life at a sold-out concert performance.
An embittered former hockey star must engage with the sport again to help his brother assemble a team for a momentous match against the British.
A free-spirited doctor is hired to assist an injured king and winds up challenging his family's tradition-bound lifestyle as she falls for his son.
Meet the astonishing animals and adventurous people living on some of the most spectacular – and formidable – mountain ranges in the world.
A bitter family battle ensues between a father and his sons when a businessman makes a deal that entices farmers to sell off their properties.
A man finds his lucky charm in the form of a woman whom he had once clashed with on every level, but on whose presence he must now rely to succeed.
When a young Indian couple moves to the American suburbs, they are shocked to discover that they've become enmeshed in a secret terrorist plot.
A disillusioned rickshaw driver in Punjab dreams of moving to Dubai, but his plan to butter up his would-be benefactor goes horribly wrong.
Fleeing London to evade a gangland debt collector, Omi Khurana returns to his native village in India, passing himself off as a successful lawyer.
An ordinary-looking guy weds the woman of his dreams, but his jealousy threatens to destroy their union in this lighthearted tale of marital mismatch.
While prepping for a family wedding, a young man falls for his sister’s friend, who has already been promised to someone else.
When three brothers unwittingly get entangled in a murder associated with a fraudulent ashram leader, they set out to expose him to society as a fake.
Featuring breathtaking imagery and thought-provoking narration, this film takes viewers to the summits of some of the world’s most amazing mountains.
A martial arts specialist accidentally becomes a superhero when he steps in – in costume – to help the cops catch a criminal.
When jingle composer Nanda's car breaks down on his way to Chennai, he hitchhikes there with Arjun, who tries to rope Nanda into a shady deal.
A bright-eyed villager comes face-to-face with the gritty realities of modern-day Mumbai when he sets out to find his childhood friend.

column4: My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Forgotten Friendship
column8: School yearbook editor Sunset Shimmer has suddenly been erased from the memories of her best friends and must find out how to fix this.

column4: My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rollercoaster of Friendship
column8: Rarity gets a summer job at Equestria Land, making Applejack feel jealous. But when their friends start vanishing, they must work together to find them.
After declaring that he's going to film himself committing suicide for a school project, Archie videotapes reactions from friends and family.
After his sleeping disorder hinders him from protecting his girlfriend, a man sets out to take revenge on the thugs who attacked her.
A teenage boy becomes smitten with his new drama teacher and pursues her, despite the perilous risks of being found out.
With custom-built cameras attached to their bodies, animals from nine species offer a rare and intimate glimpse into their lives.
When three different boys propose to a lively, strictly reared girl who yearns to be a performer, she agrees to marry the winner of a singing contest.
When her friend’s rapist evades punishment from the law, a determined young woman takes revenge into her own hands in this story based on real events.
Complications around the cremation of their deceased friend inspire three septuagenarian friends to build their own mortuary.
India's primary intelligence agency sends an enigmatic operative on a top-secret mission to avenge the 11/26 terrorist attack on Mumbai.
A pizza delivery boy who doesn't believe in the supernatural is forced to confront his convictions after being trapped in a house on his route.
When a woman arrives in Mumbai and hires three spirited boys to care for her estate, she discovers they're more trustworthy than her family members.
The plot thickens around two horse-racing competitors when three beautiful women come into their lives and a murder is committed.
In this sequel set in the world of horse racing, half-brothers Ranvir and Rajiv Singh return for another complex tale of love, greed and violence.
Three old friends who have always hated politics are in for a shock when the friend who dislikes politics the most is somehow elected head minister.
After several failed attempts to obtain a visa, a man desperate to escape Punjab pays a British woman to marry him so he can move to England.
Gabrielle Reece hosts a transformative competition of tough fitness challenges as 10 women partner with 10 elite personal trainers.
In London, a mysterious blind man named Kenny appears to be an assassin who uses echolocation to kill, but there is more to Kenny than meets the eye.
Featuring experts in their fields and raw and moving footage, this documentary makes a case for increased autonomy in women's choices for childbirth.
When shy Kumar gets stuck on the losing end of a love triangle, the Love Doctor, Mokia, has a strategy for Kumar to win the love of his life.
A film crew captures a year in the life of modern polygamist families at Rockland Ranch, a community for fundamentalist Mormons in the Utah desert.
Imprisoned for drug smuggling as a child, a young man uses the law he studied while in jail to take revenge on those who wronged him.
Upon returning to his industrial hometown, a young man must decide whether to follow his own dreams or acquiesce to his father's plans for his future.
A masked freedom fighter known as "V" takes up arms against a totalitarian government and finds an unlikely ally in a young woman.
This powerful Tamil action film follows the shared fate of two very different siblings: policeman Thiru and his roguish brother, Guru.
A spoiled trust fund brat finds himself stuck in a rut of meaningless late-night parties – until he meets a significantly older woman and writer.
A divorced mother of three children runs a happy household – until her former husband brings his new career-oriented girlfriend into the picture.
A peasant from Punjab and his best friend pose as detectives, filmmakers and more while trying to retrieve stolen money in this romantic comedy.

column4: Zack and Miri Make a Porno
column8: Zack and Miri make and star in an adult film to bring in easy money. But their unspoken feelings for each other might threaten the whole enterprise.
Two young parents struggle to keep their marriage afloat and their son protected amidst financial woes, career goals and clashes of ego.
Twenty-six years after the 1980 massacre at Gwangju, South Korea, three relatives of the victims come together to avenge the infamous orchestrator.
After the world's top scientists disappear, orphaned April secretly forges ahead with a family experiment and gets tangled up in a vast conspiracy.

column4: Barbie & Her Sisters in a Pony Tale
column8: Barbie and her sisters set off on a Swiss adventure to the majestic Alps, where they're excited to spend the summer at a fun-filled riding academy!
Surf champ Merliah discovers she's actually a mermaid in a girl's body. With the help of a dolphin, Merliah must rescue her mom, the Queen of Oceana.
A princess with a predictable life finds herself transformed by a magical butterfly's kiss into Super Sparkle, a crime-fighting superhero.
When royal Princess Courtney trades places with famous rock star Erika, two worlds collide while both learn to appreciate new friends and experiences.
A hoverboard-riding princess of the cosmos, Barbie must band together with a team of talented new friends to save the stars from winking out.
When devilish fairies capture Ken and fly away with him, Barbie and Raquelle travel to the glittering fairy world of Gloss Angeles to save him.
Blair Willows is excited when she gets to go to Princess Charm School, where she meets princesses Delancy and Hadley, and searches for a magic crown.
A high-tech spy agency transforms Barbie and her best friends into secret agents, using their gymnastics skills to bring down a cunning cat burglar.
Barbie stars as a princess who would rather sing and dance than be a royal. When a famous pop star visits the kingdom, they decide to switch places.
Pulled into her favorite video game, Barbie becomes a fun, roller-skating heroine who's battling a sinister emoji that's trying to take over.
Middle schooler Valt Aoi, with his Beyblade Valtryek, faces off against friends, classmates and rivals to become the world's number one Blader.
Young Cuca leaves his idyllic village on a grand adventure to find his father, who has traveled to the city seeking work.
This series explores the magnitude and scale of modern air travel, and the challenges faced by those responsible for its smooth functioning.

column4: Equestria Girls: Tales of Canterlot High

Three 6-year-old kids who live normal lives during the day become superheroes at night, fighting crime as a team known as PJ Masks.

To escape the stress of fame, teen pop star Jordan goes incognito in a small town, where he forms a special bond with high school art student Emily.
After realizing that their boob tube is gone, Beavis and Butt-head set off on an expedition that takes them from Las Vegas to the nation's capital.
When ladies' man Robin meets Jamika, he falls head over heels, but she greets him with four surprises: her son and her girlfriend Bebe's three kids.
This documentary charts the rise and fall of hot yoga founder Bikram Choudhury as his global empire is born and disturbing revelations come to light.
Lazarus finds Rae beaten and near death, and acts as a father figure to help redeem her. But before saving anyone, Lazarus must face his own demons.
As a lethal virus spreads globally, four friends seek a reputed plague-free haven. But while avoiding the infected, the travelers turn on one another.
A village landlord's daughter and an educated commoner must decide if their budding forbidden love is worth resisting a repressive social hierarchy.
This riveting crime doc follows Bill as he confronts America's broken judicial system after his son is falsely sentenced to 40 years in prison.
After two community college geology professors discover microscopic alien life-forms on a meteorite, the military and government become involved.
Grieving mother Karen McCann takes justice into her own hands when the man who raped and murdered her daughter is freed on a technicality.
A Christmas reunion becomes a gateway to the past in this three-part series that explores the intimate complexities of one family's history.
Andy Samberg stars in this comedy as an accident-prone daredevil who's determined to jump 15 buses on his moped and impress his abusive stepfather.
The Olsen twins put a cute new spin on Mark Twain's classic tale "The Prince and the Pauper," playing identical 9-year-olds from very different backgrounds: orphaned Amanda and wealthy Alyssa.
Lorena Ramírez of Mexico's Rarámuri community lives a pastoral life – except when she straps on her sandals to compete as an ultramarathon runner.
Over the years, as they come and go in each other's life, childhood pals Rosie and Alex struggle to resolve the lasting, intimate bond between them.
A self-trained engineer risks debt, love and reputation in his quest to improve the grueling work conditions of his mother and her weaving community.

column4: Once Upon a Time in the West
column8: In this epic spaghetti Western, a flinty gunslinger is hired by a railroad tycoon to kill anyone standing in the way of his trans-American iron horse.
When average-guy Kirk starts dating drop-dead-gorgeous Molly, his friends don't see it lasting, so Kirk does everything he can to avoid losing Molly.
A socially awkward Catholic schoolgirl vows to win a dreamy classmate’s affections by taking first prize at an upcoming talent show.
This 3-D motion capture adapts Georges Remi's classic comic strip about the adventures of fearless young journalist Tintin and his trusty dog, Snowy.
At once spooky and grisly, this thriller follows a woman's quest to find the truth behind claims her mother killed three people during an exorcism.
Following a friend's suicide after her husband dumps her for a younger model, three women plot payback against their two-timing exes.
When the authorities find a drowned woman's body, a small-town psychic starts having visions of who committed the murder.

column4: The Goods: Live Hard, Sell Hard
column8: Hired to rescue a flagging car dealership during a major sale, a fast-talking closer spends his days on the lot and his nights at local strip clubs.
Washed-up professional quarterback Paul Crewe is sent to jail and forced to put together an inmate gridiron team to take on a group of prison guards.
Raised on an ashram in India, a self-styled love guru returns to his native America to settle a romantic rivalry between two pro hockey players.
A young attorney and a scrappy paralegal work to help the parents of a terminally ill boy in their suit against an insurance company.
In a backwater Iowa town, young Gilbert is torn between taking care of his troubled family and a girl who shows him new possibilities for his life.
When their 4-year-old son is murdered, a young couple fights a twisting and arduous battle trying to identify a frustratingly elusive killer.
Working under treacherous conditions, an army of dedicated rescuers struggles to find anyone who survived the World Trade Center's tragic collapse.
When a divorced writer gets a letter from an old boyfriend announcing his wife's had a baby, she returns to her hometown to reconnect with her ex.
When a father of eight and a mother of 10 prepare to wed, the couple's children attempt to sabotage the union in this remake of a 1968 comedy.
A political cartoonist, a crime reporter and a pair of cops investigate San Francisco's infamous Zodiac Killer in this thriller based on a true story.
Now the Blue Sky King, Darel must lead a rescue mission to save a Dream Walker – leaving the village under the protection of the Kulipari youth.
A trio of sky-dwelling ghosts must travel to Earth to teach sinning humans a lesson, but they somehow manage to botch each well-intentioned mission.
A new pack of Pup Star pooches stumbles upon a rival team’s plan to ruin Christmas, then ends up at the North Pole to try and save the holiday spirit.
A toy manufacturer and his wife are terrorized by a demon after their orphaned niece tries to summon her late mother's spirit using a spooky ritual.
Trapped in an empty building, nine people are forced to play a lethal game. All their movements will be recorded, and only one player can survive.
Teams of elite chefs vie to impress the world's toughest palates as they whip up iconic dishes from nine nations in this star-packed competition.
"Daily Show" host Trevor Noah touches on tacos, runaway snakes, camping, racism immunity and lessons he learned from his mother in this comedy special.

column4: 100 Things to do Before High School
column8: Led by seventh-grader C.J., three students who have been warned about the dangers of high school decide to make the best of their middle-school years.
In this live-action adventure, the gang heads to Hawaii, where Timmy learns the source of all fairy magic is in dangerous hands.
The life of cheerleader Bella Dawson turns upside down when, in a twist of fate, she becomes quarterback for her middle school's football team.
Big Time Rush heads to London for their first world tour, but when the boys' bags are switched, they get mixed up in a mission to save the world.

column4: Don't Be Afraid of the Dark
column8: Young Sally Hurst discovers she isn't alone in her new house: strange creatures live there – and they might not be as friendly as Sally thinks.
An eccentric game designer builds a library full of traps and tricks for a group of kids who score the chance to navigate his elaborate scavenger hunt.
When Arnold and his crew win a trip to San Lorenzo, their adventure in the wild forces them to take the same risky path as Arnold's missing parents.
After a century-old curse of bad luck, a determined teen embarks on a journey to break her family’s generational misfortune.
A trio of siblings gets trapped in a secret temple, where they must navigate a risky obstacle course to make it out. Inspired by the ‘90s game show.
When a shy teen transfers to a new school, he elects to mix things up by playing along with the rumor that he's a vampire.
A weekend of beach-house debauchery turns into a nightmare for a group of friends when they discover that the waters are infested with vicious sharks.
When high school girl-geek Jordan becomes a werewolf after moving to Romania, she must elude her own brother, who sets out to slay her.

column4: The Massively Mixed-Up Middle School Mystery
column8: After the school principal gets pranked, a curious crew of preteen super sleuths tests their detective skills to solve an underwater ruse.
After meeting by chance, two young musicians with differing views on love and life record an album that drastically alters their lives.
From germs and emotions to social media and more, it's the science of your world explained in a way that's refreshingly relatable.

column4: ReMastered: Tricky Dick & The Man in Black
column8: This documentary chronicles Johnny Cash's 1970 visit to the White House, where Cash's emerging ideals clashed with Richard Nixon's policies.
A talented photographer stuck in a dead-end job inherits an antique Advent calendar that may be predicting the future – and pointing her toward love.
After a traumatic incident at a party makes her a target of gossip and derision, a young college student tries to change her school's toxic culture.

column4: The Other Side of the Wind
column8: On the last day of his life, a legendary director struggles to complete a new project and contemplates his legacy in this layered film by Orson Welles.

column4: They’ll Love Me When I’m Dead
column8: Actors, crew members and others who were there discuss the tumultuous creation of Orson Welles's final, unfinished film, “The Other Side of the Wind.”
Heading a new team whose aim is to crack the cases that leave others stumped, detective Tom Thorne finds himself on the hunt for two serial killers.
Investigating a series of attacks on young women, detective Tom Thorne is dragged back into the nightmares of his past as he races to find a killer.
Here comes the bride, and she's got plenty to say. Newlywed Iliza Shlesinger dissects wedding traditions as she mines her nuptials for laughs.
After ditching her domestic life to become a chef, a clueless maid crosses paths with two charming suitors who help her reach her dreams.
Follow Santiago Artemis, a Buenos Aires fashion dynamo, as he makes his dreams come true while grappling with his love life, therapist and clients.
Fearlessly funny stand-up comic and sitcom star Donald Glover puts on a live show in New York, confessing his love for Cocoa Puffs and Toys "R" Us.
Go behind the scenes at Pixar Animation Studios with this Emmy-nominated documentary tracing the creation and history of the groundbreaking company.
A cop-turned-convict discovers a crime syndicate inside a prison lorded over by an inmate crime boss – and joins in on their nightly heists.

column4: Colin Quinn: The New York Story
column8: The "SNL" veteran performs his off-Broadway show about the history of New York and the people who shape its personality. Directed by Jerry Seinfeld.
A shrewd teenager and her wisecracking best friend plan to get rich or die trying by following in the footsteps of a flashy female drug dealer.
A former Colombian guerrilla fighter faces challenges as she reintegrates into society and tries to overcome her traumatic memories.
A dizzying chronicle of excess and deception dissects a fascinating case of fine-wine fraud and the con man who cheated investors out of millions.

column4: Naomi and Ely's No Kiss List
column8: Naomi and her gay best friend, Ely, have been inseparable since childhood, but their bond faces its biggest test yet when they fall for the same guy.
After committing suicide, a washed-up rocker returns from the grave to torment the five people who betrayed him in life.
When a wardrobe malfunction goes viral, a bubbly live streamer struggles to navigate her classmates' cruel judgment and the small town she lives in.
After the deities Bai Qian and Ye Hua meet and fall in love, their romance stands the test of three lifetimes — each an epic in its own right.
Worlds collide and lives shatter when Altagracia, a powerful and elegant businesswoman, plots a ruthless revenge while falling in love.
When her fugitive husband leaves her homeless and penniless, a once-wealthy woman has no other choice but to join the working class.
Christmas comes early for an aspiring young journalist when she's sent abroad to get the scoop on a dashing prince who's poised to be king.

column4: Jim & Andy: The Great Beyond - Featuring a Very Special, Contractually Obligated Mention of Tony Clifton
column8: Through the lens of his stunningly immersive performance as Andy Kaufman, Jim Carrey ponders the meaning of life, reality, identity and career.

column4: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Face Your Fears
column8: In three tales about fear, a baby elephant gets captured by a circus, two boys enter a haunted house and a parrot faces his fear of flying.
Two Mississippi families – one black, one white – confront the brutal realities of prejudice, farming and friendship in a divided World War II era.
When a gift sack full of kittens gives Santa a bad allergic reaction, the kitties have to take over and deliver the presents on time.
Three rival freelance stringers scour the streets at night to film crime scenes, fires, accidents – and anything else they can sell to news outlets.
When a woman is brutally murdered on a playground, a group of detectives find themselves drawn into a dark conspiracy as they search for the killer.
A Hollywood stuntman and getaway driver is lured from his isolated life by a lovely neighbor – until her violent husband is released from prison.
Decades after a nuclear war, survivors on the moon revisit Earth to locate a potential power source – and find shape-shifting reptiles instead.

column4: Jeff Dunham: All Over the Map
column8: America's most beloved ventriloquist hits the road, bringing along all of his most popular pals, including Achmed, Peanut and Walter.
At the beginning of the 20th century, circumstances drive a young, idealistic suffragette to find radical approaches to fighting male oppression.
Determined to save an Amazon tribe being squeezed by logging, a group of students finds nothing but trouble when their plane crashes in the jungle.
After a look-alike takes over her account, a cam girl with a growing fan base sets out to identify the mysterious culprit and reclaim her own identity.
These six intimate stories explore the abiding emotional bonds that form between dogs and their caregivers, no matter the circumstances.
Aspiring to be an internet celebrity and make big bucks, a filmmaker travels the world to learn the tricks of the trade from social media influencers.
Witness the birth of the Mexican drug war in the 1980s as a gritty new "Narcos" saga chronicles the true story of the Guadalajara cartel's ascent.
To spice up a dinner party, old friends agree to share every private message that pops up on their phones – with disastrous results.
Ranging from absurd to profound, these Western vignettes from the Coen brothers follow the adventures of outlaws and settlers on the American frontier.
When a down-to-earth Chicago baker and a soon-to-be princess discover they look like twins, they hatch a Christmastime plan to trade places.
Go behind the scenes with Brazilian pop icon Anitta, along with her friends and family, as she aims to create a new song and music video each month.
In a postapocalyptic world, rag-doll robots hide in fear from dangerous machines out to exterminate them, until a brave newcomer joins the group.
Encountering each other after a long separation, two childhood friends from orphanage must overcome great odds to fulfill an old promise and find love.
In 1980s Tokyo, an enigmatic expat is suspected of killing her friend, who's gone missing in the wake of their love triangle with a local photographer.
In the most remote areas of the Amazon jungle, a writer and his anthropologist friend meet communities who have resisted change for centuries.
Mía's vacation with her dad is disrupted by the surprise arrival of Lupe, Mercedes, Juanma and Álvaro as their school drama moves lakeside.
A pampered but kind-hearted average joe ditches his romancing and peacekeeping ways when he’s framed for a murder he didn’t commit.
A world-weary man’s self-imposed home confinement becomes a comedy of errors with the simultaneous arrivals of a peculiar package and a curious journalist.

column4: I'm with the Band: Nasty Cherry
column8: In an unfiltered, intimate docuseries, pop star mentor Charli XCX finds out what it takes to build – and break – a real, badass all-girl punk band.
After a chance encounter in LA, two teens from different social backgrounds reunite at an exclusive high school attended by Korea’s über rich.
The seniors in Sakuragaoka High School's music club live out the graduation trip of their dreams when they celebrate by performing in London.
A selfish postman and a reclusive toymaker form an unlikely friendship, delivering joy to a cold, dark town that desperately needs it.

column4: La Robe De Mariee Des Cieux
column8: After a chance encounter that ends on bad terms, two clashing strangers soon cross paths again as their fates become inevitably intertwined.
Anna chooses February 29 to propose marriage to her boyfriend, but after meeting a charming innkeeper, she must evaluate her original plans.
An unfortunate accident alters the life of a high school basketball prodigy, who abandons his beloved sport and becomes entangled in a love triangle.
A refined young Joseon scholar's life turns upside down after he rescues a drunk princess who later accuses him of taking something precious from her.
A trio of filmmakers treks across India to explore the correlation between vanishing rivers, massive energy projects and renewable energy sources.
An intense rivalry between Henry Ford II of the Ford Motor Company and Enzo Ferrari results in the most epic showdown in racing history.
A band of misfit rich kids in Mexico strike out on their own selling MDMA and quickly run into trouble with other narcos, the law and their families.
When a lonely teenager skips his morning classes to sit in a lovely garden, he meets a mysterious older woman who shares his feelings of alienation.
Trapped on an island destroyed by a tsunami, the students of an elite school try to hold on to hope. But mysterious forces seem to work against them.
Spirited high school misfits with hearts of gold begin their journeys into adulthood as they navigate school, friendship, romance and heartbreak.
When an aging father seeks the help of a doctor and a journalist to look for the son who left him 16 years ago, he learns some surprising truths.
Scouted by a famous Spanish club, Valt Aoi heads to Spain. With their sights on the World League, he and his teammates face the European League first.
A wedding planner’s world is turned upside down when a handsome private investigator is hired to disrupt one of her biggest jobs.
Up against a corrupt government official and crushing poverty, a young boy in the Delhi slums attempts to raise funds to build himself his own toilet.
With their relationship running on autopilot, a discontent husband and wife must confront their issues while on a trip with the extended family.
Hoping to find answers to her estranged father's mysterious illness, a young woman visits his old villa and uncovers a horrifying truth from the past.
Through interviews with locals, this documentary investigates the triggers and outcomes of the 2013 communal riots in the heart of Uttar Pradesh.
While trying to buy his wife a set-top box, a struggling writer and his pal get entangled in the domino effect of a spectacularly botched drug deal.
Given unprecedented access to soldiers and terrorists alike, journalist Michael Ware presents an epic, uncensored, intimate account of the Iraq War.
As a lonely widower prepares to leave India to live with his children in America, he looks back on past memories and unfinished business.
When his wife begins to exhibit alarming behavior, a husband tries to find whether she suffers from a personality disorder or something more sinister.
In this first full Shopkins movie, Peppa-Mint is the new Shoppie in town who stirs things up by hosting a team cooking competition.
Beloved movie star Scarletta Gateau visits Shopville and recruits the Shopkins for a quest through the jungle to the mysterious world of Pawville.
The Shopkins and Shoppies jet around the world in search of missing friend Kooky Cookie, a stolen diamond and more vloggable adventure.
After an unexpected misstep, a crew of skilled Parisian robbers find themselves forced to carry out a daring heist for a powerful crime organization.
In 1843, crippled Martin returns from war to his Basque hometown and finds his brother has grown into a giant, which they turn into a circus act.
A timid man gets unexpected superpowers while trying to save his family's land and a sacred tree from a ruthless tycoon.
On the island of Rocky Perch, security company owner Chuck Adoodledoo and his friends provide kung fu-style protection for their fellow bird citizens.
During an uprising in Russia's St. Petersburg, teen girl Lucky meets handsome Aditya, the Indian ambassador's son, and together they flee the chaos.

column4: The Irregular at Magic High School
column8: Siblings Tatsuya and Miyuki enroll at Magic High School, where Miyuki's honors status comes between her and her underachieving older brother.
An ambitious young law enforcement graduate is thrilled when her idol takes her on as a trainee. But his methods aren't anything like she imagined.
An Indian American man living with his artistic wife and contentious father-in-law struggles to handle his household and a foundering IT company.
The cerebral and popular German cabaret comic expounds his theories on gender norms, primal instincts and a decidedly gastrointestinal Big Bang.
This coming-of-age tale follows Rahul, a young boy growing up in a Mumbai slum whose alcoholic father abuses him and his mother.

column4: Oliver Stone's Untold History of the United States
column8: This documentary series offers an alternative take on modern American history, focusing on underreported events that shaped the nation's character.

column4: Clarence Clemons: Who Do I Think I Am?
column8: This intimate documentary follows the life of legendary saxophonist Clarence Clemons and his spiritual awakening before his death in 2011.

column4: Fadily Camara : La plus drôle de tes copines
column8: Irrepressible French comedian Fadily Camara weaves jokes, vivid characters and physical comedy into a lively stand-up show at La Cigale in Paris.
Love leaps off the page when an astronomer magically meets her comic book hero in the flesh, but learns that his fictional problems are very real.

column4: DeRay Davis: How to Act Black
column8: Dynamic comic DeRay Davis hits the stage like a ball of fire, nailing the finer points of living, dating and handling show business as a black man.
While serving as the marshal of rowdy Abilene, Kansas, "Wild Bill" Hickok uses guns and gall to tidy up the lawless frontier town.

column4: Chelsea Peretti: One of the Greats
column8: "Brooklyn Nine-Nine" star Chelsea Peretti showcases her diverse talents in this dark yet silly reimagining of the comedy special.
Will Ferrell stars as a Spanish-speaking cowboy in this comedy about a Mexican clan trying to rescue their ranch from greedy creditors.
In this docuseries, soccer great Diego Maradona comes to Culiacán, the heart of the Sinaloa Cartel, to save the local team, the Dorados, and maybe himself, too.
In a mazelike Manila slum, at war with incensed civilians and a brutal cartel, special agent Nina Manigan must fight her way through one fierce night.
Grammy-winning singer Loudon Wainwright III reflects upon his unique relationship with his father in an evening of original songs and heartfelt stories.
A war veteran plagued by guilt over his final mission teams up with his best friend's widow to infiltrate a dangerous Copenhagen biker gang.
Featuring interviews, insights and archival footage, this documentary aims to reveal how historical events shaped the music of John Coltrane.
Armed with boyish charm and a sharp wit, the former "SNL" writer offers sly takes on marriage, his beef with babies and the time he met Bill Clinton.
After being dishonorably discharged from the Navy Seals, Bob and David are back serving our country the way they do best – making sketch comedy.

column4: Jeff Garlin: Our Man In Chicago
column8: Comedian Jeff Garlin (unintentionally) celebrates his 37th year of stand-up and shares his learnings on love, loss, success and food addiction.
At the end of their low-budget tour, a punk band accepts a gig at an isolated rural club, only to discover that their hosts are neo-Nazis.
This documentary follows the 2016 tour of beloved rock band The Tragically Hip as they make their way across Canada one last time.
This stream-of-consciousness drama centers on a day in the life of a gay college professor who's reeling from his longtime lover's recent death.

column4: Put Your Head on My Shoulder
column8: On the cusp of graduation, an accounting major searching for her career winds up living with a genius physics student who shakes up her daily routine.
After a near-death trip home, a Marine looking to help his comrade survive returns to the underground world of MMA, where new battles await.
Traumatized by combat, newly returned war veterans find solace in service dogs that guide them back to a fulfilling civilian life.
Two veteran buddy cops are back for a second chapter, this time to tackle a car theft ring that turns out to be much more than they bargained for.

column4: The Beginning of Life: The Series
column8: Using breakthroughs in technology and neuroscience, this series examines how environment affects infants – and how infants can affect our future.

column4: True Memoirs of an International Assassin
column8: After his publisher markets his crime novel as a memoir, a novice author finds himself forcibly recruited into a deadly political plot in Venezuela.
The history of military tanks unfolds in a documentary series that traces their role in history and geopolitics from World War I to the 21st century.
While investigating a possible outbreak at an Arctic research facility, scientists discover a new virus that could wipe out every human on the planet.
In an old shipyard town in France, sociopolitical tensions beset a writing workshop where the instructor notices a student with a dark side.
The musings of comedian Bill Burr are let loose in this special, which was filmed at the historic Fillmore Auditorium in San Francisco.
Featuring the boys of Johnny's West, a gang of zany transfer students are recruited for a mysterious mission ordained by their shadowy principal.
Raw and outspoken, comedian Alexis de Anda bares her soul about weddings, exercise, sex, gynecologists, drugs and much more in this stand-up special.
Chile's Natalia Valdebenito hits Santiago's Teatro Caupolicán with a one-woman show steeped in irony, a dash of improv and her own personal style.
In lawless badlands, reclusive Cabeleira sets out to discover the fate of his gunman father and grows to be a feared assassin himself.
This documentary series examines the Einsatzgruppen, Nazis responsible for the mass murder of Jews, Romani and Soviet prisoners in Eastern Europe.
The Irish American comic riffs on everything from growing up in Missouri, signing up her parents to be Uber drivers and anything to do with bacon.
A stylist, a hair designer and a makeup artist team up to give Britain's biggest fashion disasters some much-needed makeunders.
Tasked with escorting a prosecution witness to court, an aging cop gears up for the 16-block trek – but they'll be lucky to make it there alive.

After one of his high school students attacks him, dedicated teacher Trevor Garfield grows weary of the gang warfare in the New York City school system and moves to California to teach there, thinking it must be a less hostile environment.
The residents of an isolated town look to revive their home's identity when a group of foreigners unexpectedly arrive, bringing culture shock with them.
Two astronauts attempt to brave a life in Earth's orbit on a record-setting mission to see if humans have the endurance to survive a flight to Mars.
In a future where regeneration technology lets humans live indefinitely, a cop and a troubled young woman investigate a strange wave of youth suicides.
A neo-Nazi gets sent to prison for murder and comes out a changed man. But can he prevent his younger brother from following in his footsteps?
Time passes and tension mounts in a Florida police station as an estranged interracial couple awaits news of their missing teenage son.
After a gentle businessman is forced to get anger management counseling, his therapist moves in – but turns out to have anger issues of his own.
Recovered cockpit footage and telling interviews reveal the true stories of US fighter pilots in one of the largest combat strikes in history.

column4: Barbie Dreamhouse Adventures: Go Team Roberts
column8: As the Roberts family heads to Costa Rica to investigate a mermaid legend, Barbie takes on a summer job at a water park run by a devious boss.
Elizabeth Taylor won an Oscar as Gloria Wandrous, a stylish call girl who yearns to go straight, especially after she thinks she's found Mr. Right.

column4: Cat on a Hot Tin Roof
column8: Members of a Southern clan scramble to curry favor with a dying, wealthy patriarch in this adaptation of Tennessee Williams's sizzling stage drama.
Stranded at school before holiday break, a precocious girl gets into the spirit of saving when a trio of robbers trespass and hold the janitor hostage.
Two girls realize they're both visiting grandparents they’ve never met and decide to switch places to see how the other half lives.
With Christmas just around the corner, sisters Miranda and Lyla bring their families to their childhood home, where rivalries don't take a holiday.
A stylin' special agent chases down drug lords and does her part to stop trafficking. Soon, she finds herself seeking revenge on a dealer.
A mild-mannered janitor duped into believing he's an undercover agent stumbles into an international arms ring plot involving the CIA and the FBI.
A young physician and his beautiful mistress get swept up in the danger and drama of the Bolshevik Revolution in this Oscar-winning epic.
A notorious thief allies with a street racer for a grand heist involving an elaborate game of deceit with authorities, who have their own dirty secrets.
When Blitzen suddenly retires, a miniature horse determined to join Santa's reindeer team faces fierce competition in the North Pole tryouts.
Recruited by a British agent, Shaolin master Lee infiltrates a remote island and a brutal martial arts tournament to spy on a sinister crime lord.
An entrepreneur prone to partying and his estranged brother, a teacher resigned to a humdrum life, begin to bond under fragile circumstances.
When terrorists hijack a 747 and turn it into a nerve gas bomb aimed at Washington, D.C., commandos use an experimental plane to try to stop them.
A tough homicide cop faces his most dangerous assignment when he must stop a murderous evil spirit who can move from one host to the next.

column4: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
column8: A sportswriter and his Samoan lawyer embark on a hallucinogenic three-day romp from Los Angeles to Las Vegas in this counterculture cult favorite.
In this documentary, survivors recall the catastrophic 2018 Camp Fire, which razed the town of Paradise and became California’s deadliest wildfire.
A pulp-fiction sci-fi classic, Forbidden Planet stars Leslie Nielsen as a heroic starship captain who finds the paradise planet Altair-IV.
Tired of dealing with boyfriends who wrong them, gal pals Lauren, Emily and Andrea decide to turn the tables and become the players themselves.
Gigi's an avant-garde French waif being groomed as the fille de joie of affluent and handsome Gaston. Soon Gigi metamorphoses into a stunning beauty.
In this witty whodunit, wealthy guests and their servants gather for a weekend stay at the home of Sir William McCordle, who is soon found murdered.
After a car crash, a criminal psychiatrist awakens to find that she's a patient in the same mental institution that currently employs her.
John Travolta and Olivia Newton-John star in this hit musical comedy about a greaser and the good girl he falls for – much to his friends' chagrin.
As Helena gains the love and trust of a dangerous heroin cartel leader in 1960s Barcelona, she hones the skills she needs to rise up the ranks.

column4: Harlem Globetrotters: The Team That Changed the World
column8: Relive the greatest moments of the Harlem Globetrotters with this documentary that chronicles the team's legendary 1948 defeat over the Minneapolis Lakers and their historic 1951 Berlin trip.
BFFs Wesley and Georgie and their silly cat sidekick Pretzel transform into ninjas and enter a magic world, where they solve problems and save the day.
When her husband abruptly ends their marriage, empty nester Kate embarks on a solo second honeymoon in Africa, finding purpose – and potential romance.
Home for the holidays, a broke puppeteer knows there’s treasure buried somewhere under her town. To find it, all she has to do is die – almost.

column4: How to Be a Latin Lover
column8: When an aging Lothario gets the boot from his sugar mama, he must pull out all the stops to find a new female sponsor.
Dray lives life one woman at a time and is the envy of all his friends, until his sister decides to show him the error of his philandering ways.
After the end of apartheid, newly elected President Nelson Mandela uses the 1995 World Cup rugby matches to unite his people in South Africa.
Jimi Hendrix's family, friends, and fellow musicians discuss his life and influence. Hendrix also appears in classic performance footage.

A wealthy, despicable businessman comes to the realization that he may lose half his fortune to the obnoxious wife he's trying to divorce. So, he decides to arrange his own kidnapping in order to wipe himself out and claim poverty.
A motley crew of apocalypse survivors living at an abandoned truck stop never suspects that the pregnant woman among them is carrying the Messiah.
When Pedro marries her sister, Tita throws herself into her cooking – and discovers she can transfer her emotions through the food she prepares.

column4: Listen Up! The Lives of Quincy Jones
column8: Steering clear of convention, this affecting documentary pays tribute to the life and work of composer, musician and producer Quincy Jones, one of the best-known and most respected men in the music industry.
In the 23rd century, inhabitants of a domed city exist in a world filled with life's pleasures – but no one is allowed to live past the age of 30.
In this black comedy, an English professor marries his landlady to get closer to his forbidden obsession: her teenage daughter.
In this urban romantic comedy set in Chicago, the ups and downs of courtship play out between a young black poet and a pretty shutterbug.
A woman joins the janitorial staff of the Federal Reserve Bank and conspires with two co-workers to pilfer old money that's scheduled to be destroyed.
To keep the boys in line, student council president Misaki runs the school with an iron fist – while secretly working as a waitress at a maid café.
TV news reporter James Russell helps put small-time criminal Franklin Hatchett in jail, but turns to protecting Hatchett when he escapes from prison.
Three friends uncover the truth about a scary abandoned house in their neighborhood that has a personality of its own and seems to be eating people.
Marlon Brando gives a nuanced performance as the aristocratic Lt. Fletcher Christian, an officer aboard the HMS Bounty who leads a mutiny against the ship's tyrannical Capt. Bligh.
When Ignacio learns of an orphanage's financial woes, he pitches in to help – by disguising himself and joining the professional wrestling circuit.

In this parody of the Lethal Weapon franchise, criminals murder a detective and steal her prized evidence: microfilm with a recipe for cocaine cookies. Luckily, loose-cannon cop Jack Colt and his by-the-book partner, Wes Luger, are on the case.
Frank Sinatra leads an all-star cast as Danny Ocean, who decides to knock over a few casinos on the Las Vegas Strip with his buddies.
This fictionalized account of three real-life notorious Harlem drug dealers is told in flashbacks as they plunge into the world of hustling.
The Fab Five touch down in Tokyo to spread the joy, explore the culture, and help four Japanese men and women find the confidence to be themselves.
When Jim Stark arrives in a new town with his troubled past firmly in tow, he quickly falls for the girl next door and befriends the vulnerable Plato.
April and Frank's marriage unravels when a plan to change their "perfect" lives becomes their last hope to escape lives engulfed in emptiness.
A woman is thrilled to find out she's pregnant. But as her belly grows, the more certain she becomes that her unborn child is in serious danger.
A law student befriends and "befoes" a fellow gambling addict and a club owner, and tensions run high when they must come up with $15k in just 5 days.
During a visit to the Bronx to help out at his uncle's store, a cheerful martial arts expert springs into action when a gang terrorizes the shop.
Fleeing the family business and an arranged marriage, Santa’s daughter chooses a magical adventure of her own: College.
A man returns home after being released from a psychiatric hospital, where he'd been confined since age 12 for murdering his mother and her lover.
In 1950s Harlem, three singing sisters hit the big time and end up losing one another in this musical melodrama inspired by the Supremes.
The seemingly invincible Spider-Man goes up against an all-new crop of villains in the third installment of the blockbuster adventure series.

column4: Spitfire: The Plane that Saved the World
column8: In this epic documentary, last-surviving veterans trace the history of a legendary fighter aircraft that dominated the air during the Battle of Britain.
Brennan and Dale might be grown men, but that doesn't stop a childish sibling rivalry from erupting after Brennan's mom marries Dale's dad.
To get away from the thug life, cocaine dealer Youngblood Priest puts together one last deal that will net him enough money to start over.
New York City radio host Erica Bain decides to take the law into her own hands after losing her fiancé in a brutal Central Park attack.
A progressive new minister's arrival in a small village threatens to end an age-old tradition that brings a yuletide miracle to one of the residents.

In Depression-era New Orleans, cocksure stud poker player Eric Stoner – the titular Cincinnati Kid – challenges longtime champ Lancey "The Man" Howard to a showdown at the table, where a war of wills – and nerve – ensues.
Nicholas receives an unusual birthday present from his brother, Conrad – a gift certificate to play a unique kind of game formulated by "CRS."
In World War II, a battalion goes on a daring rescue mission to liberate the Americans and Filipinos who've been captured by the Japanese.

column4: The House of Flowers Presents: The Funeral
column8: The de la Mora siblings publicly mourn the death of their mother amid multiple surprises and mishaps at Virginia's funeral.
Wayward Prince Hal must turn from carouser to warrior king as he faces hostilities from inside and outside the castle walls in the battle for England.
Private eye Joe Hallenbeck is forced to team up with a disgraced quarterback to uncover a conspiracy by a politician and a football team owner.
A gravity-defying boy raised in seclusion matures into an extraordinary man – and an international celebrity – who longs for human connection.
A computer hacker learns that what most people perceive as reality is actually a simulation created by machines, and joins a rebellion to break free.
The crew must protect Zion, the last outpost still under human control, after it is pinpointed by the machines responsible for the Matrix.
The final installment in the Matrix trilogy finds an unconscious Neo trapped in a subway station in a zone between the Matrix and the machine world.

column4: The Old Thieves: The Legend of Artegios
column8: While carrying out prison sentences, five notorious thieves in Mexico City share their principles, preferred methods and respect for the craft.
When law student Darby Shaw theorizes about the assassinations of two Supreme Court justices, she is put in danger and turns to a reporter for help.
After a government spy is hospitalized, New York City cab driver Jimmy unwillingly takes over the spy's role – with the aid of a computerized tuxedo.
The spotlight shines on iconic jazz pianist and composer Thelonious Monk in this 1988 documentary featuring vintage performance clips and interviews.
It's Grabbleapple harvest season in the Rainbow Kingdom ... but Glummy Glooma doesn't want autumn to come. Can True and her friends save the festival?
Moments after he arrives in Spain for an antiterrorism summit, U.S. President Ashton is shot.
José Olaya, a Spanish miner, emigrates to Argentina in 1934, while his son, an architect, moves to Spain after Argentina's economic collapse in 2001.
A mysterious classmate leads four idealistic teens in a revolt against a rising tide of nationalistic fervor, but their movement takes a dark turn.
When a spoiled girl pushes her father too far with her spending and outlandish behavior, he ships the Malibu princess off to a strict boarding school.
This introspective rockumentary follows the career triumphs and intimate moments of legendary Mexican band Zoé as they embark on a global tour.
Looking to survive in a world taken over by zombies, a dorky college student teams with an urban roughneck and a pair of grifter sisters.
After receiving an anonymous tip about a bomb, a police commissioner must negotiate with the terrorist, who demands the release of four militants.
A cop full of self-doubt loses his gun five days before he's due to leave the force, and becomes an unexpected hero as he tries to retrieve it.
In this high-tension thriller, an anonymous caller on a cell phone threatens to harm a man's family if he doesn't carry out every order.
After being accused of cheating on a reality TV show, a dance troupe seeks to redeem itself by winning the World Hip-Hop Dance Championship.
Thrown out of the elite dance studio he founded, Vishnu's spirits rebound when he sees young street dancers prepping for an annual contest.
This animated retelling of the classic Indian tale of Prince Arjun – part of the Sanskrit epic Mahabharata – begins during the prince's youth.
When a dispute breaks out between five siblings over their mother’s property, one devoted son will go to any lengths to protect her land.
Years after rejecting Barfii, a hearing and speech impaired young man, for a more "appropriate" suitor, Shruti finds herself falling for him.
When two slackers' made-up sport, BASEketball, becomes a national craze, they hope to cash in on the basketball/baseball hybrid's popularity.
The adorable residents of Sylvanian Village always have lots of fun with their friends and families!

column4: Calico Critters: A Town of Dreams
column8: Freya heads into town with her mother for a very special occasion: a dress designed by her sister Stella is going to be in a fashion show!

column4: Calico Critters: The Treasure of Calico Village
column8: Freya and her friends inspire the mayor to put on a competition at the fete to pick the loveliest thing in Sylvanian Village.
With a horde of enemy invaders bearing down, four sons of an illustrious Sikh guru lead a tiny but valiant army into a desperate fight for freedom.
Having risen from humble beginnings, an ambitious young man sets his sights on winning a major dance competition that could catapult him to fame.
Still reeling from a business failure, the restaurant manager of a ski resort finds her world jolted by a new chef, who has his own hidden past.
Mistaking a broke, small-time hustler for a millionaire, two bumbling fishermen hatch a scheme to use him to help pay off their debts.
In a last-ditch effort, the jaded coach of the Southall United Football Club assembles a ragtag team and helps lead the team to a comeback season.
An accountant and a producer hatch a scheme to finance a movie, while making every effort to ensure that it flops so they may pocket the difference.
A struggling math teacher holds down a second job to keep his family afloat. But when he receives a wedding invitation, he's determined to attend.
During a wilderness getaway, a gang of sociopathic criminals kidnap a woman and assault her husband, who must summon all his strength to save her.

column4: Edmilson Filho: Notas, Comedy about Relationships
column8: Brazilian comedian Edmilson Filho walks his audience through the stages of a modern relationship, playing up the differences between men and women.
Leon Vitali had a thriving acting career most others would envy. Then he gave it all up to devote himself completely to the vision of Stanley Kubrick.
An Indian man who has become a major business mogul in Canada must return to his homeland where he's reviled due to being wrongly branded a traitor.
Organized crime enforcer Miles Daly strives to reinvent himself as a Hollywood filmmaker in this satire based on Elmore Leonard's best-selling novel.
Former con artist Sanju surrounds himself with the finer things, a blissful life troubled by only one thing: his wife, who wants even more.
A mysterious, clever girl named Nanno transfers to different schools, exposing the lies and misdeeds of the students and faculty at every turn.
Anticipating the next move in a serial killer's grisly game, a police chief realizes that his daughter and estranged wife are the next likely victims.
Stories of personal victories coincide with Team India's battle for the Cricket World Cup in this engaging ensemble drama.
One woman experiences the dramatic highs and lows of fame in this voyeuristic glimpse past the glitz and glamour of a Bollywood superstar's life.
A young man returns to his native village on a mission of vengeance after his father commits suicide in the wake of false accusations.
Three professional friends, all husbands living with domineering wives, take a well-deserved vacation in the resort city of Goa.
Without fully realizing the consequences, a boy who wants to relocate from India to Canada sells his heart to a gangster in need of a transplant.
This Bollywood drama tells the story of three best friends who dream of starting a cricket training academy in Ahmedabad for very different reasons.
Cheenu dreams of resurrecting the restaurant he has inherited to its former glory, but his brother, a compulsive gambler, loses the place to a cop.

column4: Katt Williams: The Pimp Chronicles: Pt. 1
column8: In this 2006 show, comic Katt Williams uses his edgy style and personal experiences to paint a sassy, hilarious portrait of life in black America.
After falling in love during college, architect Maddy and free spirit Payal have five wonderful years together, until a mystery suddenly divides them.
A group of Mumbai up-and-comers search for love and struggle for success in this ensemble drama that centers on an eager young call-center executive.
Alternative comic Marc Maron is back on stage in New York to talk Chinese food, drug abuse, sex in hotel rooms and life with his girlfriend.
When his father moves from the U.S. to Heidelberg, Germany, an African American teenager struggles to find his place and pursue his hip-hop dreams.
A moving portrayal of the 2006 train bombings in Mumbai, this Indian drama follows the interconnected stories of several strangers.
When they both fall for the same girl, best pals and shameless womanizers Prince and Jassi go head-to-head to compete for her love.
This thriller tells the true story of model Jessica Lall – who was shot dead in a restaurant – and the campaign to bring her killer to justice.
Starting as a petty thief, a man rises to become one of the city's biggest operators and carves out the kind of lifestyle he'd once only dreamed of.
Paan Singh Tomar goes from celebrated runner to star brigand and rebel when life after sports fails to unfold as planned.
A small-time con man assembles a team to help him avenge the death of his partner-in-crime at the hands of a powerful gangster.
In this Bollywood drama, a corporate go-getter sees his priorities shift when personal tragedy brings him face-to-face with political corruption.
Asked to deliver a package for a friend, Madhu gets her fiancé, Jayaganthan, to take care of it, and he then passes the task to one of his roommates.
A policeman's son overcomes his reluctance to join the force following a brutal attack on his father and ends up in the middle of a robbery case.
Self-proclaimed "Queen of Comedy" Sommore storms the stage to deliver a riotous stand-up performance in Charlotte, North Carolina.
After noting a strange odor in his child’s pajamas, a single dad’s search for the source uncovers potentially toxic secrets of the chemical industry.

column4: The Great British Baking Show: The Beginnings
column8: A dozen amateur bakers amiably compete for the coveted title of Britain's best as they whip up tasty treats for judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood.
This documentary highlights the endangered existence of the Scottish wildcats, and the conservation efforts required to prevent their extinction.

column4: The Untold Tales of Armistead Maupin
column8: This documentary traces the life of "Tales of the City" author Armistead Maupin, from his conservative roots to his rise as an LGBTQ champion.

column4: The Water Horse: Legend of the Deep
column8: A boy watches an egg he found hatch into something incredible. But how long can he keep such a big secret from his mom – and the Scottish government?
Two computer scientists work to achieve technological singularity to create a world where computers can transcend the abilities of the human brain.
Three youths from rural South Africa set out for Johannesburg, where they're thrust into the seedy underbelly of the city and must fight to survive.
An educated man assists the illiterate residents of his village with written correspondence, sometimes manipulating the letters to suit his interests.
A poor family’s goat suddenly acquires divine status, sparking a widespread frenzy as everyone clamors to benefit from its unexpected celebrity.
When his cruel uncle abandons him, a young orphan learns to access the untapped superpowers that have been waiting within him all along.
Six friends decide to undertake a grueling mountain trek, only to find that the difficulties in store for them are not merely physical.
Heirless Maharaj Brajbhan leaves his throne to his cousin Vikram, but when Brajbhan's wife, Badi Rani, finally conceives, Vikram plots to destroy her.
After having her heart broken by a man who seduced her at a party, a young, ambitious woman concocts a scheme to get revenge.
Low TV ratings drive a well-known journalist to concoct a plan to interview a notorious underworld figure who is also a suspected terrorist.
Professional burglar and blowtorch expert Víctor is recruited by the Russian mafia to break into a vault as part of an elaborate bank heist.
In the 1980s, a recently discarded television set from the 1960s refuses to accept its fate and tries to break out of the junkyard.
A competitive streetcar racer's obsession with winning drive him to develop a vehicle with an innovative engine that's never been used before.
Trace the history of Hitler's armored private train, a 15-car mobile headquarters boasting state-of-the-art communications and anti-aircraft cannons.
While visiting India for her cousin's wedding, a Canadian girl develops strong feelings for a boy from a lower caste.
A man's decision to marry three women, to keep them from committing suicide, complicates his relationship with his girlfriend.
A railway stationmaster tries to cope with his wife's death, his estrangement from his son and the corrupt world in which he lives.
Host RJ Anmol conducts in-depth interviews with prominent Indian celebrities, who share the stories that lie behind their successes and failures.

column4: One Heart: The A.R. Rahman Concert Film
column8: In this concert film, Indian musical maestro A.R. Rahman performs 15 of his most popular songs and reveals himself through interviews and clips.
Christmas is just around the corner, but Pettersson and Findus are worried the snowy weather (and lack of a tree) may keep them from celebrating.
During a time of political turmoil, a mother goes on a journey in search of her missing son, who has been misjudged and labeled a terrorist.
In a village where girls are auctioned off rather than married, a man falls in love with a girl who is about to face the bidders.
Two common boys travel from India to Thailand to find success and money, enjoying their friendship and finding ways to cheat the cheats.
This documentary explores the rich heritage of Indian classical music and the reasons behind its modern decline in popularity.
A former professional boxer serving time in a brutal labor camp must fight incredible odds to gain his freedom and avenge an act of violence.
With the help of a gutsy female detective, a prosecutor who has lost the ability to feel empathy tackles a murder case amid political corruption.
As a killer stalks the streets, a troubled young courier suspects that a doctor may be the long-lost sister he hasn't seen since childhood.
Five lawyers from different firms develop a strong bond of friendship that is occasionally tested by their court cases and growing romantic feelings.
A single mother of five struggles for decades to forge a successful business empire, only to see her family descend into animosity and betrayal.
An orphaned Chinese woman in Singapore refuses to yield to her lowly station in life, setting her family on a tumultuous course for generations.
A devious businessman covets his partner's priceless treasure map, while a related murder case calls into question some biological family ties.
Spanning 30 years, a group of dedicated and diverse friends experiences happiness and hardship in a newly independent Singapore.

column4: Trip to Bhangarh: Asia's Most Haunted Place
