column8: To amuse themselves, six college friends decide to pay a visit to a fortress believed by some to be the most haunted place in Asia.
Jake's date with his dream girl takes a turn when she disappears, and Jake's grandpa – a former intelligence officer – sets out to find her.
In a modern adaptation of a mythological tale, a devoted wife is willing to do whatever it takes to rescue her husband from the clutches of death.
A soon-to-be-retiring Mr. Lino teaches 20-something Nin the strict rules of his new warehouse job in this dramedy about the absurdities of work life.
The patriarch of a wealthy family with one industrious son and one who's a playboy arranges for the marriage of one to the woman the other loves.

column4: A Grand Night In: The Story of Aardman
column8: Aardman Animations icons Wallace & Gromit, Morph and more join fans and collaborators for a retrospective celebrating the studio's 40th anniversary.
Betrothed while in utero, a resort group president enters into an arranged marriage with a legal assistant. Despite their bickering, love blooms.
When her uptight new boss and landlord starts a war on office romances, plucky Liang-liang quickly starts looking for ways to get him to lighten up.
After a chance meeting at a ballpark, the kind son of a former gangster tries to help an outgoing radio DJ get over her recent heartbreak.
A wealthy heir's search for a nameless childhood sweetheart leads him to an inn run by a family with three sisters. But which one is his true love?
When a marriage-phobic woman hires a seductress to test how faithful her eager-to-wed boyfriend is, her plan takes an unexpected turn.
When her loved ones cook up a morbid plan to make her take time off from work, Yang Yiru goes on a vacation, truly believing she has terminal cancer.

column4: Norman Lear: Just Another Version of You
column8: This documentary turns the spotlight on the man behind the iconic "All in the Family," with comments from friends, family and famous collaborators.
Pac aims to keep Berry Day the happiest day ever by unraveling a curious mystery about his parents and thwarting Betrayus's plan to capture Santa Pac.
Spanish provincialism is put into the spotlight as a man from the Basque Country embarks on a mission to keep his daughter from marrying a Catalan.
When a man who's seemingly lost everything is grabbed by police for questioning, it starts a twisted cat-and-mouse game between him and a detective.

column4: The Last Days of Chez Nous
column8: Successful writer Beth's tepid marriage and home life face a new round of challenges when her footloose younger sister arrives for an extended visit.
Entrepreneurs from Vermont and Quebec sell Christmas trees on the streets of New York, becoming a cherished part of neighborhood holiday traditions.
After the death of a long-ago lover, married philanderer Rob tracks down her friend, a drug-addicted prostitute desperate to escape her dead-end life.
Aided only by a tough female police officer, a Hong Kong taxi driver tries to escape from gangsters pursuing incriminating evidence left in his cab.
Inspired by the variety shows of the 1970s, "A Russell Peters Christmas" is a sweet, silly, sentimental and, most of all, funny Christmas special.
"Parks and Recreation" star Aziz Ansari takes the stage to share his unfiltered views on adulthood, babies, marriage, love and more in the modern era.
This collection cherry-picks trailers, forgotten scenes and poster art from 47 gory oldies, including Bay of Blood and The Blood Spattered Bride.
Learning he is the grandson of a famous knight, a young man hilariously fights a rival gang to win over the most beautiful woman in the tribe.
A comedy writer for David Letterman unearths a hidden world of hilariously bizarre musicals, which turns into a toe-tapping obsession.
When a zealous gang leader plans to take out a friend-turned-rival for control of his turf, internal tensions complicate the battle to be the boss.
Hoping to leave their haunted house behind, a suburban family moves to a new place, only to learn the home wasn't haunted... but their eldest son is.
Kidnapped as a child and raised in the circus, a young lion tamer’s tough side emerges when he gets entangled in an underworld murder mystery.
Inside one of Cairo's most impoverished areas exists a place where criminals control everything and everyone.
A down-on-his-luck man must prove he's not as hapless as he seems when the woman he's on a date with is suddenly kidnapped.
A taxi driver longs to be a pop singer, but the road to stardom is wrought with competition and struggle until he befriends a helpful belly dancer.

column4: Norm Macdonald: Hitler's Dog, Gossip & Trickery
column8: In this new stand-up special, Norm Macdonald delivers sly, deadpan observations from an older – and perhaps even wiser – point of view.
A high-achieving 11-year-old student embarks on a journey of self-discovery at a school on a nearby island as he grapples with tensions at home.
When a busy mother and father realize they need help with their two young children, they hire a series of maids, often with humorous results.
Two female friends, each with confidence issues, help each other search for true love and deal with their romantic rivals.
Dedicated engineering student Iris succumbs to love and marries, but fate holds both tragedies and triumphs for her personal and professional life.
A wedding planner and an ex-Marine both have been unlucky in love. But a chance meeting and a spat over a parking space soon change all that.
When a young man determines to discover his father's true identity, he faces unexpected realizations that shake his sense of self.
An aspiring actor uses a magical book to transport himself inside the movies he had always dreamed of starring in – but not without consequences.
A single mom and skilled chef yearns for her children to settle down and offers them life lessons through the special dishes she creates.
A young trio aims to protect the world from evil, armed with magic crystals that allow them to control time, commune with spirits, and more.
Along with her son and best friend, a grieving widow hikes into the woods to scatter her late husband's ashes, only to discover they're being stalked.
Hari Kondabolu breaks down identity politics, celebrity encounters, his mango obsession and more in an unpredictable stand-up comedy special.
A quiet ex-con's tenuous grip on reality starts to slip when his manipulative mother brings out a part of him he hoped to leave behind.
Three former military operatives offer disturbing, firsthand accounts of the deadly impact that U.S. drone warfare has had on civilians overseas.
Young Ulises falls in love with teen Sofia, even as he is forced to lure her into his family's prostitution ring. Now he'll do anything to rescue her.
After meeting an untimely demise in separate incidents, Cha Min and Go Se-yeon discover they’ve come back to life in new bodies they don’t recognize.
After the death of a loved one, a woman decides to pursue her passion for writing by penning television scripts.

column4: In the Bosom of a Thorn
column8: After the invasion of Kuwait, a woman’s infant daughter is taken from her. Now, her daughter looks to make her way back home years later.
Seven female chefs describe what it’s like breaking into the restaurant industry's notorious boys' club.
When accused of a murder eerily parallel to a plot in his novel, a best-selling crime writer must navigate a web of hidden enemies.
Four individuals at a crossroads in life are given the chance to take both paths, and decide which road is best for them.
A decade after the seminal Brazilian film "City of God," this documentary reunites some of the cast and crew to find out what paths their lives took.
Germany's most celebrated actor is commissioned by Nazi propagandist Joseph Goebbels to prepare the leader of the Third Reich to deliver a speech.
In this blend of documentary and dramatization, circumstances test notions of love held by a young stripper, a single-dad surfer and a teen musician.
A commercial diver becomes trapped on the ocean floor with dwindling oxygen and little hope of a timely rescue, so he tries to save himself.
Over 50 years of their lives, a couple enjoys the blessings and setbacks of parenting, and learns that God has to be at the center of their family.
A looming collision with Jupiter threatens Earth as humans search for a new star. The planet's fate now lies in the hands of a few unexpected heroes.
During World War I, the bond between a young Englishman and his loyal horse, Joey, is tested when Joey is sold to the cavalry and sent to France.
Ali Wong's stand up special delves into her sexual adventures, hoarding, the rocky road to pregnancy, and why feminism is terrible.
Two federal agents battle through an army of rioting prisoners – and their sense of reality – inside a high-tech prison modeled after Dante’s Inferno.
A former addict moves to a new city with her children for a fresh start, but her struggle soon takes on an unexpected, supernatural dimension.
Wealthy, beautiful Valentina falls in love, only to realize that her man and her family are involved with one of Mexico's most powerful drug cartels.
Talented pooches from around the world compete to be the next Pup Star, but behind-the-scenes schemes threaten to ruin the fun.
Homicide detective Gene Handsome sets out to solve a woman's murder while searching for clues about what's missing from his personal life.
Eclectic stand-up comic Manu NNa relays everyday tales about the struggles of being gay in Mexico and shares his love of telenovelas and mezcal.
Self-professed teenage "space nerds" at Space Camp chase their dreams of traveling to Mars, while experts reflect on NASA's history and future.
A naïve young woman goes to Istanbul to meet the now-grown boy who jokingly promised to marry her in 11 years after she saved his life as a child.
A young mechanic comes out to his extremely straight best friends. Once they get used to the idea, they're determined to help him find the right guy.
When he causes a car accident that leaves a young woman with amnesia, a man finds himself telling incredible lies to make her and her family happy.

column4: A Little Help with Carol Burnett
column8: Comedy icon Carol Burnett returns to TV with a panel of clever kids, who help adults and celebrity guests solve their problems with brutal honesty.
In a future where technology has rendered privacy obsolete, a detective investigates a serial assassin who has been deleted from all visual records.

column4: Dany Boon: Des Hauts De France
column8: In an eclectic one-man show, French superstar Dany Boon reflects on his homeland, his first comedy gig and the challenges of parenting hostile teens.
Facing an inevitable outcome, terminally ill patients meet extraordinary medical practitioners seeking to change our approach to life and death.
Threatened by creditors, a newly unemployed man agrees to work for a debt collector, but soon discovers his deal with the devil has unexpected costs.

column4: Lo más sencillo es complicarlo todo
column8: When a 17-year-old learns the TV news host she pines for is engaged, she and her best friend launch an elaborate plan to prevent his marriage.
A Chinese pharmaceutical lawyer framed for a vile crime teams up with a sharp-witted Japanese detective to stop a dangerous corporate plot.
A woman enters a quirky mental health clinic after attempting suicide upon finding out her husband is having an affair with her best friend.
Along with her two friends, a determined woman travels to Vietnam to bring home the baby her recently deceased daughter had planned to adopt.
Three brothers seek to avenge the tragic death of a loved one, but become emotionally entangled with the daughters of those they hold responsible.
Reunited after 15 years, famous chef Sasha and hometown musician Marcus feel the old sparks of attraction but struggle to adapt to each other's worlds.

To blow off some steam, friends Akshay, Joshi and Lambodar, posing as a gang called C Kkompany, make a phony extortion demand to Joshi's apathetic son. The trio is shocked when their prank call makes them anonymous celebrities.
A gifted but insecure woman embarks on a transformative journey when she enlists an enigmatic con man to recover her stolen car from an eccentric thug.
To win back his ex-girlfriend, a nerdy teen starts selling ecstasy online out of his bedroom – and becomes one of Europe's biggest dealers.
Brazilian TV personality and politician Wallace Souza faces accusations of masterminding the violent crimes he reported on and rallied against.
Star athlete Rohan has his eye on a beautiful art student. But when his best friend Simran experiences a crisis, he drops everything to help her.
True love is put to the test when another woman comes between a pair of star-crossed young lovers in this thriller.
When his mother suffers a traumatic incident, a boy from the Mumbai slums treks to Delhi to deliver his written plea for justice to the Prime Minister.
An orphan girl taught magic by her sick grandma must find work in seedy Bangkok, where unsavory characters run afoul of her increasingly dark powers.
After a five-year suspension, a once-legendary race car driver decides to get back in the game against a new generation of opponents.
A couple out to have a sensuous weekend at a house outside of Mumbai finds it rigged with surveillance cameras and occupied by an evil entity.
The horror continues when Ragini's video goes viral and a sleazy director decides to make a movie about the incident in the original house.
When three small-time Mumbai crooks steal a bag on a train, they find that it's filled with weapons and realize that their lives may be in danger.
Five teens from Harlem become trapped in a nightmare when they're falsely accused of a brutal attack in Central Park. Based on the true story.
An unearthed audio interview of Hollywood icon Hedy Lamarr reveals a woman with brains as well as beauty, who was the first to patent frequency hopping.
A filmmaker trains the camera on her own family as she examines the impact her grandfather, troubled artist Arshile Gorky, had on three generations.
While filming a movie in England, Hollywood icon Marilyn Monroe slips away with a young Brit for a week of self-discovery and frivolity.
A minister who researches religious cults turns to his Buddhist monk friend for help investigating a new group with mysterious origins.
Confronted with the potential end of their marriage, Ethan and Sophie take off for a weekend together, hoping to negotiate their future.

column4: Sarah Silverman A Speck of Dust
column8: In her first comedy special post-health scare, Sarah Silverman shares a mix of fun facts, sad truths and yeah-she-just-went-there moments.
After starting a family of his very own in America, a gay filmmaker documents his loving, traditional Chinese family's process of acceptance.
After going to a Halloween party, college student Luis Andrés Colmenares is found dead. Was it an accident or murder? Inspired by true events.
A hotheaded widow searching for the hit-and-run driver who mowed down her husband befriends an eccentric optimist who isn't quite what she seems.
After their mother's death, four sisters learn a shocking family secret and embark on an adventure to discover the truth about their genealogy.

column4: Extremely Wicked, Shockingly Evil and Vile
column8: Single mother Liz falls for Ted Bundy and refuses to believe the truth about his crimes for years. A drama based on a true story.
Harrowing and hilarious tests await the brave and foolhardy, as well as the judges, in this comedy game show. If they flinch, they feel the pain.
When a beautiful belly-dancer moves into their apartment building, a group of unhappily married men strives to get her attention.
On the run from a dogged internal affairs agent, a corrupt cop reluctantly teams up with a defiant teen to unravel a conspiracy – before it's too late.
Teens from a Chicago high school grapple with their dreams, relationships and identities in a transformative summer before they leave for college.
Free-spirited toucan Tuca and self-doubting song thrush Bertie are best friends – and birds – who guide each other through life's ups and downs.
Undercover agents infiltrate a drug kingpin's operation by posing as a couple at the campground where he spends his weekends. Inspired by real events.

column4: Si saben cómo me pongo ¿pá qué me invitan?
column8: When four unhappy couples attend a spiritual retreat at a resort to try and solve their relationship troubles, shenanigans ensue.
The furor over the addition of two Muslim players to the Beitar Jerusalem soccer club underscores the role of institutionalized racism in Israel.
During World War II, daredevil star Miss Julia entertains soldiers at the Indo-Burma border, where she's caught up in a web of love and deceit.
This 2015 Sundance Film Festival breakout documentary from producer Rashida Jones spotlights the "amateur" porn industry and the women it exploits.
A shapeshifter has to kill, then inhabit his victims, or die. But as his need for new bodies speeds up, he finally faces down his own mortality.

column4: The Nutcracker and the Four Realms
column8: When her late mother gifts her a key, Clara embarks on a dreamlike journey full of fantasy and conflict in this retelling of the holiday classic.
This documentary explores the careers of some of porn's top stars and examines their adjustment to "normal" society after leaving adult entertainment.
After their mother’s tragic death, a trio of sisters bond over their newfound powers, vanquish demons and band together to defend their magical legacy.
"Roastmaster General" Jeff Ross and a slew of guest stars poke fun at major historical figures while also honoring their enduring impact on the world.
Nobody's safe as Michelle Wolf unapologetically takes aim in this weekly topical show that blends sketches with live comedy and in-studio guests.
The life of a bank manager is turned upside down when a friend from his past manipulates him into faking his own death and taking off on an adventure.
After a night out, Sandee wakes to discover she and her buddy have either taken their platonic friendship to a whole new level or ruined it forever.
When Prince Lee Cheong returns to Joseon after his brother’s death, he finds the kingdom plagued by deadly creatures – but they’re not the only threat.
A naive Madrid lawyer travels to Africa to search for her younger sister, who has gone missing in a part of Congo plagued by violence and strife.
Reunited with her best friend’s younger brother, who’s back from a stint abroad, a recently dumped career woman begins to see him in a new light.
This intense documentary follows real cases of American girls enslaved in the child sex trade through ads in a newspaper's online classified section.
Mobilized by teenage activist Joshua Wong, young citizens of Hong Kong take to the streets in a bid to preserve their history of autonomy from China.
After street smart kid Raees rises to become Gujarat's bootlegging king in the 1980s, he tries to balance his life of crime with helping his people.
When a proud general is tasked with winning an unpopular war, he takes the challenge head-on, not knowing that hubris may be his own worst enemy.

column4: The Last Man on the Moon
column8: Astronaut Gene Cernan looks back on the exciting history of NASA's lunar landings and how being the last man to stand on the moon changed his life.
When freshman engineering student Kongpob stands up to older bully Arthit, their confrontation soon leads to a deep attraction between the two boys.
From controversial cartoonist to powerful Mumbai politician, this biopic maps the meteoric rise of far-right Shiv Sena party founder, Bal Thackeray.
Seeking inspiration, a young 19th-century painter finds a woman who is his love, his muse and his willing subject, but his work becomes controversial.
Argentine actor and comedian Fernando Sanjiao uses humor and impersonations to explore the concepts of masculinity and fatherhood in modern times.
When Harper is sent to Spain for an important work meeting, her hard-partying friends tag along and convince her to pursue a fling with a famous DJ.

column4: Steve Martin and Martin Short: An Evening You Will Forget for the Rest of Your Life
column8: Longtime pals and showbiz icons Steve Martin and Martin Short share countless quips, catchy tunes and hilarious stories about their lives in comedy.
Convinced his stepfather caused the crash that left his mother in a coma, a law student drunkenly agrees to his murder, then can't rescind the deal.
Displaced by Hurricane Maria, three Puerto Rican women navigate their families' uncertain futures as their federal housing aid in New York expires.
To live is to eat. For people around the world in precarious and dangerous circumstances, eating itself is dangerous, precarious – and essential.
Close to paying off her debts, a Nigerian sex worker in Austria coaches a reluctant novice, and assesses the risks of taking a faster path to freedom.
Stranded at a summer camp when aliens attack the planet, four teens with nothing in common embark on a perilous mission to save the world.
In this twisty horror-thriller, a once-promising music prodigy reconnects with her former mentors, only to find them taken with a talented new pupil.
Desperate to secure funding for her med tech startup, an idealistic scientist and her husband strike an outrageous deal with a mysterious investor.
Former inmates, officers and celebrities critique the U.S. prison system in this documentary packaged as a how-to handbook for the incarcerated.

column4: The Lonely Island Presents: The Unauthorized Bash Brothers Experience
column8: The Lonely Island spoofs notorious baseball stars Jose Canseco and Mark McGwire in this visual rap album set in the Bash Brothers' 1980s heyday.
A futuristic France tries to keep its people from despair and rebellion over crippling poverty by engaging them with a violent TV competition show.
Comic Hasan Minhaj of "The Daily Show" shares personal stories about racism, immigrant parents, prom night horrors and more in this stand-up special.
A huge fan of a Korean TV drama is transported to a magical realm where she has the power to alter her favorite show's story line as a "Facilitator."
Mexico City restaurant star Gabriela Cámara opens sister eatery Cala in San Francisco, with a similar menu and unusually welcoming kitchen culture.

column4: The Man Who Feels No Pain
column8: Leveraging his ability to withstand pain, a young man trains to follow in the footsteps of his martial-arts hero in this high-action, meta comedy.
There's an organization gathering espers for a nefarious purpose. Powerful psychic Mob, however, is just trying to be the protagonist of his own life.

column4: Tig Notaro Happy To Be Here
column8: Comedian Tig Notaro unleashes her inner prankster in a playful stand-up special packed with funny anecdotes, parenting confessions and more.
A pregnant teen is forced by her family to leave her boyfriend and assume a new identity in America, but 12 years later, the couple reunites in Korea.
After enduring both business and family upheavals, a ruthless investment director has a heart transplant and finds a new way to look at life and love.
On the cusp of marriage or divorce, four couples consider the meaning of love, sharing a life, meddling families and the weight of their commitment.
A blend of the royal family's intimate recollections and rarely seen home movies pays tribute to Queen Elizabeth II on the eve of her 90th birthday.
When his big stock plan fails, a hotshot fund manager winds up homeless and must learn the secret ranking system of the street in order to survive.
A married middle-aged woman is swept off her feet, both romantically and artistically, by a gifted young pianist.
A renowned actor who is still pining over the loss of his first real love writes an autobiography about his memories of her, hoping to reconnect.

column4: The Super Mario Bros. Super Show!
column8: Mixing live action and animation, this classic series brought the beloved Super Mario Bros. video game characters to television screens everywhere.

column4: Jen Kirkman: I'm Gonna Die Alone (And I Feel Fine)
column8: Jen Kirkman delivers some sharp, hilarious truths about divorce, kids, sex and turning 40 in this Netflix original comedy special.

column4: The Other One: The Long Strange Trip of Bob Weir
column8: This chronicle of Bob Weir highlights his brotherhood with Jerry Garcia and his success as a member of one of the world's most influential bands.
In a crime-infested Miami neighborhood, a gay African-American boy with a drug-addicted mother grows up with the help of a mentoring drug dealer.
Wanda Sykes tackles politics, reality TV, racism and the secret she'd take to the grave in this rollicking, no-holds-barred stand-up special.
Through his relationships with two wildly different women, a vertically challenged bachelor with a larger-than-life persona must discover his purpose.
An exploration of the American circus, as the spectacle evolved from a one-ring show to a cultural event and eventually, a dying breed.
When a con man tries to retrieve a bag of money, he swoons for a woman with ties to a notorious crew of criminals.
A woman must decide if she’s willing to end her pregnancy to save her own life after being diagnosed with breast cancer.
One minute, Civil War veteran John Carter is evading Apaches; the next, he's waking up on Mars, a once-fruitful planet that's devolved into chaos.
A man who hopes to bring light to his village must compete with an officer from the electricity department to win over the love of his life.
A disgraced Secret Service agent must come to the rescue when Korean terrorists descend on the White House and take the president hostage.
After a mother and her daughter are gang-raped by seven men, the daughter suffers a mental breakdown, and the single mom sets out to get revenge.
Four cops escorting a mobster to a high-security prison fight for survival when a gang boss orchestrates a riot from outside to silence their charge.
Maria Bamford performs a rapid-fire, playful stand-up set for crowds at park benches, bowling alleys and LA theaters in this roving comedy special.
A troubled couple living near the North Pole begins a perilous journey south in an attempt to find peace and vanquish ghosts from the past.
A homeless vet who has PTSD steals a motorcycle and hits the road, trying to sort out what life means now that war is in the rear-view mirror.
When they travel to their father's ancestral village, city kids expecting a natural paradise instead find a poor, dusty town that harbors secrets.
When a disgraced ex-cop discovers a dying woman, he's compelled to track down her killer – an act of self-redemption that takes him down a dark path.
An Ankara homicide detective with a dark personal life and a disdain for rules and political correctness solves murders and fights police corruption.
Inside a vast, self-replicating city bent on eliminating all life, mysterious loner Killy emerges to guide a remnant of humanity desperate to survive.
Pop stars and impersonators face off to be the last one standing as the audience tries to determine the real singer by listening to their voices only.
Thailand's complicated history with marijuana continues to play a role in its policies and laws, as well as the health and security of its citizens.
After living as a man for nearly 60 years, Laerte Coutinho, one of Brazil's most brilliant cartoonists, introduces herself to the world as a woman.
This docuseries examines the decades-old murder of Sister Catherine Cesnik and its suspected link to a priest accused of abuse.
When their parents fail to pick them up for winter break, two students stay on at an all-girls boarding school in the company of a terrible presence.
Newly famous after challenging Muhammad Ali for a championship title, boxer Chuck Wepner spirals down the slippery slope of being a celebrity.
Amid a terrifying pandemic, a father searches the wilds of Australia for someone willing to protect and care for his infant daughter.
Amid growing tensions in their marriage, a Johannesburg professor and his journalist wife find their lives upended by a famous, hard-partying author.
True and her friends are making music – and they want you to dance and sing along. So cut loose, silly goose! These fun beats are totally sweet.
Religion thwarted Lucas and Jade's young love. They reunite decades later, but Jade's heart is torn between the man she knew and his younger clone.
Archival video and new interviews examine Mexican politics in 1994, a year marked by the rise of the EZLN and the assassination of Luis Donaldo Colosio.
This documentary focuses on the devastating violence of the Israel-Palestine conflict and its effects on the children of Gaza.
This intimate documentary follows a group of Syrian children refugees who narrowly escape a life of torment and integrate into a foreign land.
Seeking answers after a life-changing incident in 2012, filmmaker Hernán Zin interviews other war reporters about the personal toll of their work.
Unaware they’ve matched online, a struggling writer embellishes his lifestyle to impress a successful exec with whom he sparks an unexpected romance.
An old-school Brooklyn native devotes his days to caring for his adorable dog, Bruno – and making sure the neighbors show his pooch the proper respect.
An ex-assassin tries to leave her dark past behind until a power-hungry gang targets her and her family, forcing her to summon her killer instincts.
After discovering the family of Solomon Linda, the writer of "The Lion Sleeps Tonight," a reporter tries to help them fight for fair compensation.
Italian comic and satirist Saverio Raimondo regales a Milan crowd with tales of online antics, awkward injuries and white-knuckle flights.
As two teen prodigies try to master the art of time travel, a tragic police shooting sends them on a series of dangerous trips to the past.
To secure a bone marrow donation, an actress diagnosed with leukemia makes a marriage pact with a young CEO – but love and secrets get in the way.
An aspiring actor leaves Hollywood and takes to the road to do stand-up after he's cast in a series of increasingly stereotypical "black" roles.

column4: Tinker Bell and the Legend of the NeverBeast
column8: When suspicious scout fairies scheme to capture the fearsome-looking NeverBeast, Tinker Bell and Fawn set out to save the wondrous creature.
While making a film about the incursion of Christopher Columbus in the New World, a director finds the Bolivian locals protesting modern exploitation.
A curious reporter finds love while pursuing the story of a mysterious figure who's leaving bags of cash for strangers around New York City.
In this quiet, wistful drama, a woman on her deathbed searches her fraying memories for love and fulfillment through surreal, meditative tableaux.

column4: Kyo Kii... Main Jhuth Nahin Bolta
column8: The life and career of a lawyer are thrown into chaos when his son's wish magically renders him incapable of telling a lie.
With his writing career dragging, Eddie Morra finds his life turning around after he takes a drug that provides astonishing mental focus.
This provocative drama examines how the voyeuristic nature of modern society affects three unusual couples in Northern India.

column4: Mission Istaanbul: Darr Ke Aagey Jeet Hai
column8: A television journalist makes a risky career move by accepting a job offer from a controversial Istanbul television station.

column4: Once Upon a Time in Mumbai Dobaara!
column8: This turbulent sequel to Once Upon a Time in Mumbai carries on the saga of the gangland don Shoaib Khan, who continues pressing for more control.
When a schoolteacher inherits an adorable pug, she has to find a way to take care of it while dealing with her flatlining love life.
Set in the financial boom of the late 1980s, this tale centers on a recent college grad trying to figure out what to do with his life.
Mixing old footage with interviews, this is the story of Arsenal's improbable win versus Liverpool in the final moments of the 1989 championship game.

Vipul Amrutlal Shah directs this sci-fi rom-com that stars Akshay Kumar and Aishwarya Rai as Kishen and Mala, a married couple who are so miserable, they inspire their son, Bunty, to go back in time and make his parents fall in love.
Broke and with no concrete plans for the future, two young men discover that a stunning heiress lives nearby and try to charm her into marriage.
Epicureans and experts trace the migration of Italian cuisine and its evolution in the Americas, delving into the ideas of origin, diaspora and heritage.
In a film based on true events, an awkward but ambitious TV reporter struggles to adapt when she's ordered to focus on violent and salacious stories.
A violent confrontation between a motorcycle-riding bank robber and a rookie cop spirals into a tense generational feud.
In his first special since his serious car accident, Tracy Morgan cracks jokes about life in a coma, his second marriage and his family's dark side.
Given just seven days by a genie to find a girl who will fall for him, a nerdy young man embarks on a madcap and messy search for his would-be wife.
A battle-scarred Special Ops military vet joins a CIA-funded assignment to take down a Russian terrorist and his trigger-happy comrades.
When their aging father’s illness reunites two sisters under one roof, new tensions arise between them as old wounds and hidden secrets surface.
Fearless Dennis, his loyal dog Gnasher and best friends Rubi, JJ and Pieface quench their thirst for adventure by wreaking havoc all over Beanotown.

column4: EMI: Liya Hai To Chukana Padega
column8: A bank hires an enigmatic and unorthodox debt collector to recover money from four borrowers who are unable to pay their loans.
Wanting his missing father to come home, a Kashmiri boy repeatedly attempts to call God for help – until one day, a hardened army officer picks up.
Inspired by the classic novel, this telenovela follows Heidi, who leaves her happy life in the mountains behind when her aunt takes her to the big city.
Love blooms between a bubbly, aspiring voice actress and a cool, enigmatic violin-maker after they cross paths on a reality TV show.
A student tries to steal a test from a teacher's home, leaving him for dead after an accident. A string of murders may be the professor's revenge.
Longtime friends Rahul and Karan head to Mumbai intent on making their dreams come true, but both men are suddenly saddled with bad luck.
When an unlikely porn actor falls for a woman outside the industry, he employs his co-stars as a stand-in traditional family to impress her father.

column4: Once Upon a Time in Mumbaai
column8: Mumbai's top mob boss rules the underworld with honor and compassion, but his power-hungry protégé will shake up the world of organized crime.

Based on a true story, this action film follows an incident that stunned a nation in the early 1990s. In Mumbai, India, the notorious gangster Maya holds off veteran cop Khan and a force of more than 200 policemen in a six-hour bloody gunfight.
When Shaji Pappan and his gang of goofy outlaws find themselves low on funds, they plan to once again win a hefty prize in a tug-of-war competition.
When his protégé goes rogue and poses a grave threat to the government he serves, a veteran officer of the Indian Army tries to stop him at all costs.
Beautiful and adventurous doctor Resham meets a handsome Chinese backpacker named Adam while traveling with friends on a journey of self-discovery.

column4: Lupin the 3rd: The Castle of Cagliostro: Special Edition
column8: Lupin, his sidekick, Jigen, and the samurai warrior Goemon set out to take over an evil counterfeit operation at Count Cagliostro's fortress.
When a cop kills the brother of an expat American gangster who runs a Bangkok fight club, his crime-boss mother flies in to supervise revenge.
This anime adventure follows the battle between a saint of Athena and an avatar of Hades who's working on a painting that could destroy the world.
A village schoolteacher and the ghost of a murdered man, who were both betrayed by those closest to them, join forces to help each other.
This documentary series explores the glamour of Bollywood through the stories of the men and women who have illuminated its screens.
Chronicling a 1980 Titan II missile accident, this sobering documentary weighs the balance of power and safety involving weapons of mass destruction.
A dreamer falls for a girl who is in love with someone else and tries to create a rift between her and the man she loves.
Best friends Sarah and Mindy share an unexpected moment while on a road trip. Years later, the two struggle to reconnect before a wedding.
A Viennese child who was kidnapped and held captive in a basement before escaping after eight years reveals her headline-making story of survival.
Two boyhood pals – one righteous, the other a criminal – take very different paths to adulthood. Their love for the same woman may prove disastrous.
Inspired by a true story, this TV drama shadows a young Colombian woman who goes to shocking lengths to escape a life of poverty.
Buckle up for a look inside a biannual school bus race in Florida, a harrowing event where carnage and collisions are most definitely encouraged.
Before the dawn of World War II, an ambitious actress pursues her dreams in Berlin. But her plans derail when she becomes Joseph Goebbels’ mistress.
After burgeoning criminal Gunz joins the increasingly violent TIC crew, the gang finds itself dealing with threats from all sides.

column4: Attacking the Devil: Harold Evans and the Last Nazi War Crime
column8: Intrepid newspaper editor Harold Evans wages an ongoing battle to expose the truth about a dangerous drug and obtain compensation for its victims.
In this sequel to the 1991 film, a determined fire investigator recruits an imprisoned arsonist to help untangle a web of fire, murder and corruption.
An unlucky woman finds a solution for her hateful ex, a trying job hunt and a stalker through a charming P.I. – only to endure a new set of problems.
When Shibuya time-warps to 2388, high schooler Daisuke and his friends are conscripted by AHRV agent Milo to fight the hostile cyborg race, revisions.
This celebration of the groundbreaking comedy show "Laugh-In" stars Lily Tomlin, Snoop Dogg, Billy Crystal, Tiffany Haddish, Neil Patrick Harris and more.
Buoyed by hopeful experiences with medical marijuana, physicians and parents of children with cancer call for more research of its healing potential.
Witness some of the most riveting showdowns in the animal kingdom as cameras capture leopards, polar bears and other predators targeting their prey.
When a long list of shenanigans lands Tyler in hot water, he’s forced to suit up and spend his summer training for an elite junior lifeguard program.

column4: Norm of the North: Keys to the Kingdom
column8: When Norm the polar bear is framed for a crime he didn’t commit, his friends step up to help him clear his name.
Two years after the hit "Baby Cobra," Ali Wong is back with another baby bump – and a torrent of hilarious truths about marriage and motherhood.
When insurance accidentally pays her millions, retired teacher Eva and her pal Maddie head to the Canary Islands for the adventure of their lives.

column4: Merata: How Mum Decolonised the Screen
column8: New Zealand film archivist Heperi Mita traces the cinematic legacy of his mother and trailblazing Maori filmmaker Merata Mita.
After surviving a near-fatal injury on the job, a cop sets out to investigate a conspiracy involving the top brass of the police department.
Struggling writer Wally Spivak is stuck in a rut – until he meets an engaged couple and starts to see life in a whole new way.
Julien's been dethroned, but loyal friends and some very unlikely allies will propel the lovable lemur on a colorful journey to take back his kingdom.
Examine the rise, fall and rebirth of political operative Roger Stone, who's been an influential member of Team Trump for decades.
When a twisted killer tells the police he'll only speak to a fictional 1980s TV detective, the washed-up actor who played him takes the gig.
When his new love is captured by an evil snake charmer, a young cobra and his scorpion best friend set out across the desert on a wild rescue mission.
An odd encounter with a fan and a tryst with that fan's ex-boyfriend leads a sexually adventurous singer on an escapade in Chile.
Fresh out of juvenile detention in Marseille, 17-year-old Zach falls for a young prostitute and soon faces a dire dilemma while working as a pimp.
In 1920s Beijing, a host of talented performers gather to show off their skills. The challenge: reproduce a magic trick called the Eight Immortals.
This animated series follows young Mowgli and his animal mentors Bagheera and Baloo, who do their best to protect him from fierce tiger Shere Khan.
Mexican comic Carlos Ballarta mocks himself and points out the absurdities of parenthood and how he uses his wife's pregnancies to avoid commitments.
This baffling true crime story starts with the grisly death of a pizza man who robs a bank with a bomb around his neck – and gets weirder from there.
When teenager Elle's first kiss leads to a forbidden romance with the hottest boy in high school, she risks her relationship with her best friend.
Fresh voices bring some of the most famous names in history to life. A live-action sketch comedy show based on the series of best-selling books.
It's Diwali! To celebrate, Chhota Bheem and his friends put on a stage show of the Ramayana, re-enacting the epic story behind the festival of lights.
Finally released after being trapped in an ancient book for centuries, a wicked warrior sets out to conquer Dholakpur – but not if Bheem can help it!
Bheem and King Indraverma travel to Rome for a trading venture, but when the king of a neighboring land attacks, can Bheem’s wile and wit save the day?

column4: Chhota Bheem Ka Troll Se Takkar
column8: Trolls kidnap the king's daughters and overtake the kingdom of Messina. Can Bheem track them down and bring the princesses home?
After her partner cheats on her, an architect returns to her hometown to reassess her life with the help of her eccentric family. Based on the novel.
At the Sacramento County Jail, incarcerated women fight the power and one another as they try to make the best of life – and love – on the inside.
In 1987 New York, LGBTQ ball fixture Blanca starts her own house, soon becoming mother to a gifted dancer and a sex worker in love with a yuppie client.
A princess descended from a ruined noble family disguises herself as the woman who saved her life and embarks on a mission to avenge her loved ones.
When everyone else mysteriously vanishes from their wealthy town, the teen residents of West Ham must forge their own society to survive.
When longtime friends meet up for a wine-soaked birthday getaway in Napa Valley, their perfectly planned weekend turns messier by the minute.
An outspoken, imaginative girl from a conservative family pursues her dream man while fending off the prospect of an arranged marriage.
A cooly confident aging hit man returns from exile in Paris to his old city, Mumbai, to revisit his past and perform one last job.
After a vengeful college professor targets corruption in the government, he adopts the name "Gabbar" and becomes a hero to a weary public.
An Indian intelligence agent journeys to a war-torn coastal island to break a resolute rebel group and meets a passionate journalist.
After a dedicated cop accidentally kills a 12-year-old boy, he's fired, harassed and forced to take menial work as he tries to keep his life together.
After finding a peculiar key, three smart and adventurous kids launch a quest to uncover the whereabouts of a coveted archaeological treasure.
A young man determined to renounce Catholicism by having his baptismal records excised is thwarted by church bureaucracy and his own inner conflicts.
A spunky terrier named Russell with serious wrestling chops becomes a sports phenomenon with the help of his coach, a monkey named Hunk.
In 1931, a young Navy wife tore apart Hawaii on racial lines after claiming she was raped by a gang of nonwhite islanders.

column4: Dr. Seuss' The Cat in the Hat
column8: While Mom is away, a bored little boy and girl are visited by the Cat in the Hat, who proceeds to turn the house into the "mother of all messes."
An ex-con struggles to take care of his two brothers, a gambling addict and a young man with Down syndrome, after being released from prison.
A woman stages her own suicide but still lives in fear of her abusive ex-boyfriend tracking her down and stealing the son he never knew he had.

column4: John & Yoko: Above Us Only Sky
column8: Featuring interviews and never-before-seen footage, this film tells the story behind John Lennon and Yoko Ono’s seminal 1971 album, “Imagine.”
A 15-year-old girl with autism attempts to write a mystery novel based on her hunt for the killer of a neighborhood cat.

column4: Kill Hitler! The Luck of the Devil
column8: From politicians to officers, many attempted to kill Hitler – and failed. This documentary delves into the details of how their plots unraveled.
Go behind the scenes as four determined women – including Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez – challenge big-money politicians in the 2018 race for Congress.
This documentary retraces the footsteps of Adolf Hitler's mysterious nephew and explores what became of the Hitler family line.
Haunted by terrifying visions, a Muslim healer finds his faith tested when he helps a woman locked in battle, body and soul, with a diabolical leader.
When the Sheriff of Nottingham takes his beloved captive, Robin Hood embarks on a daring rescue mission at the tyrant's castle.
After 10 years, a woman returns to her sleepy tourist-occupied hometown and discovers her high-school crush is also an unusual foreigner.
The Earth's remaining inhabitants are confined to a single train circling the globe as revolution brews among the class-divided cars.
A group of small-town students goes for glory by competing in a statewide kabaddi tournament 25 years after their school's championship victory.
In this animated adventure, Master Splinter whips the four Ninja Turtles back into shape to defeat monsters running amok in New York.
In this mythical tale, Jen, the last of the Gelfling race, is charged with healing the Crystal of Truth after its mutilation sets off an era of terror.
Host Leon Logothetis travels the world with only a vintage motorbike and the kindness of strangers, which he pays back in unexpected, inspiring ways.
A doctor and a drug addict kidnap the son of a local gangster, seeking revenge for the death of a loved one.
After a musician dies under suspicious circumstances, a hard-drinking detective and a music fan investigate why rock stars often die at the age of 27.
Explore the circumstances surrounding the tragic deaths at 27 of Jimi Hendrix, Jim Morrison, Brian Jones, Janis Joplin, Kurt Cobain and Amy Winehouse.
Due to family pressure, a corporate man reluctantly marries a woman from the village, but in their new home, she abruptly assumes a different persona.
When her small granddaughter is sexually assaulted by a powerful man and no justice is served, a poor, frail old woman plots her violent revenge.
The cases are supernatural; the police officers human. Together, cops Aditi and Vikrant must solve mysteries from the realm of the paranormal.
Unassuming high school girl Jan-di stands up to – and eventually falls for – a spoiled rich kid who belongs to the school's most powerful clique.
A young man in Kerala has two weeks to stop the woman he loves from a fixed marriage in the U.S., but he doesn't have the papers to get there.
In Naples, Buenos Aires and New York, people reflect on the Neapolitan tradition of "suspended coffee" and how it changed their lives.
To bring down a global human trafficking ring, an Interpol agent recruits the help of a brutal criminal with inside knowledge of the yakuza.
A Spaniard working in Argentina sees his life upended after accidentally giving bad directions to a passerby, who demands compensation for the error.
In Yorkshire, a withdrawn gay farmer begins a torrid affair with a Romanian migrant worker who shows him the depths of his capacity for affection.
When the daughter of a wealthy family returns from college, she gets a frosty welcome from her brother, who has problems – and plans – of his own.
In the forests of Karnataka, a farmer and his community face eviction from the land when they get caught in the currents of socio-political change.
Two friends' lives are changed forever when they are recruited by a top-secret organization tasked with protecting the country from foreign threats.
The story of famed L.A. nightclub Catch One and owner Jewel Thais-Williams, who defied all odds and provided a safe space for black LGBT communities.

column4: John Mulaney: Kid Gorgeous at Radio City
column8: John Mulaney relays stories from his childhood and “SNL,” eviscerates the value of college and laments getting older in this electric comedy special.
From fake marriages to online shopping fraud, a whip-smart police officer investigates truly baffling cons that were inspired by true stories.
After a blackmailing scandal and being sidelined from the French national team, Real Madrid forward Karim Benzema tells his side of the story.
Not romantically inclined, a popular radio personality finds herself caught between two diametrically opposed suitors.
A story of two couples' journey of new love, loss and unexpected reunion spans decades, from the 1970s through present day.
A simple auto-rickshaw driver on the streets of Lucknow, Hiralal Tiwari does everything he can to give his gravely ill daughter a happy life.
Just in time for Valentine's Day, a program developer pitches a revolutionary dating algorithm to her new CEO, who volunteers them as guinea pigs.
With numbers written on a doll as their only clue, three officers of the law track down a psychotic killer, unearthing dark secrets along the way.
Seeking to heal after a traumatic assault, a young woman retreats to a small village by the hills, where she finds hope, love and new purpose.
Pocoyo gears up for exciting car races and learns that friends, teamwork and imagination are what matter the most.
Acrobatic aliens arrive on spaceships and perform for everyone, but when angry aliens arrive as well, Pocoyo and his friends must now put on a show.
To celebrate the carnival, everyone learns to dance to different music. Plus, Pocoyo's friends surprise him with something delicious.
Pocoyo and his friends have a costume contest to celebrate Halloween and learn new things about planets and stars in space.
Pocoyo finds a special toy and plays new games with his friends, then they’re spooked by a scary box and try to find out who’s inside.
Everyone is getting excited for the games. Pocoyo plays baseball and golf, and races with his friends. Ready, set, go!
Eight women perform in front of celebrity judges and compete for the title of India’s top female stand-up comedian.
Desperate to save his land, an indebted farmer journeys to Pandharpur to seek divine blessing with his small son, who searches for his mother.

column4: Roberto Saviano: Writing Under Police Protection
column8: Italian TV host Pif revisits Roberto Saviano, who's been living under protection since publishing "Gomorrah," his exposé on organized crime in Naples.
With his vivid imagination, Simon the rabbit searches for fun while learning about the importance of responsibility and communication.
Seven strangers anxiously waiting for their HIV test results decide to bribe the clinic receptionist to get them early, learning one is positive.
Psychic Hiroyuki Ehara leads various celebrities through spiritual consultations, probing into their issues and spotlighting their accomplishments.

column4: Swami Baba Ramdev: The Untold Story
column8: Born into poverty and denied an education, a village boy overcomes society’s obstacles to become India’s foremost spiritual guru, revered by millions.
Featuring eight-time NBA All-Star Vince Carter, this documentary takes an in-depth look at his impact on pop culture and the Canadian basketball scene.
A newcomer ekes out a living in LA as a professional audience member on infomercials, but life gets complicated when he's thrust into the spotlight.
A group of patients with OCD wait for their flight-delayed doctor to arrive for their appointments, forcing them to endure each other's oddball quirks.

column4: Tremors 6: A Cold Day in Hell
column8: The subterranean, worm-like creatures are back, and Graboid-hunter Burt Gummer suspects they've been weaponized.
While visiting his comatose wife in the hospital, a serene old professor befriends a vibrant young woman whose husband has also fallen into a coma.
Unable to pay bills and unwilling to change his slacker lifestyle, twentysomething Aaron hatches a defrauding scheme when he finds a lost credit card.
Obsessed with an unsolved murder case, a crime novelist stuck in an unhappy marriage fantasizes about killing his wife, who soon turns up dead.
In Singapore, a homeless ex-convict hoping to reunite with his family forms a bond with a Chinese sex worker while serving as her bodyguard.
After losing his seventh job in a row, a TV producer and sci-fi buff travels back in time to 1980, where his employment prospects improve.
When a small-town wedding videographer falls in love, he decides he needs to make more money and turns to shooting sexy videos – with mixed results.
A gay man deals with his sexuality, a struggling actor has an epiphany, a boy becomes a dancer, and a man tries to fulfill his father's dying wish.
Disowned by his father as a boy, Surya is taken in by a crime boss. When his brother Shiv is wrongly imprisoned, his father pleads for Surya's help.
In this thought-provoking biopic, an idealistic judo trainer adopts a boy from the slums and grooms him into the world's youngest marathon runner.
A vulnerable singer is forced to choose between the girl he loves and another who has developed an unhealthy obsession with him.
When pretty new neighbor Seema falls for their shy roommate Sid, jealous womanizers Omi and Jai plot to break up the new lovebirds.

column4: Defying the Nazis: The Sharps' War
column8: This film documents the story of minister Waitstill Sharp and his wife, Martha, who risked everything to save thousands of refugees fleeing the Nazis.
After learning he was adopted from a Muslim couple, a Hindu man seeks his birth father but finds he must confront his bigotry to realize his quest.
Six talented but struggling improv comics see a sudden shift in their troupe's dynamic after one of them lands a much-coveted gig on television.
An unexceptional man becomes a murder suspect when the son of a high-ranking police official who harassed his daughter goes missing.
After his brother dies, wealthy Vikram reluctantly returns to India and forms a surprise bond with his orphaned nephew and the showgirl raising him.
Dylan Mohan Gray examines Africa's AIDS crisis and activists' battle with pharmaceutical companies to make life-saving HIV drugs more affordable.
Hapless brothers Gollu and Pappu stumble into a terrorist plot and end up being ordered to detonate a bomb, a task they are destined to bungle.
This anthology features seven independent anime shorts from renowned directors, delving into the futuristic universe of the video game franchise Halo.
This film chronicles the career of photographer Harry Benson, who earned global renown with his candid shots of the Beatles and other celebrities.
When French-African couple Paul and Sali discover the longed-for baby they are about to adopt is white, family chaos and confrontation ensue.
The sudden disappearance of a wealthy banker's wife cracks open a dizzying world of secret fetishes, desperate acts and elaborate deceptions.
An ad agency CEO is put under investigation when his ambitious protégée – and lover – accuses him of sexual harassment, vying for his top position.
Find out everything there is to know about Japanese tradition, from food to culture to objects and arts, and the people who are continuing it today.

column4: JFK: The Making of a President
column8: Explore how John F. Kennedy's worldview was influenced by his younger years, when he endured poor health, family tragedy and a demanding father.
Faced with a rare form of throat cancer, teen figure skater Carley Allison finds strength in singing for an online audience in this biopic.
Lives are upended when a hiking trip leads a Wall Street hotshot to explore his true feelings for an old pal who’s disenchanted with his boyfriend.
This documentary recounts the feats of the Coxless Crew, a team of four women who rowed from San Francisco to Australia in support of two charities.
The daughter of a poor rice farmer overcomes the objections of her father and the demands of a male-dominated society to pursue a career in boxing.

column4: Maya Angelou: And Still I Rise
column8: Poet and civil rights activist Maya Angelou is celebrated using her own words set over rare photographs and video illustrating her remarkable life.
After investing in a shady deal that quickly falls apart, a morally flexible real estate agent involves his wife in a dangerous recovery plan.
Explore the unconventional career of Sunny Leone, who transitioned from adult film star to Bollywood actress and reality TV star.
In Delhi for the first time, a Mumbai girl loses her phone but gets a surprise chance at true love with a local boy who begrudgingly helps her.
Mumbai shopkeeper Kanji Bhai files a lawsuit against God when an earthquake destroys his store and his insurance policy won't cover the damage.
The lives of a Mumbai man and woman who are both dealing with issues intersect through a TV dance show that she wants to win but he wants to sabotage.
Matters of the heart introduce chaos into the once-idyllic bachelor existence of three young men who share an apartment.
Three young bachelors find the reality of relationships to be far removed from the idea of true romance that they had once pursued.
A jilted bride decides to go on her European honeymoon anyway – by herself – and ends up embarking on a journey of self-discovery.
When a poor taxi driver falls in love with a wealthy young woman, he must stand up to her family and contend with his own insecurities.
This documentary profiles the celebrated Hindi film director known as much for his embrace of leftist politics and social concerns as lyrical cinema.
When they're blackmailed after a hit-and-run, a troubled rich girl and her wild friends stage a fake kidnapping with a plan to collect the ransom.
In this fact-based crime drama, a gang of con artists posing as government officials executes a heist in the form of a raid on a prominent jeweler.
When London-based doctor Manu reluctantly returns to India to find a bride, he meets the girl of his dreams – only to discover she loves another man.
When a withdrawn, long-missing teenager reappears in a chilly alpine town, his heartbroken family begins to wonder if he's actually who he says he is.
A crabby woman leaves home for a vacation and entrusts her niece's fiancé to feed her fish and adhere to a strict set of rules. He has other ideas.
Up to his old tricks, con man Dharam poses as a millionaire to get his younger son married to the daughter of a wealthy businessman.

column4: Mark Gatiss: A Study in Sherlock
column8: Mark Gatiss, who co-created “Sherlock” and plays Mycroft Holmes, discusses the show with Benedict Cumberbatch, Martin Freeman and others in the cast.
Finding a tantalizing clue in an old letter, a young woman journeys to her family's tropical plantation to uncover generations of secrets.
This visually arresting documentary essay reflects on our relationship to other living creatures as humanity becomes more isolated from nature.
This sci-fi thriller suggests that Apollo 17, despite official statements to the contrary, wasn't NASA's last manned mission to the moon.
Everything Aiko knew was a lie. Now she's joining a team of Divers to reach the place where the Burst began to stop it for good and save her family.
Investigating the murder of a pizza delivery man, a London detective uncovers a tangled conspiracy involving drug dealers, smugglers and spies.
An elderly immigrant matriarch from Hong Kong finally begins to break out of her shell of isolation when she suspects her husband of infidelity.
An American soldier imprisoned in postwar Japan enters the dark world of the yakuza, adopting their way of life in repayment for his freedom.
As a couple interviews a renowned dance professor for their dissertation, their probing questions soon betray a hidden agenda.
His hilltop farm in Vermont may be bucolic, but making ends meet is a backbreaking challenge for grizzled, hard-drinking organic farmer Peter Dunning.
Take a trip and witness the rise and fall of Tim Scully and Nicholas Sand, improbable pioneers of the drug counterculture during the 1960s.
Never ones to think things through, two Irish teens steal bicycles and set off to the coast to find a bale of cocaine from a smuggler’s capsized ship.
In a South Indian village, a centenarian's funeral brings together his free-spirited son, inheritance-hungry grandson and girl-crazy great-grandson.
Recovering alcoholic Talal wakes up inside a small-town police station cell, where he's subject to the mind games of a psychotic sadist.
Struggling to come to terms with his wife's death, a writer for a newspaper adopts a gruff new persona in an effort to push away those trying to help.
A loving couple become rivals when Belle opens a fusion bistro next to her ex-boyfriend Kram’s traditional restaurant in Bangkok’s chic Ari district.
The high life leads to high anxiety for a fashionable New York City homemaker in crisis who finds herself forced to live a more modest lifestyle.
Years after getting his girlfriend pregnant, washed-up jock Vince meets his eccentric son Michael and learns about fatherhood, one show tune at a time.
A university lecturer in Russia returns to Egypt after her husband's sudden disappearance, uncovering further mysteries the more she investigates.
Drivers, managers and team owners live life in the fast lane – both on and off the track – during one cutthroat season of Formula 1 racing.
In this sequel, a group of expert drivers skilled in drifting and high-speed racing is recruited to perform obscure tasks for a shadowy gang.
Driven by revenge, human-turned-vampire Mia sets out to vanquish Dmitry, a ruthless vampire leader who seeks an artifact that grants immortality.
Multiple generations of the Joestar family – all with the same nickname – confront supernatural villains through a series of time periods.
Burdened by troubles in life and love, a mother of three grown children searches for hope and healing on an impromptu trip to Paper Moon, Montana.
When her romance with a lustful marquis takes an unwelcome turn, a wealthy widow concocts a scheme to get revenge – with help from a younger woman.
Haunted by a tragic loss, an ex-cop with a rare inability to feel pain strikes out on his own to catch offenders who've eluded Johannesburg police.

column4: Spy Kids 2: The Island of Lost Dreams
column8: Spy kids Carmen and Juni Cortez team up with two other pint-size secret agents, Gary and Gerti Giggles, in order to take on an evil scientist.
A woman struggling with sleep paralysis begins a complicated relationship with the director of a media company, whose colleagues conspire against him.
When a deal with the devil comes due, the immortal Doctor Parnassus must renegotiate the pact to save his daughter and right the wrongs of his past.
Six book club members find their lives resemble a modern-day version of Jane Austen's novels in this drama.
In the wake of an accident that leaves her paralyzed, a champion rodeo rider vows to get back on her horse and compete again. Based on a true story.
Ordered to take down a villainous business leader who controls the city, a prosecutor gathers a team of men who may not be so clean themselves.
Born amid poverty and limited women's rights in the village of Ratu, India, Deepika Kumari rose to become the No.1 female archer in the world at 18.
A water boy for a college football team has a rage that makes him a tackling machine whose bone-crushing power might vault his team into the playoffs.
Sister Aloysius begins to have doubts about doting Father Flynn, who seems to have become overly involved in the life of an African American pupil.
When a perfectionist ad exec experiences a romantic setback, she embarks on a journey of self-discovery that begins with a dramatic hair makeover.
Two half siblings separated by family conflict cross paths as adults at a fashion agency – but one of them has a vendetta, unbeknownst to the other.
An architecture student and a history professor fall in love, pursue a dream, split up and bump into each other years later. Can there be a second chance?
A devastating breakup with her boyfriend may be the start of a new beginning for Mace, thanks to an adventurous and kind stranger named Anthony.
Feeling betrayed by their romantic partners' infidelity, Adrianne and Vince struggle to forgive while finding comfort with each other.
Out to avenge his mother's death, a college student pledges a secret order and lands in a war between werewolves and practitioners of dark magic.
An American tourist and his friends are partying in Chile, but a major earthquake devastates the area and forces them to scramble for survival.
After a daring heist, three fugitives lock themselves in a warehouse hoping to evade the police, but find a worse threat as they fight to stay alive.
Comic sensation Amy Schumer riffs on sex, dating and the absurdities of fame in a bold and uncensored stand-up set at Denver's Bellco Theater.
Witness the origins of Master Chief and the Spartan program as a group of children transform into enhanced soldiers and fight a powerful alien threat.

column4: American Crime Story: The People v. O.J. Simpson
column8: This anthology series dramatizes historic criminal cases in the U.S., including the O.J. Simpson trial and Andrew Cunanan's 1997 murder spree.
Defining moments in Andrew Cunanan's life, starting in childhood, lead up to a 1997 murder spree that kills five, including fashion icon Gianni Versace.
Tiny alien lawmen fly into Rod's bedroom and recruit him into helping them stop an intergalactic criminal – who's disguised as a very familiar human.
After lovable abandoned mutt Benji is adopted by a kind family, he chases cats, flirts with a show dog and bravely helps to rescue two abducted kids.
Benji is back in this charming story that's told from the pooch's point of view, tracking his early days as a pup to his current life in showbiz.
To protect his family, a police detective covers up a murder case. But when his partner suspects foul play, he is trapped in a dangerous game on duty.
Benji and his owner get separated in Greece. On his quest to find them, he's targeted by various bad guys who want to get their hands on him.
In his first English-language special, comedian Gad Elmaleh gleefully digs into America's food obsessions, dating culture, slang and more.
Amidst the looting and chaos of the LA riots, two Korean-American brothers fight to save their struggling shoe store while contemplating their future.

column4: Aziz Ansari Live at Madison Square Garden
column8: Stand-up comedian and TV star Aziz Ansari ("Parks and Recreation") delivers his sharp-witted take on immigrants, relationships and the food industry.
When a man discovers he will be the father to a boy, his fear and insecurities send him on an emotional, humorous quest for his own manhood.
A self-serving mythical creature's bid for invincibility backfires when he finds himself at the mercy of a woman who can see otherworldly beings.
Skeeter's life is turned upside down when the fantastical stories he makes up to entertain his niece and nephew inexplicably turn into reality.
Sarah leaves her son in the Philippines to reunite with her husband in London, where she struggles personally and professionally as a care-home worker.
Now a careworn middle-aged man, Christopher Robin goes on a familiar adventure when his old pal Winnie the Pooh brings him to the Hundred Acre Wood.
After learning his brother died on a mission in Romania, a former soldier teams up with two allies to hunt down a mysterious enemy and exact revenge.
Maddy and Cole were inseparable before high school. Then she got popular; he didn't. But after Maddy is betrayed, she and Cole reunite – to ruin prom.
While patiently waiting for her boyfriend to come out of his coma, Audrey finds herself falling for the caring and successful Ethan.
Four individuals in modern India grapple with their identities amid social taboos, trauma and brutal sexual discrimination in this quartet of stories.
Growing up in poverty and political turmoil, he found his way out in the ring. The early years of world-famous boxer Manny Pacquiao unfolds in this biopic.
After the untimely demise of her first three husbands, a stoic single mom is left to raise twelve children on her own and provide for her big family.
A happily married man gives in to temptation when a wealthy client pursues him, setting off a torrid love triangle.
Cameras follow Tommy Caldwell and Kevin Jorgeson as they take on the staggering challenge of free-climbing Yosemite’s most formidable rock formation.
Cinematographers visit the remote forests and mountains of China in hopes of capturing footage of pandas, monkeys, red-crowned cranes and more.
Warehouse workers Vince and Zack compete in a full-on war to be named Employee of the Month and win a date with their dream girl.
Originally polar opposites, an American fashion student and the daughter of an industry mogul form an everlasting bond and start a rock band in Milan.
Fifteen years after a traumatic crime, a woman is released from psychiatric care and tries to drive out an evil spirit that continues to haunt her.
When a man is left to die inside an illegal gold mine, his daughter travels through a magical landscape to save him.

column4: Trailer Park Boys: The Animated Series
column8: Nova Scotia’s favorite miscreants have always been super sketchy. Now, carrying on from the Season 12 finale, the boys have become complete cartoons.

column4: Bure Kaam Bura Natija, Kyun Bhai Chacha Haan Bhatija
column8: A clever uncle-nephew duo solves mysteries, crimes and other problems for the citizens of a colorful town where something zany is always going down.
A law professor is enlisted by Mexico's attorney general to join a special operations unit infiltrating the capital's most notorious drug cartel.
Following a devastating alien invasion, an American soldier and a French foreign aid worker attempt to find refuge in the Kenyan countryside.

column4: Th Eena Meena Deeka Chase Comedy Show
column8: A hungry fox and three resourceful, surprisingly formidable birds turn the animal kingdom on its head in this lively animated series.
En route to a fresh start in Los Angeles, young couple Alex and Scarlett stop over in a sleepy Southwestern town that loosens their grip on reality.

column4: Bridget Christie: Stand Up for Her
column8: Performing stand-up for a packed house in London's Hoxton Hall, comedian Bridget Christie dives into the politics of gender, sex and equality.
A young couple fights supernatural foes in an attempt to save their daughter from the dark and mysterious forces that follow her every move.
Five acclaimed contemporary directors tell the story of five legendary Hollywood filmmakers who enlisted in the armed forces to document World War II.

column4: GLOW: The Story of the Gorgeous Ladies of Wrestling
column8: This engaging documentary chronicles the 1980s phenomenon "The Gorgeous Ladies of Wrestling," which elevated its female grapplers to star status.
This detailed examination of the 1945 Hiroshima bombing includes the prelude to and aftermath of history's controversial first use of atomic weapons.
Though culturally insensitive by modern standards, this propaganda film examines the history of Japan from the 16th century through the 1930s.
Some returning combat veterans suffer scars that are more psychological than physical. This film follows patients and staff during their treatment.
When his reclusive-banker lover disappears, a hard-partying young British hedonist plunges into the dangerous world of espionage to find the truth.
Join zoologist Dr. George McGavin for a fascinating, up-close look at the habits and behaviors of primates, our closest animal relatives.
Shocking footage shows Nazi concentration camps after liberation, including Buchenwald and Ohrdruf, where Gen. Eisenhower ordered local Nazis to tour.
When her father moves his family to an industrial mill town, the parson's daughter, Margaret Hale, struggles to adapt to her harsh new surroundings.
Frank Capra's documentary chronicles the rise of authoritarianism in Germany, Italy and Japan as America prepares for a defense of liberty.
After the Allies invade Italy, the Liri Valley town of San Pietro becomes an example of the brutal effects of combat, both for soldiers and civilians.
Director John Ford captures combat footage of the Battle of Midway, an air and sea campaign that was a turning point in the war in the Pacific.
A scientist whose proof of an afterlife caused a rash of suicides forges ahead with his research, while his disapproving son falls for a troubled woman.
Richie Beckett is an aging Brighton crime boss who's struggling with the onset of dementia, just as a rival gang is trying to take over his territory.
This two-part tale delivers the true story of the Great Train Robbery of 1963, the biggest one in England's history.

column4: The Memphis Belle: A Story of a
column8: Not Provided
Not Provided
This series tracks the ups and downs of an 18-month investigation into the 2014 stabbing murder of teenager Nicholas Robinson in Bristol, England.
This documentary urged African Americans to enlist and join in the effort to be part of America's continuing fight in World War II.
A P-47 Thunderbolt squadron is shown in preparation, at play and in bombing raids aiming to halt Nazi supply lines and aid Allied ground troops.
British and American troops join forces to liberate a Nazi stranglehold in North Africa, sharing battles, hard work and a peaceful Christmas dinner.

column4: Undercover: How to Operate Behind Enemy Lines
column8: This World War II-era training film dramatizes how secret agents should act while undercover and how to avoid capture by enemies.

column4: Why We Fight: The Battle of Russia
column8: This installment of Frank Capra's acclaimed documentary series highlights the need for a Russo-American alliance to defeat the Nazis.
The natural bounty of Alaska sustains its diverse species through extreme weather conditions in three seasons, each with its rewards and challenges.
The widely varied geology and dramatic landscapes in the continental crossroads of Arabia harbors a rich history and an abundance of wildlife.
Filmmaker John Huston narrates this Oscar-nominated World War II-era film about life among the U.S. soldiers protecting Alaska’s Aleutian Islands.
Christian musician Israel Houghton leads his band Israel & New Breed on a tour supporting their newest album of multicultural, hybrid-genre songs.
Ken Bruen's bestselling crime novels leap to life in this series of TV movies featuring Irish cop-turned-private-investigator Jack Taylor.
Equipped with crayons and his creativity, a boy with autism draws an imaginary world where his animal pals help him tackle real-life situations.
When two brothers fall for two sisters, they quickly realize the age differences between them are too big to ignore.
A tenacious high school girl raised in foster homes in the inner city tries to reconnect with her ex-con father by joining a boys wrestling team.
A quirky couple spends their three-year dating anniversary looking back at their relationship and contemplating whether they should break up.
A petty thief teams up with two bickering accomplices to safeguard a powerful relic and save humankind from a tribe of vengeful, winged humanoids.
Groundbreaking artists share their life stories in this vibrant documentary series that captures hip-hop's impact on global culture.

column4: Sofía Niño de Rivera: Selección Natural
column8: Mexico's Sofía Niño de Rivera brings her dark humor to the stage with jokes about marriage traps, sexually attractive leopards and funny funerals.
On a bleak future Earth, a soldier endures a radical genetic transformation to save humanity. But his wife fears he's becoming more creature than man.

column4: Trailer Park Boys: Countdown to Liquor Day
column8: After their latest jail stint, boozy pals Julian, Bubbles and Ricky plan to go legit but learn trailer park manager Jim aims to demolish their homes.
In this feature-length adventure, Ricky, Julian and Bubbles – just out of jail – plan the lamest scheme yet: to get rich by stealing tons of change.
Friends, associates and critics reveal the truly American story of Donald Trump, the brash businessman who defied the odds to become U.S. president.
A weekend hike for urbanites Alex and Jenn takes a dangerous turn when they become lost deep in the remote territory of a menacing bear.
When Christopher Columbus mysteriously appears in modern-day Kolkata, India, two struggling young men look to him for advice on achieving success.
Fallen Los Angeles police officer Terrence Downe finds new life as a secret weapon: a scientifically altered super-cop with unlimited lives.
When James's living situation turns sour, he has little choice but to move in with his new girlfriend – a decision he almost immediately regrets.

column4: Middle School: The Worst Years of My Life
column8: At Hills Village Middle School, budding cartoonist Rafe and best pal Leo challenge their uptight principal by breaking every rule in his handbook.
Aspiring hip-hop star Francisco builds a name for himself as a musical artist while his conscience helps him through family drama and discrimination.
On India's Independence Day, a zany mishap in a Mumbai chawl disrupts a young love story while compelling the residents to unite in aid of a little boy.
Alone in Finland, a retired Mexican boxer lives in desolation under the weight of an agonizing past, until he gets a shot at redemption in the ring.
While investigating the disappearance of a teen girl in a tight-knit Galician town, a Civil Guard officer uncovers secrets linked to a loss of her own.
In near-future Paris, two brilliant siblings unveil a high-tech implant designed to pair up soul mates. But the beta test yields unwelcome surprises.
Husband. Father. Fighter. Meet Chuck Wepner, the liquor salesman and self-proclaimed real-life inspiration behind Rocky Balboa.
Two steely former Texas Rangers are tasked with tracking and killing infamous criminals Bonnie and Clyde in this crime drama based on real events.
An urban legend about a duffel bag of cocaine buried in the Caribbean leads a misfit band to hatch a nutball plan to find it in this comic documentary.
Social pressure, a complicated past and a clash of values beset the life of a businessman and his family.
