After an actor is hit by a car driven by the police commissioner's sister, his scheming brother-in-law files a bogus suit against the commissioner.
The wounds of a traumatic childhood and a corrupt, unjust system push a young man into becoming a cold-blooded, ruthless gangster.
Teen idol Justin Bieber provides personal snapshots from throughout his career, culminating with scenes from his triumphant 2010 concert tour.
Wrongfully accused of murder, two students' last hope lies with their defense attorney, an inexperienced bumbler who's never even tried a case.
On his first visit to his home city of Kolkata in 13 years, a Paris-based chef is faced with a cooking challenge that will change his life forever.
This documentary chronicles the rise of the footwear designer behind a billion-dollar empire and his subsequent comeback after a financial scandal.
When the son of a wealthy businessman and the daughter of a struggling engineer fall in love, the young man's parents question the girl's motives.

column4: Martin Luther: The Idea that Changed the World
column8: This docudrama tells the dramatic story of the monk who took on the Catholic Church, tracing his life before and after the contentious "95 Theses."
An orphan girl who has ambitions of marrying a rich man changes her identity to win the heart of a prominent businessman's son.
After a disgruntled man blames his Marathi heritage for his lack of his success, he is visited by Shivaji, a great medieval Marathi king.

column4: Monster High: Escape from Skull Shores
column8: A swanky cruise veers off course for Lagoona and her friends when they're left stranded on Skull Shores, an island with a notorious beast.
In their bid to win the Skulltimate Roller Maze championship, Monster High loses its star players, Clawd and Deuce, to injury.
Big changes are afoot at Monster High when administrators announce a merger with two other schools, designed to bring all monsters together.
Draculaura is whisked to Transylvania to be crowned vampire queen, but when she learns she's been duped, the search is on for the true royal heir.

column4: Monster High: Why Do Ghouls Fall in Love?
column8: Draculaura's ghoulfriends have some suspicions about one of her two persistent suitors – but can they stop him before he steals her un-beating heart?
An 18-year-old struggling to understand her best friend's suicide talks to teenagers who have grappled with mental illness and suicidal thoughts.

column4: Now More Than Ever: The History of Chicago
column8: This rockumentary tells the behind-the-scenes story of the Hall-of-Fame band Chicago, from their jazz-rock fusion roots to chart-topping pop hits.
A self-diagnosed nymphomaniac reveals a lifetime of sexual experiences to a man who saves her from being beaten in an alley.
In pre-World War II France, two sisters purport to be able to communicate with the dead and soon catch the eye of an ambitious filmmaker.
Explore the world of Pokémon with 10-year-old Ash Ketchum and his partner, Pikachu, as they aim for Ash's ultimate goal: becoming a Pokémon master.
The results of a DNA test spur Puerto Rican rap icon Residente to set out on a global voyage in search of his roots and fresh musical inspiration.

In an effort to honor the family matriarch's dying wish, Urmila and her husband, Shrikant, embark on a quest to find a husband for charismatic yet choosey Sai. But some things are easier said than done.
At large in the city, five inmates of a mental asylum run up against the insanity of the outside world while trying to prevent a terrorist plot.
A tragic accident drives a wedge between two teenage boys, threatening a friendship that had seemed firm and unshakeable.
Formerly a Korean resistance fighter, a policeman working for Japan is tasked with tracking down resistance leaders before they acquire explosives.
An arbitration panel is formed after a company CEO in Nigeria is sued for wrongful dismissal and rape by an employee with whom he had an affair.
An optimistic farmer is determined to succeed in spite of the lack of rain in his region, and the sinking spirits around him.
A grisly find atop a mountain in the French Pyrenees leads investigator Martin Servaz into a twisted dance with a serial killer in this icy thriller.
A drama student is torn between creative possibility and ethical boundaries when his girlfriend's family gets caught up in a sex scandal.
When a power failure throws their suburban town into chaos, Matthew and his wife stoop to desperate measures to secure medication for their child.
A bank heist takes an unnerving turn when the three sibling robbers attempt to gain entrance into an subterranean vault with sinister secrets.
Personality differences, an old friend and a past flame poke holes in the way a husband and wife perceive their marriage.

column4: Treasures from the Wreck of the Unbelievable
column8: This cinematic journey into the waters off East Africa chronicles the story behind artist Damien Hirst's massive exhibition of oceanic treasures.
Trained dancer Vandana Hart travels the world to learn traditional and urban dance styles from the local experts who know them best.

Thanks to an arranged marriage that was designed to make an ailing grandmother happy, newlyweds Rahul and Swati are virtually strangers. Can a four-day honeymoon make a difference when it comes to the couple's feelings about each other?
As her seemingly idyllic life begins to crumble, a lonely woman in a restrictive marriage starts an affair with a gentle bookstore owner.
Extensive film clips and interviews tell the story of American filmmaker Ellis R. Dungan, who spent 15 years in India and helped define Tamil cinema.
Raised by three mothers, a self-assured teen in turmoil meets the father figure she never had. But she also stands to drive the man and his son apart.
A production crew that thinks it's making a documentary about a humble Mumbai rickshaw driver unmasks a horrifying truth about their film's subject.
Barry, a worker bee stuck in a dead-end job making honey, sues humans when he learns they've been stealing bees' nectar all along.
Still haunted by the traumatic event that ended her high school romance, a young professional gets a new subordinate: her former sweetheart.
An unexpected pregnancy sends a woman back to her hometown to share a house with three nice guys. Each has problems, but each would make a great dad.
After his wife inexplicably disappears, a man takes their two children and relocates to his hometown in an attempt to end their grief and move on.
Fired for being gay, schoolteacher Richard returns in drag as force-of-nature Bianca, gets hired for the same job and plots sweet, scornful revenge.
An author having trouble finishing his new romance novel because he's lost faith in love regains his romantic soul after meeting a flight attendant.
An elderly, hearing-impaired Indian man stays connected to the world of the past through the beloved valve radio he has owned since childhood.
A charming cabbie, a cop turned assassin and a housewife who’s also a hooker share one thing in common: a bizarre and violent afternoon in Kolkata.
In the rugged mountains of Afghanistan, armed bands of young boys survive by scavenging for old land mines, mining lapis lazuli and trading in opium.
Examine the troublesome coexistence of humans and rodents in Mumbai, where the byproducts of a big economy have led to a thriving rat population.
Explore how the media and nationalism have fueled Venezuela's passion for physical appearance and the multibillion-dollar beauty pageant industry.
Drug abuse and the darker side of Punjab rear their heads in the intense, interwoven tales of a cop, a doctor, a migrant worker and a rock star.
A 32-year-old romantic looking for a long-term, monogamous relationship meets a handsome bad boy who only believes in one-night stands.
A doctor performs plastic surgery on a fat man who's been jilted, and continues his transformation by turning him into a handsome, desirable man.
In the 1970s, a group of activists who gathered to protest nuclear testing formed the iconic Greenpeace environmental organization.
Visitors arrive from space to help Red Ranger and his squad – temporarily stripped of their powers – fight against Lord Zedd and Rita Repulsa.
Everyone's favorite teenage mutants are back in live action to fight crime with help from a new ninja turtle – a female named Venus De Milo.
Dr. Tommy Oliver returns when his students discover the Dino Gems that morph them into the Dino Power Rangers, enabling them to stop the evil Mesogog.
With the Power Chamber destroyed, former Turbo Power Rangers T.J., Cassie, Carlos and Ashley search for Zordon, who's been abducted by Dark Specter.
The Power Rangers travel to California in search of their new master and find him running a pizza parlor – so they join the staff to be trained.
As demons rumble from their graves beneath Mariner Bay, a government organization called Lightspeed recruits five civilians to defend the city.
Five teenagers, transformed by the mystical powers of the Quasar Sabers into the Galaxy Power Rangers, battle the evil Scorpius and Captain Mutiny.
When the wicked Undead Army is unleashed, sorceress Udonna empowers five teenagers – the Mystic Force Power Rangers – to save mankind.
When the elite warriors from the Wind Ninja Academy are captured by the evil Lothor, Shane, Tori and Waldo become Wind Power Rangers to fight back.
To keep powerful jewels from falling into the hands of two wicked brothers, five young Power Rangers set out on a dangerous global adventure.
The Power Rangers' new member, Dillon, isn't sure he wants to be on the team until he has a dream that sets the Rangers into action.
When the Troobian Empire attacks Earth, the B-Squad Power Rangers Space Patrol Delta morphs into action to squash the alien threat and save the world.
A new generation of Power Rangers must master the Symbols of Samurai Power, which give them control over the Earth's elements to battle dark forces.

column4: Power Rangers Samurai: Christmas Together, Friends Forever (Christmas Special)
column8: On Christmas Eve, as the teens at Shiba House reflect on their first year together, they get an unexpected lesson on the true spirit of the holidays.

column4: Power Rangers Samurai: Clash of the Red Rangers
column8: The Samurai Rangers team up with the RPM Ranger Red to fight off Master Xandred's Mooger army and a robotic villain from the RPM Ranger's dimension.

column4: Power Rangers Samurai: Party Monsters (Halloween Special)
column8: On Halloween night, the creepiest creatures from the Netherworld trade war stories about their battles with the Samurai Power Rangers.
Armed with a key that allows them to morph into any team of Legendary Rangers from the past, the Super Megaforce Rangers fight ruthless Prince Vekar.

column4: Power Rangers Super Megaforce: The Legendary Battle (Extended)
column8: New footage augments the tale of the Rangers, who give their all to save Earth from Vrak and Emperor Mavro, as the Armada stages an epic final attack.
The Samurai Power Rangers continue their battle against the evil Master Xandred, who has now joined forces with the malevolent Serrator.

column4: Power Rangers Super Samurai: Stuck on Christmas
column8: The Samurai Rangers get stuck in the Megazord's cockpit on Christmas Eve when it breaks down. Can the Rangers get out in time for Christmas?

column4: Power Rangers Super Samurai: Trickster Treat
column8: When a Nighlok invades the Samurai Rangers' dreams and turns them into nightmares, the Rangers must figure out what is reality and what is illusion.
The team launches a new campaign against evil in the year 3000, when the imprisoned criminal mastermind Ransik is freed by his daughter.
The Rangers use high-tech battle cars to take on Queen Divatox and her Divazords, who mount an attack on the Rangers' beloved Angel Grove.
Raised in the wilderness, young Cole Evans leads the Wild Force Power Rangers as they summon their animal powers to battle the evil Master Org.
This "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers" spinoff finds Tommy and the gang battling new enemies, using abilities acquired from the Zeo Crystal.
When Earth is threatened by a massive alien invasion, the planet's supernatural guardian calls upon five teenagers to form the ultimate defense team.
On Halloween, the scariest night of the year, the Rangers have a strange encounter with a mysterious medium who conjures "visions" of monsters past.

column4: Power Rangers: Megaforce: The Robo Knight Before Christmas
column8: Robo Knight learns the meaning of Christmas from a group of children when he is mistaken for a donated Christmas toy and is shipped to a foreign land.
Join Strawberry Shortcake and her berry best friends in the whimsical land of Berry Bitty City, where they learn about teamwork and decision-making.
While covering a story in New York City, a Seattle-based reporter uncovers a link between two missing women that changes her article entirely.
After a young mother is widowed by war, her faith is tested as she struggles to stay afloat financially and raise her daughter.
Three 30-something women in high-level jobs at a beauty e-commerce firm seem to have it all – except when it comes to love and romantic chemistry.
Explore the public and private sides of feminist firebrand attorney Gloria Allred, who's battled some of the biggest names in politics and business.
Four friends with a long-standing – but strained – connection take a hiking trip into the Swedish wilderness, from which they may never return.
A traveling trader provides a window into rural life in the Republic of Georgia, where potatoes are currency and ambition is crushed by poverty.
In an otherworldly river town, a policeman follows the trail of a sinister force to save his community from deadly spells.
Using a magical photo booth that sends him back in time, Noah relives the night he met Avery over and over, trying to persuade her to fall for him.
A recovering addict becomes her estranged daughter's only hope after the teen awakens a terrifying child-stealing witch from an urban legend.
When an NBA lockout sidelines his big rookie client, an agent hatches a bold plan to save their careers – and disrupt the league's power structure.
When Elastigirl gets recruited for a high-profile crime-fighting mission, Mr. Incredible takes on his toughest assignment ever: full-time parenting.

column4: Kevin Hart's Guide to Black History
column8: Kevin Hart highlights the fascinating contributions of black history’s unsung heroes in this entertaining – and educational – comedy special.
The fun, fondant and hilarious cake fails head to Mexico, where very amateur bakers compete to re-create elaborate sweet treats for a cash prize.

column4: ReMastered: The Two Killings of Sam Cooke
column8: While Sam Cooke rose to stardom as a soul singer, his outspoken views on civil rights drew attention that may have contributed to his death at age 33.
As a young couple write the story of their families' shared history, both reveal their relatives' dark secrets and one must make a painful confession.
When a Galician shipper and drug lord hiding his Alzheimer's disease plans to retire, his second-in-command plots to steal the empire from the heir.
When armed gunmen seize the Iranian Embassy in 1980, a tense six-day standoff ensues while elite British soldiers prepare for a dangerous raid.
Happy koala Blinky Bill and some spunky pals travel the Outback following clues to help him find his long-lost father and finally bring him home.
Desperate to break up with his clingy girlfriend, a nerdy cartoonist hires a mysterious agency to do the deed. But the agency has unusual methods.
Equipped with a mechanical heart and determined to stay out of death's shadow, young Jack understands that love could prove fatal.
How was the scientific understanding of the ancients so advanced? A team of experts answers this and other questions in this fascinating series.
A young woman's attempt to come out of the closet on Thanksgiving gets complicated when her male roommate shows up to her parents' home unannounced.
The year is 2041 and a dispute between a man and his wife has set the human race back. In this battle of the sexes, the primitive life isn't so simple.

column4: Michael Bolton's Big, Sexy Valentine's Day Special
column8: After Santa tells him he needs 75,000 new babies by Christmas to meet toy supply, Michael Bolton hosts a telethon to inspire the world to make love.
Framed by an empress who plans to steal a dragon-taming mace, imperial magistrate Dee Renjie soon uncovers a greater plot that threatens the kingdom.
A divorced handyman with a drinking problem bonds with his 8-year-old son when a search for his stolen toolbox leads to a series of misadventures.
For an audience of drummers, comedian Fred Armisen shares and demonstrates his thoughts on musical genres, drummer quirks, regional accents and more.
Following an unsuccessful mission in Somalia, the two surviving members of a U.S. Army helicopter crew are embroiled in an unseemly conspiracy.
A marijuana farmer's extraterrestrial paranoia creates trouble for a group of young campers who pitch their tent on his land in Northern California.
A rascally bird with a distinctive laugh pecks back with a vengeance when his forest habitat is threatened by a slick lawyer building his dream home.
After each of them loses a child to murder, two women who meet in a support group initiate their own investigation when the police are no help.
While investigating an actress’s supposed suicide and her connection to the mafia, a veteran journalist discovers that corruption runs deep.
The police officers at South Korea's busiest patrol division toil day and night as keepers of law and peace – but the reality is far from orderly.

column4: Ray Romano: Right Here, Around the Corner
column8: Ray Romano cut his stand-up teeth at the Comedy Cellar in New York. Now, in his first comedy special in 23 years, he returns to where it all began.
After his teenage daughter goes missing, a widowed surgeon in an affluent neighborhood begins unearthing dark secrets about the people closest to him.
An Egyptian doctor becomes a police informant and uses his rare gift of tracking ancient artifacts in the smuggling business.
The war is over, and Violet Evergarden needs a job. Scarred and emotionless, she takes a job as a letter writer to understand herself and her past.
An undercover detective crosses paths with familiar faces in the mafia underworld during the final years of Britain's ruling of Hong Kong.
A teenager moves to Chicago for the summer and finds a poignant mentor in her aunt and a sweet love interest in a girl who works in the neighborhood.
Orbiting above a planet on the brink of war, scientists test a device to solve an energy crisis and end up face-to-face with a dark alternate reality.
After moving to a hardscrabble suburban California town, a young woman becomes dangerously entangled with a local drug enterprise.
This documentary examines the naked yoga gurus of India whose devout spiritual practice connects them to the eternal, transcending the material world.
Four astronomers from England celebrate 50 years of friendship and achievement by taking a reflective road trip through the American Southwest.
A magical ring holds the key to life, death and love for a marine archaeologist who seems to live two lives in different centuries and countries.
In a special packed with stealthy humor, Hannibal Buress tackles zipper etiquette, the legacy of steroids and the fallout from his Bill Cosby routine.
A security expert and ex-CIA agent living in Belgium must go on the run with his estranged teen daughter when they're both marked for assassination.
After an architect transforms a slaughterhouse into trendy lofts, its new inhabitants discover that the structure is haunted by its evil past.
An aimless, unemployed millennial hangs out with his pals and resists growing up, until an affair with his best friend's girl forces him to change.
In each episode, four celebrities join host Jon Favreau for dinner and share revealing stories about both show business and their personal lives.
A gifted writer who's the youngest editor-in-chief ever at his publishing company gets enmeshed in the life of a former copywriter desperate for a job.
Comedian Daniel Sosa inhabits various characters, including a Tupperware dealer, a thirsty priest and a Trojan horse soldier in this stand-up special.
A young father returns home from jail eager to care for his son and become a writer, but crime, poverty and a flawed system threaten his plans.
This documentary recounts the life story of evangelist preacher Billy Graham featuring interviews with family members and former presidents.
When a Marine's mission goes awry, he must survive behind enemy lines – without stepping off a mine – among the harsh elements of a desert war zone.
When a near-drowning leaves a famous singer from the '90s with amnesia, she hires a karaoke singer who can imitate her to prep her for a comeback tour.
This documentary follows three players on the Miami Heat Wheels, who face long odds on the way to the national wheelchair basketball championship.
The alcohol-fueled high jinks of a bachelor party go haywire when the buddies of an ill-fated groom abduct his fiancée's new lover.
After people in his town start turning up dead, a grumpy landlord is visited by a man who recounts an unsolved serial murder case from 30 years ago.
Trace the brave journey of actor Andy Whitfield, who received a devastating cancer diagnosis while starring in the series "Spartacus: Blood and Sand."

column4: Mike Birbiglia: Thank God for Jokes
column8: Comedian Mike Birbiglia takes the stage in Brooklyn and hits on hard truths about puppets, late people and the very real dangers of being funny.
The lives of several friends are thrown into chaos when a woman becomes pregnant by her husband's gay best friend after a drunken one-night stand.
Following their storybook wedding, Popoy and Basha find married life – and starting a business together – more challenging than they ever imagined.
Finding himself in a desperate situation, undercover agent Emman asks his former best friend, Erika, to join him on a dangerous mission.
Rocco needs to hire a bride so he can access his trust fund. Rocky desperately needs a job. Their marriage starts out fake, but ends up as much more.
Gab is eager to tie the knot with her handsome boyfriend, but there's a problem, and it's a doozy: She's already married to a total stranger.
When her son comes out to her as gay, a religious mother struggles to reconcile his truth with her own beliefs and their orthodox family values.
Four sisters unite to stop their young brother's pending nuptials upon meeting his fiancée’s demanding family, revealing long-simmering family issues.
Quadruplets separated as babies reunite in Manila when one needs a liver transplant, but long-held family resentments threaten to derail everything.

column4: It Takes a Man and a Woman
column8: Laida and Miggy used to be in love, but now they're forced to work together in a professional capacity – and neither is completely over their past.
Popular blogger Cali is hired for a marketing campaign alongside another viral sensation: her ex-boyfriend Gio, who's intent on winning her back.
Inspired by Malaysia's 14th General Election, this film trails six individuals and the obstacles they face in the days leading up to the historic event.
To make another woman jealous, a campus heartthrob asks a fellow student to be his pretend girlfriend, but fate has other plans for the fake couple.
A rock musician and a law student whose true passion is music fall in love and pursue a romance that complicates both of their blossoming careers.
The mistress of a wealthy businessman is torn between her loyalty to him and her love for a young architect connected to her in unexpected ways.

column4: The Only Mother To You All
column8: Raising her large family alone after her husband's death, Ina searches for work and finally lands the most unlikely job: president of the Philippines.
Ride along for a dramatized version of the real-life investigations into the murders of rap icons Tupac Shakur and Biggie Smalls.
Laida and Miggy think they've found perfect happiness with each other, until their burgeoning careers force them into a long-distance relationship.
Pong, a corporate assistant, poses as his company’s president in order to help Georgina, a marketing executive, close a crucial business deal.
Mentalist Derren Brown engineers an audacious social experiment demonstrating how manipulation can lead an ordinary person to commit an appalling act.
Rollicking, outrageous and audacious, Marlon Wayans gets raw on racism, age-appropriate rap rhymes, gay rights, raising kids and even the Kardashians.
An ex-cop investigates the death of his best friend and two other spies, killings that lead to a mole operating from India's embassy in Budapest.
Filmed in front of a raucous crowd, comedian Ralphie May unleashes his hilariously raunchy perspective in his first Netflix original stand-up special.
A seemingly clueless idealist relies on his exasperated sisters for shelter and support after his girlfriend dumps him and his dog is taken away.

column4: Zach Galifianakis: Live at the Purple Onion
column8: The unorthodox, piano-playing stand-up star Zach Galifianakis makes a splash on the scene and serves up a healthy dose of his signature wit.
A shy luddite gains fame, attention and friends after he uses photoshop skills to create a fake glamorous life on social media.

column4: The Heyday of the Insensitive Bastards
column8: An all-star cast brings to life the short stories of author Robert Boswell in this anthology series of vignettes set in modern-day America.

column4: The Rift: The Dark Side of the Moon
column8: When a team of special agents is sent to recover the wreckage of a downed satellite in Serbia, their mission takes a horrifying turn.
Winnie Mandela speaks about her extraordinary and controversial career, from her early life to her marriage to her ongoing efforts to end apartheid.
During Carnival, two teens from different classes meet years after being kept apart. Bad decisions lead the boy to hide with the girl inside a float.

column4: Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon: Sword of Destiny
column8: Renowned warrior Yu Shu-Lien comes out of retirement to keep the legendary Green Destiny sword away from villainous warlord Hades Dai.
In a society terrorized into silence, the brother of a 1960s Indonesian genocide victim learns the identity of his murderers and confronts them.
Bad news from the past unhinges vagabond Dwight Evans, sending him on a mission of bloody retribution that takes him to his childhood hometown.
Winter the dolphin, who survived a tragic injury by receiving a prosthetic tail, bonds with an orphaned baby dolphin after her beloved pool mate dies.
When authorities jail his son for rejecting religious bias, a poor father’s struggle to bail him out highlights rural India’s enduring casteism.
In 1991 Madrid, after holding a séance at school, a teen girl minding her younger siblings at home suspects an evil force has entered their apartment.
When Anastasia Cardona's drug lord husband is murdered, she inherits his cocaine empire, leading to a life of wealth, power, violence and betrayal.
In a crime-plagued area of Rio de Janeiro, a team of honest cops, including a determined rookie, fights corruption and mistrust on all sides.
With his hometown in ruins, young Eren Yeager becomes determined to fight back against the giant Titans that threaten to destroy the human race.
World War IV is over, but a bomb has gone off in Newport City, killing a major arms dealer who may have ties with the mysterious 501 Organization.
As Motoko and Batou attempt to thwart a mysterious terrorist group, Togusa tracks the killer of a man with a prosthetic leg made by Mermaid's Leg.
Freed of her responsibilities for the 501 Organization, Motoko must now learn how to take orders from Aramaki.

column4: I Don't Feel at Home in This World Anymore
column8: A timid nursing assistant gets a new lease on life when she and a neighborhood loner track down the degenerates who broke into her house.
When an evil force threatens his village, a gifted teen who can talk to ghosts puts his skills to good use, one legend at a time.
Based on Korea's longest-running webtoon series, this comedy follows the ridiculous daily lives of a cartoonist, his girlfriend and his subpar family.

column4: Marvel Super Hero Adventures: Frost Fight!
column8: In this Christmas-themed special, Captain America and the Avengers battle Loki and Ymir, who plot to steal Santa Claus' powers and conquer the world.
A Catalán prisoner at a Nazi concentration camp uses his office job to steal photo negatives of the atrocities committed there. Based on true events.
Two young stars with different backgrounds and agendas enter into a fake marriage to advance their careers, until the fake starts turning real.
When his girlfriend vanishes, a mute man ventures into a near-future Berlin's seamy underworld, where his actions speak louder than words.
The death of a 15-year-old African American boy in Jersey City sets off a police cover-up and a search for the truth.
Firsthand accounts, re-enactments and computer-generated graphics retell in detail Thailand's biggest news stories from the past.
All the flavor. None of the BS. Star chef David Chang leads friends on a mouthwatering, cross-cultural hunt for the world's most satisfying grub.
On a remote island, elite soldiers discover their training exercise is actually an experimental death trap teeming with efficiently lethal robots.
This firsthand account tells of two kidnapped South Korean movie professionals who became the unwilling personal filmmakers of dictator Kim Jong-il.
From his run-in with a grizzly bear to partying with the Russian mafia, the shirtless comic returns with laugh-out-loud tales in this stand-up special.
While she successfully advocates for her female clients in difficult divorce cases, a lawyer’s trauma from sexual assault impacts her own marriage.
After he's diagnosed with terminal cancer, middle-aged Michael asks his neighbor friend Andy to help him end his life before the disease does.
Amid a turbulent romance and rising tensions in Paris, a young woman finds herself caught in a dizzying spiral of dreams, memories and what-ifs.
An older woman's unique friendship with a young boy inspires her to examine the strained relationship she shares with her married son.
A former Mafia hit man living quietly as a mechanic veers back into his old world after his daughter is abducted and faces an old foe in New Orleans.
Donald Rumsfeld reviews his long political career, from his time in Congress to serving as secretary of defense under Gerald Ford and George W. Bush.
A man from a criminal family yearns to break away and find a better life, but his father's staunch opposition puts his dreams of freedom in jeopardy.
Surviving power struggles, betrayals and plots, Hitler's inner circle of Nazi leaders seizes control of Germany and designs its disastrous future.
Ken Burns's documentary depicts the action of famous Civil War battles, and relates the stories of soldiers, generals and a beleaguered president.

column4: Ken Burns: The Roosevelts: An Intimate History
column8: Award-winning documentarian Burns profiles three members of one of America's premier political families: Theodore, Franklin and Eleanor Roosevelt.
This dramatic documentary explores the life and mind of Magnus Carlsen, the charismatic Norwegian prodigy who became world chess champion.

column4: Prohibition: A Film by Ken Burns and Lynn Novick
column8: Ken Burns's documentary traces the passage of the 18th Amendment, the social and legal effects of prohibiting alcohol, and the repeal of Prohibition.
Tales of tragedy and scandal unfold through the history of Chatsworth, a grand estate that has been home to some of England's most noted aristocrats.

column4: Secrets of Henry VIII's Palace: Hampton Court
column8: The history of this grand 500-year-old palace is inextricably tied to the lavish lifestyle of King Henry VIII and the doomed fates of his six wives.

column4: Secrets of Her Majesty's Secret Service
column8: This documentary spotlights more than 100 years of operatives and operations in the U.K.'s secret service, the world's oldest intelligence agency.
Known as the setting of "Downton Abbey," Highclere Castle truly was the home of aristocrats and an army of servants, with a rich past to share.

column4: Secrets of the Tower of London
column8: Explore the storied history of the iconic Tower of London as it evolved from a royal castle into a dungeon prison and, finally, an armory and mint.

column4: The War: A Film by Ken Burns and Lynn Novick
column8: A seven-part series brings World War II to life through the harrowing personal accounts of soldiers and others from "typical" American towns.
A petty smuggler from Busan dives headfirst into illicit drug trafficking in the 1970s and rises to become king of narcotics exports to Japan.
During a trip to Jamaica, a London gang targets a disloyal member who has been meeting with rivals. Meanwhile, an undercover cop stands among them.
When his abducted brother returns seemingly a different man with no memory of the past 19 days, Jin-seok chases after the truth behind the kidnapping.
Director Steven Spielberg takes on the towering legacy of Abraham Lincoln, focusing on his stewardship of the Union during the Civil War years.
After the death of his wife, a teacher and his son move to a new city, where emotional connections with two women help them begin to heal.

column4: Trevor Noah: Afraid of the Dark
column8: The "Daily Show" host ponders the perils of naming countries, how traffic lights turn New Yorkers invincible and why you shouldn't drink in Scotland.
Whoopi Goldberg narrates Elmo creator Kevin Clash's remarkable journey from a working-class Baltimore neighborhood to Jim Henson's "Sesame Street."

column4: Kevin James: Sweat the Small Stuff
column8: The film and television star riffs on life's many royal pains in this hourlong special taped at New York City's Hudson Theatre in 2001.
Powerlifter Matt Kroczaleski faced his greatest challenge when he came out as transgender. This documentary captures his transition into a woman.
A willing team of chefs and researchers goes on a gastronomic adventure around the globe to weigh the benefits of using bugs as a future food source.
A courageous 11-year-old Afghan girl disguises herself as a boy and takes on odd jobs to provide for her family when her father is arrested.
A modern love story is connected to an ancient folk tale as star-crossed lovers from different social classes are kept apart by their families.
A horror novelist with a traumatic past returns to her childhood hometown, where she revisits her night terrors and loses sight of reality.
A family’s tense reunion turns terrifying when they get trapped in their home by an unknown force, and sinister commands begin appearing on their TV.
When caste discrimination prevents a villager from giving his deceased father a rightful burial, he takes his fight for equality to court.
Hosted by Will Smith, this series follows eight astronauts who share their unique perspectives on Earth, the fragile and beautiful planet we call home.
Framed for her father’s murder, an exiled Viking princess is guided by the god Odin as she prepares to return to her kingdom and reclaim the throne.
After 250 years on ice, a prisoner returns to life in a new body with one chance to win his freedom: by solving a mind-bending murder.
Fueled by his own rough upbringing, Snoop Dogg creates a youth football league to keep at-risk kids off the streets and focused on their goals.
On a mission to defy stereotypes, Malaysian stand-up comedian Kavin Jay shares stories about growing up in the VHS era with his Singapore audience.
Two shy and socially awkward co-workers in Budapest form a special bond through a mysterious mystic connection that manifests in a dream.
Reunited in their hometown for their father's funeral, two self-interested brothers meet a peculiar woman who shares a huge secret about their family.
Surprise news that his girlfriend is pregnant sends loutish Owen on an ill-advised trip to reconnect with his twisted sister and sadistic grandmother.
After being recruited to be a raconteur in London, a handsome teenager discovers he suffers from a rare condition where he faints upon seeing fine art.

column4: Spy Kids: All the Time in the World
column8: Former Spy Kids Carmen and Juni return to help twin siblings Rebecca and Cecil Wilson save the world with their retired secret-agent stepmother.
Examine the triumphs, tragedies, cultural shifts and technological leaps that occurred during the millennium's first decade.
Los Angeles police officers embark on an innovative program mentoring promising students from the harsh, gang-infested Watts neighborhood.
An intelligent but intense honor student traumatizes his high school teacher and mentor when he doesn't get the grade he believes he deserves.
While alchemist Edward Elric searches for a way to restore his brother Al's body, the military government and mysterious monsters are watching closely.
Hiding his own murderous past, a man suffering from Alzheimer's must protect his daughter from her boyfriend, who he suspects is also a serial killer.
Four Korean celebrity men and guest stars of both genders discuss women, sex and relationships – to an unprecedented degree of openness.
When her son is kidnapped and later found traumatized, a lawyer takes justice into her own hands, causing events that spiral out of control.
Five baby animals from different parts of the world grow up learning to survive in the wild, nurtured by the love and guidance of their families.

column4: Tini: The New Life of Violetta
column8: After completing a world tour, a teen pop star spends the summer at an Italian villa to recover from heartbreak and grow into a mature artist.
As he tries his hand at baking, brewing and braising, acclaimed food writer Michael Pollan explores how cooking transforms food and shapes our world.
Teams of recently deceased people who've been revived and given high-tech weapons must cooperate to defeat an army of monsters in Tokyo and Osaka.
Two small abominable snowmen flee their mountain to escape a scientist who's trying to capture them and end up spending Christmas with a human family.
When he gets a fan letter from a young monster movie buff, Dracula visits him and soon has a new friend helping him to get his confidence back.
Extreme pressure from his father to excel at school during childhood has dangerous psychological effects on a brilliant but suicidal man’s adult life.
On returning home and finding they're believed to be dead, a collection of near-strangers from the same village try to find a reason for their plight.
Three friends on a wilderness trip find bags full of cash and must evade the criminal who hid the money in the first place.
Weeks before being named Miss World, Linor Abargil was raped. She tells the world her inspiring true story in this Emmy-nominated documentary.
A man buys a young girl, code-names her "Doll" and sends her to live with a mother of two who has a mysterious mission to be fulfilled.
Posing as a telecom salesman at a business conference, a CIA agent fights to protect a fledgling Eastern European democracy from a military coup.

column4: Love for Ten: Generation of Youth
column8: A nerdy engineering student falls for a pretty, outgoing girl at his college. To get closer to her, he joins the theater group she belongs to.
A bridge under construction collapses in Mumbai, killing a man's family and launching him on a crusade to bring those responsible to justice.
A reclusive pawn shop owner sets his sights on revenge when vicious gangsters kidnap his drug-addicted neighbor's young daughter.
Still desperate to find his granddaughter nearly a decade after her kidnapping, a devoted grandfather chases a dangerous new lead.
A hard-driving submarine captain is hired to steal gold from a sunken Nazi sub, but there's no honor among thieves during this underwater heist.
This documentary follows the rapid rise and fall of the Manhattan discotheque and the glittery debauchery that attracted the city's eccentric and elite.
When an ex-cop becomes a superintendent of an apartment building, he suspects the sinister janitor is behind the eerie disappearances of its tenants.
Argentine comedian Agustín "Radagast" Aristarán adds doses of magic, music and acting to his high-energy stand-up routine.
It's 1996 in a town called Boring, where high school misfits in the AV and drama clubs brave the ups and downs of teenage life in the VHS era.
A stunning cancer diagnosis spurs Abbie to seek a future girlfriend for fiancé and childhood sweetheart Sam, who's clueless when it comes to dating.
Explore the stories of ordinary people dealing with extraordinary circumstances in this series that focuses on overcoming obstacles and odds.
Sean Penn stars in this biopic about Harvey Milk, the openly gay San Francisco politician who was murdered by a disgruntled city supervisor in 1978.
When a programmer uses his wife's sympathetic voice for his company's customer service app, he starts to rely more on her idealized self than her.

column4: Marvel's Iron Man & Hulk: Heroes United
column8: When scientists join Hulk's gamma energy with Tony Stark's Arc Reactor, the resulting force creates a foe that only the two Marvel heroes can combat.
After learning of their son's death on the battlefield, a grieving Berlin couple embark on a quietly dangerous act of resistance against Adolf Hitler.
Amid a marital crisis, Fikret befriends songstress Solmaz after a wacky encounter and must fill in as the father of her soon-to-wed daughter.
Kat and Eva’s happy romance hits a rough patch when Eva decides that she wants a child. Visiting friend Roger could help complete their family.
Disparate characters, including an aspiring time traveler, a phony chef, a drug-addicted waitress and several others, share a surprising connection.
With his carefree bachelor days behind him, a young entrepreneur’s ambitions for adulthood come with some painful personal and professional decisions.
Meet the growing, worldwide community of theorists who defend the belief that the Earth is flat while living in a society who vehemently rejects it.
Inspired by the movie "Thelma & Louise," three young people with Down syndrome leave the institution where they live to take a road trip together.
On the incandescent shores of Goa, a young man tumbles down a mind-bending – and soon dangerous – series of trips after taking hallucinatory drugs.
While taking shelter from a Mumbai monsoon, an investment banker forms an unlikely connection with a naïve prostitute over the course of the night.
After a series of strange deaths, a high school reporter tries to pin down the killer who's targeting students eligible for a prestigious scholarship.
Killed too soon due to a clerical error in heaven, a man is sent back to earth with a new lease on life, this time in the body of his portly friend.
This miniseries spinoff of "Rita" follows teacher Hjørdis as she plans a school play on bullying featuring a cast of socially awkward students.

column4: Larry Charles' Dangerous World of Comedy
column8: Legendary comedy writer and director Larry Charles travels the world in search of humor in the most unusual, unexpected and dangerous places.
Days before Eid, a salesman fired from his job drives to Ayval?k to meet his girlfriend's family, but the trip goes astray due to his zany travel buddy.
When a blind chef’s girlfriend goes missing, his unnerving search for her leads him to find there's more to her disappearance than what meets the eye.
As his father sits behind bars, a young man is lured into Los Angeles' merciless drug world and forced to choose between God and gang life.
After a failed mission, an ex-Royal Marines Commando tries to overcome his demons while investigating the death of his ex-girlfriend's father.
A commitment-phobe agrees to marry his girlfriend, setting in motion a series of hilarious mishaps that has him questioning what he got himself into.
A renowned music teacher mentors a promising young singer, but when her fame begins to overshadow his own, he lets jealousy and competition take over.
This docuseries disputes the Mexican government's account of how and why 43 students from Ayotzinapa Rural Teachers' College vanished in Iguala in 2014.
For the right price, BFFs Jen and Mel will ruthlessly end any romance. But when one of them grows a conscience, their friendship begins to unravel.
Five high school students serving Saturday detention in a former corrections facility must find a way to outsmart an unseen menace out to kill them.
In the midnight hour, a lone DJ broadcasts the strangest – and scariest – tales from the outer edges of Kirlian, a lost city somewhere in Argentina.
Reunited by their father's death, estranged siblings with extraordinary powers uncover shocking family secrets – and a looming threat to humanity.
Everyday guy Kabir is thrown for a loop when he meets Kuhu, a freewheeling party girl. Now, he's a changed man, dancing, running half-naked through the streets and donning ladies' shoes at her whim.
When an old fling shows up with their infant child, a dallying man-child must take on the role of father and create a fairytale world for his daughter.
Competing con artists attempt to creatively and ruthlessly swindle a fatherly lottery winner while on a lively cruise from Spain to Mexico.
Caught between a corrupt mayor and a prosecutor intent on exposing political depravity, a police detective must decide whose side he's on.
A simple man's peaceful life is complicated when an incident brings him in contact with a gangster and launches his journey into the underworld.
A young man enlists the help of his friends to avenge his uncle's death by taking on a powerful, unscrupulous politician.
A jealous, possessive mother thinks she is competing with her new daughter-in-law for the affections of her overindulged son.
Two communities in Mumbai get a final chance to compete with each other in the celebration of the iconic Ganesh Chaturthi festival.
Two men who grew up in Mumbai's slums are drawn into the city's brutal narcotics trade, where they fight on opposite sides of the law.
A man and a woman struggling to keep their respective marriages afloat run into each other at a marriage counselor's office, with unexpected results.
Eleven high school classmates awaken, restrained to a large dining room. While fearing for their lives, they question a motive to this bizarre act.
Caught in a downward spiral of failed career moves, misguided ambitions and bad relations, a pair of lost souls find hope in an unexpected friendship.

Raised in working-class Mumbai, Manisha has an independent spirit that angers her father, who favors Manisha's medical student sister, Mini. Things reach a breaking point when Manisha's father beats her for accepting a modeling contract.
In this epic tale, a once-murderous sea captain is holed up in a monastery in retreat from the devil, whom the captain fears is coming for his soul.
A child whose innocence and devotion set him apart from the other children of his village grows up to be one of the foremost saints of India.
A change in the leadership of a political party sparks bitter conflict and the party's division into two rival factions.
Long past his heyday, a still-virile boxer tries to reconnect with his daughter as he confronts the onset of a terminal, degenerative neural disorder.
Newly orphaned Aram leaves Beirut to live with his grandfather in Los Angeles, and overwhelmed by culture shock, he falls prey to an Armenian gang.
After winning a shared trip to a soccer match, two colleagues who hold opposite world views find they're stuck traveling together for the duration.
After a new teacher arrives, students' dreams begin to come true. Class president Ye-rim must solve the nightmarish mystery before it's too late.
Celebrate the remarkable 40-year career of influential Canadian rockers Rush with this documentary, which details the band's formation and evolution.
A young woman's life gets a jump-start after she and a musical genius are both struck by the same falling star. But will the side effects derail love?

column4: The Fury of a Patient Man
column8: After his lover is killed in a jewelry store robbery, quiet José romances café owner Ana, who's unaware he has other motivations.
When the accidental death of a couple's young son sends them grieving in opposite directions, they're forced to re-examine their life and marriage.

column4: Stop at Nothing: The Lance Armstrong Story
column8: An athlete dupes the world with his tale of miraculous recovery from cancer, becoming a sports hero and beacon of hope, but can he outpace the truth?
In each episode of flirtations and fails, one real-life single navigates five blind dates. The mission: Find one match worthy of a second date.
Good girl Cam recruits her pot-loving bestie Jinky to help deliver a backpack full of weed for her drug-dealing fiancé.

column4: Ken Jeong: You Complete Me, Ho
column8: In his first-ever stand-up special, Ken Jeong pays tribute to his wife and shares stories about Hollywood and how "The Hangover" saved his life.
Chris Rock takes the stage in Brooklyn for a comedy special filled with searing observations on fatherhood, infidelity and American politics.
Individually, bank employees Sanjay and Karina don't earn enough to be able to buy a home, so they decide to enter into a marriage of convenience.
Brave people get onstage to read hilarious and humiliating tales of gawky teenage love, family dysfunction and other stories from their younger years.
When he's caught up in a deadly conspiracy, an unemployed greeting card writer must create the perfect card for a new holiday to save his skin.
Stand-up comic Katherine Ryan reminisces about unusual relationships, life in the hometown she hates and the time she enraged an entire nation.
Hoping to pump up their sound, a punk band hires Pepe, a keyboardist with Down Syndrome, but tensions erupt when he steals the show with his talent.
A coldhearted heiress, a man from her past and an ambitious new hire in her company all become entangled on a battleground for money and power.
After the death of their beloved mother, three foster sisters find their bond tested by old grudges, career tensions and a startling revelation.
In this fast-paced Indonesian thriller, a young martial arts master travels to Jakarta, where he saves an orphan from a human-trafficking ring.
This documentary explores the tensions between the lucrative big-game hunting business and wildlife conservation from a variety of perspectives.
The team behind the searing documentary reveals what inspired them to tell the story of Virunga and the lethal fight to save the gorillas' sanctuary.
In rural India, where the stigma of menstruation persists, women make low-cost sanitary pads on a new machine and stride toward financial independence.
Five shorts reveal a fictional Hong Kong in 2025, depicting a dystopian city where residents and activists face crackdowns under iron-fisted rule.
A middle-aged actress is cast in a film adaptation of the play that made her famous 20 years earlier, but in a much less glamorous role.
A trio of brothers cope with their parents' volatile relationship by running wild and unchecked, and one of them experiences a visceral awakening.
After a tough upbringing, natural-born fighter José Aldo confronts his personal demons in his quest to become an MMA champion in this sports biopic.
Years after taking up normal lives incognito, the cyborgs are forced to fight again when the superhuman Blessed appear with a plan for humanity.

column4: David Brent: Life on the Road
column8: With "The Office" long in the past, middling salesman David Brent ditches work and goes on tour with his rock band in a disastrous stab at stardom.
Outspoken comedian Beppe Grillo reminisces about his long career, including the triumphs and controversies that fueled his rise in Italian politics.
This documentary examines how Adolf Hitler's talent for manipulation, psychology and image-making led him from humble origins to near-world conquest.
This collection includes the acclaimed rock documentary about Metallica, plus a film checking in with the still-thriving group 10 years later.
A Google executive boldly attempts a death-defying mission to travel to space and free-fall back to Earth without a rocket.
Hip, irresponsible Londoner Will invents an imaginary son and starts attending single-parent meetings to find available women.
A young 17th-century witch time travels to the future to save the man she loves, but first must adjust to present-day Cartagena and defeat a dark rival.
A diverse crew of experts dive deep into the origin stories of mythological monsters before building replicas of the creatures using 3D CGI technology.
When a boy trades boxing school for ballet lessons, he may take his newfound talent all the way to the top - and win over his disapproving father.
Established during World War II, North America's first secret agent training school – known as Camp X – paved the way for present-day espionage.

column4: Cats & Dogs: The Revenge of Kitty Galore
column8: Cats and dogs must set aside their differences and merge animal instincts when Kitty Galore decides to claw her way to global domination.
A teen navigates a bitter feud between his willful mom and a free-spirited man, who's the lover and insurance beneficiary of his recently deceased dad.
This documentary investigates the surge in vaping culture and whether e-cigarettes can really help smokers kick the habit.
Love is in the air as Zoe and friends go on a quest to find a fabled Maid's Stone. But when rivalry blinds them to danger, it's Raven to the rescue!
When a teen and her family's hired servant turn up dead, inept police bungle the inquiry and wind up fingering a controversial prime suspect.
Interviews and dramatic reconstructions illuminate the twisted motivations and brazen crimes of serial killer and respected physician, Harold Shipman.
This documentary paints a candid picture of Australian street artist Anthony Lister as he navigates his burgeoning career and personal hardships.
Stories from spiritual leaders, physicians and those with chronic illnesses reveal the powerful connection between the human psyche and physical health.
In a far corner of the Pacific Ocean, people who live entirely at sea share insights into their incredible amphibious lifestyle.
When Superman and the other Justice League superheroes start disappearing, it's up to Batman to unravel the caper and save the day.

column4: Lego Friends: Girls on a Mission
column8: Five best friends put their teamwork, wits and courage to the test when they take on a mission to protect Heartlake City from bad people.

column4: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Black Panther
column8: When Thanos joins forces with villains Killmonger and Klaue to destroy Earth, Black Panther rushes to stop them from stealing Wakanda's vibranium.

column4: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Guardians of the Galaxy
column8: The Guardians are on a mission to deliver the Build Stone to the Avengers before the Ravagers, Thanos and his underlings steal it from them.

column4: LEGO Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu: Day of the Departed
column8: Cole finds himself trapped in Yang's temple after accidentally releasing a host of villainous spirits that the Ninja must defeat.

column4: Lo que la verdad esconde: El caso Asunta (Operacion Nenúfar)
column8: This true crime series investigates newfound evidence and unanswered questions in famous criminal cases, such as the murder of Asunta Basterra Porto.
After receiving a strange present, a professor and his pregnant wife are plagued by tragedy and a paranormal presence that's determined to kill.
Ink junkies dig skin deep and share personal stories about their collection of body art.
When his best friend is murdered by the shadowy Ozunu clan, Raizo, an orphan raised to be an assassin, vows revenge.
A team of modern-day adventurers follows the footsteps of the money-hungry explorers who trekked the Klondike in search of Canadian gold.
A psychic medium takes a job as personal shopper for a spoiled celebrity in order to contact the spirit of her brother, who owned her employer's home.
Nadia keeps dying and reliving her 36th birthday party. She's trapped in a surreal time loop – and staring down the barrel of her own mortality.
While investigating the mysterious death of a teacher, a grizzled detective gets caught up in the world of a high-stakes virtual reality game.

column4: Sword Art Online Alternative: Gun Gale Online
column8: College student Karen takes up Gun Gale Online and gets a reputation as the Pink Demon. Then her gaming buddy Pitohui asks her to join the Squad Jam.
Host Francesca Stavrakopoulou travels across the Middle East, offering extraordinary insights into the stories of the Old Testament.
In a global competition, eight fishing enthusiasts battle extreme conditions and dangerous waters to be crowned the ultimate angler.
This documentary follows British bomb disposal teams in Afghanistan and the dangers they face in their methodical lives on the front lines of war.
When Nadine's best (and only) friend starts dating her detested older brother, the teenage cynic's life becomes even more unbearable.

column4: The Story of Us with Morgan Freeman
column8: Explore the forces of love, belief, power, war, peace, rebellion and freedom in this series about the ties that bind – and destroy – humanity.
A disparate group of teenage girls discovers how to obtain supernatural abilities, but abusing their newfound power has disturbing consequences.
A taxi driver living in a Mumbai slum seeks to better his family's life by building an extension of his home while dealing with a lecherous contractor.
True and Bartleby try to cheer up the Rainbow Kingdom’s loneliest citizen, but his gloomy mood is contagious! Can a trio of wishes turn things around?
A feared critic, an icy gallery owner and an ambitious assistant snap up a recently deceased artist's stash of paintings – with dire consequences.
This wide-ranging documentary examines the behaviors considered in a diagnosis of psychopathy and includes nonviolent, successful figures in history.

column4: Why Are We Getting So Fat?
column8: A Cambridge geneticist dispels misconceptions about living with obesity and explores why the epidemic continues to expand across the UK and America.
From Moscow to Mexico City, three BBC journalists delve into the inner workings of some of the most burgeoning metropolises on Earth.
From a bubble-shaped palace to an island built on plastic bottles, tour the world’s most fantastically bizarre residences.
After launching a successful underground restaurant out of their apartment, an ambitious chef and his wife open an all-consuming upscale eatery.
Aiming to hasten an uprising, the leader of an underground rebellion dispatches acrobatic assassin Aeon Flux to eliminate the government's top leader.
Leonardo DiCaprio crisscrosses the globe to investigate the consequences of man-made globe warming and the measures being taken to reverse it.
Expelled from private school for attempted suicide, emo Ethan enters the world of Seymour High and meets a cute Christian who's ready to convert him.

column4: Gender Revolution: A Journey with Katie Couric
column8: Katie Couric explores our evolving understanding of gender identity, speaking with transgender and intersex individuals about their experiences.

column4: How the Beatles Changed the World
column8: Interviews and rare archival footage illuminate how the Beatles' influence over music and culture continues to be felt around the world.
At an initiation ritual for the young men of his Xhosa community, a closeted factory hand meets a Johannesburg teen who discovers his best-kept secret.
Iconic rocker John Mellencamp lights up Chicago in an electrifying live performance featuring old classics and new tracks.
Filmmakers explore how pop culture shapes a new generation's beliefs about gender, sexuality and violence on display among students on spring break.
Adopting a child's perspective, this show takes a humorous look at what happens during those action-packed 15 minutes of snack time each day.
Needing hard evidence to convict a company chairman of fraud, an investigator bargains with the company's tech expert to turn over his boss's ledger.
This comic documentary follows the Mortified movement, a series of stage events where adults share awkward childhood moments in front of strangers.
Narrated by Robert Redford, this documentary tours the awe-inspiring landscapes, historic sites and untamed wilderness of America's great parks.
Martin and Gabi try to form a relationship after meeting through a hookup app, but when boredom creeps in, they seek out an unconventional solution.
In the wake of a young artist’s suicide, his pianist mother and his despairing girlfriend square off in a living nightmare beset by guilt and blame.
Popular fairy tales take on a darkly comic edge in these short animated films based on a book by Roald Dahl and illustrator Quentin Blake.
In this three-part documentary series, host Marcus du Sautoy examines the mathematical code underlying all of life on Earth and the universe itself.
California residents and farmers face powerful barons in the struggle to secure water rights in this fresh historical account of profit and interests.
Inspired by the famous song "Contrabando y Traición," Camelia, a beautiful girl from San Antonio, kills her lover and becomes a legendary drug runner.
Related tales of a family seeking refuge and two men on a train to Amritsar evoke the dreadful unease surrounding Hindu-Sikh tensions in 1980s Punjab.
A young couple falls in love, but conflicting loyalties drive them apart. Years later, fate intervenes and hands them a second chance.
Two roaming Kenyan bandits attempt to change the course of their lives by exchanging their rifles for running shoes.
A revenge-seeking diamond thief gathers a ragtag crew to infiltrate a Dubai hotel hosting a dance contest. But first they have to learn how to dance.
A selfish, manipulative schoolteacher takes advantage of a schoolgirl's vulnerability to gratify his dark, narcissistic desires.
When its special ops agency is wiped out, Spain hastily assembles a new team to defuse a terrorist plot. But who are these scrappy would-be heroes?
Fiery passions take center stage in this intimate look at the Australian String Quartet and, perhaps more vital, the priceless instruments they guard.
A North Korean propagandist who escaped to Seoul now creates satirical art about Kim Jong Il's regime and copes with repercussions of his defection.
After a weekend fling with artist Victor, Veronica, a psychiatrist and politician's wife, becomes the target of Victor's dangerous romantic obsession.
Three best buddies are thrown into a wild chase for a priceless painting that was stolen from a house they used to throw a huge party.
When his wife goes missing, university professor Saurabh remains at home while the police investigate, but his grip on reality loosens as days pass.
Young fashion designers vie for the chance to become Mexico's next big talent by competing before judges in grueling tests of creativity and stamina.
This Sundance prize-winning documentary is an intimate portrait of 1980s Harlem drag balls: a world of fierce competition, sustenance, and survival.
This newly preserved collection features more than 20 films made by groundbreaking African American directors for black audiences from 1915 to 1946.
Featuring legendary and up-and-coming MMA fighters, this documentary details the history of the brutal sport and the fighters' struggles and triumphs.
Years after they were childhood sweethearts, Manuela and Olmo share a night in Madrid, where they discuss their past and the possibility of a future.
A girl discovers a dog-training app that can get boys to obey her every command. But she soon learns that it isn't the cure-all she had hoped for.
Fairy tales get a funny twist when Masha retells them, because she tends to get the details just a little jumbled up in this animated kids' series.
Exonerated in the murder of her father and stepmother, Lizzie Borden takes on crime lords, detectives and other foes as she savors her new infamy.
M'Dear and her sisters struggle to keep their singing act together before a church Christmas pageant while Grandpa teaches the kids a valuable lesson.
As danger stalks the world outside his isolated home, an overprotective father faces a tough decision when another family shows up seeking help.
After his ailing father makes a shocking confession, a desperately depressed man sets out to find the woman he believes will change his destiny.
This documentary series reconstructs history's most complex, high-stakes hostage negotiations as kidnapping victims recount their terrifying ordeals.
As Havana slowly revolves through the year, wistful detective Mario Conde probes the sultry heart of the city to investigate dark and deadly crimes.
Pop music superstar Mariah Carey hosts this all-star holiday celebration with special guests and a celebrity reading of "The Night Before Christmas."
When an otherworldly force wreaks havoc on a war-torn European city, an engineer teams up with an elite Special Ops unit to stop it.
Kari Byron, Tory Belleci and Grant Imahara rank history's greatest inventions, heists and more in this series from the producers of "MythBusters."

column4: Trailer Park Boys: Drunk, High and Unemployed: Live in Austin
column8: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles bring their trailer park humor out onto the stage for a night of bravado, schemes and an intoxicated acting demo.
A low-level intelligence agent gets pulled into action and espionage above his pay grade when he's ordered to assist a trigger-happy senior agent.
In a fictional megalopolis, a stunning underworld theft triggers a fierce power struggle among the gangsters, with an enigmatic cop on their trail.
After losing a World Cup bet, two hapless buddies must use their wits to pay off their debt to a big Jakarta bookie in this action-packed comedy.
Crunch Calhoun, a daredevil motorcyclist and mostly reformed con artist, agrees to do one last job: helping his brother Nicky steal a priceless book.
Orphaned by a tragedy that took the lives of her parents, Srintil grows up in a poor Indonesian village aspiring to be a sacred dancer.
Between divorce, bad relationships and coming out as gay, a group of affluent friends realize that none of their lives are as easy as they seem.
A popular high school girl strains her relationship with her close-knit clique when she begins falling for a reclusive, lower-class schoolmate.
Three flatmates get involved in the shady business belonging to one roomie's fiancé, and discover that a global crime syndicate is gunning for them.
In this intimate drama, circumstances draw together four people from different castes – which would normally preclude them from forming friendships.
Stuck in a liquor store during an alleged robbery, a group of strangers shares hidden truths and forms an unexpected bond on Christmas Eve.
When a mysterious woman hires Shankar to spy on a family, he must determine how his own father's abandonment figures into the situation.
Soft-spoken Jai and spitfire beauty Aditi couldn't be more different – but their family and friends know that they're a perfect match.
In 1890s India, an arrogant British commander challenges the harshly taxed residents of Champaner to a high-stakes cricket match.
After witnessing a murder, a meek family man must summon his courage when he finds himself on the wrong side of a notorious gangster.
Two indigent farmers consider suicide so that their families can collect a government subsidy that's paid to the relatives of deceased farmers.
When Shankar, who performs on the road with partner Chanchal and elephant Appu, falls for a Russian circus performer, jealousies and conflicts arise.
When daydreamer Ishaan is sent to boarding school, an unconventional art teacher tries to help the imaginative student discover his true identity.
The ordered life of a Reykjavik heart surgeon unravels when his daughter descends into a life of drugs and crime thanks to a sinister boyfriend.
After a skilled fighter falls in the ring, his younger brother emerges from the shadows to train and get revenge against a brutal champion.
A quirk of fate sends an ordinary, sweet-natured high school girl and her father into the home of the school genius, on whom she has a huge crush.
After a bad breakup, a struggling New York comedy writer tries to don a brave face and care for his dying mother in Sacramento.
This documentary series recounts the tumultuous history of Cuba, a nation of foreign conquest, freedom fighters and Cold War political machinations.
Work problems are piling up for a businessman. But when he discovers a pathway to his daughter's imaginary world, he starts finding some solutions.
As controversy surrounds the evangelical church he helped found, Edir Macedo must juggle betrayals, politics and personal loss in this biopic sequel.
When the Italian prime minister meets his lover and political rival while on an official trip to Budapest during Christmas week, things go topsy-turvy.
Two cops investigate the murder of a famous Turkish-German soccer player, but one of them has underworld connections that mire the case in controversy.
To prove a point about measuring up and fitting in, Texas teen Willowdean Dickson enters a local pageant run by her ex-beauty queen mom.

column4: Free Rein: The Twelve Neighs of Christmas
column8: As Bright Fields preps for its Mistletoe Ball, a broken ornament leads Zoe to a family secret, while Gaby finds herself at the mercy of new boss Mia.
An orphaned boy raised by animals in the jungle seizes his destiny while confronting a dangerous enemy – and his own human origins.
At top-secret U.S.-Australian joint defense facility Pine Gap, fissures appear in the critical alliance as spies work with, and against, each other.

column4: ReMastered: Who Killed Jam Master Jay?
column8: Run-DMC DJ Jam Master Jay made a huge impact in music and his community. But friends and family still seek closure years after his unsolved murder.

column4: Super Monsters and the Wish Star
column8: Christmas wishes come true for Lobo, whose favorite cousin arrives for a surprise visit, and for Glorb, who wishes he could be everywhere at once!
Social media stars Paris Hilton, Josh Ostrovsky, Brittany Furlan and Kirill Bichutsky hustle to build online empires – and face the pitfalls of fame.
An assembly of writers, philosophers and scientists share The Secret, which reputedly brought success to Plato, da Vinci, Einstein and other greats.
With unique individual perspectives that converge into a unified voice, sketch comedy group Astronomy Club delivers a smart and absurd brand of humor.
Searching for a soul mate, a ghost negotiates with God for three more days on Earth to find love, then meets a woman in need of help herself.
A successful actress with an abusive husband confides in friends who have troubling relationship issues of their own.
In this competition show, aspiring makeup artists navigate colorful challenges to win a career-making opportunity in the beauty industry.
Academy Award-nominated filmmaker Noah Baumbach directs this incisive and compassionate look at a marriage coming apart and a family staying together.
In ancient Disboard, a young warrior befriends an ex machina and embarks on a harrowing mission to stop a global war and save humanity from extinction.
Desperate to leave a life of prostitution, a teenage mother attempts to outsmart her ruthless boss who is determined to keep his prized asset.

column4: Spirit Riding Free: Spirit of Christmas
column8: Lucky and friends must figure out how to get home in time for Christmas when a falling boulder – and a serious snowstorm – derail their travel plans.
Teased constantly by classmate Takagi-san, middle-schooler Nishikata swears payback by trying (and failing) to give her a dose of her own medicine.
Henry Lee Lucas rose to infamy when he confessed to hundreds of unsolved murders. This docuseries examines the truth – and horrifying consequences.
Johnny Depp stars in this adaptation of Hunter S. Thompson's novel about a boozy journalist who moves to Puerto Rico and falls for a taken woman.
Four sisters deal with family drama and secrets throughout three different time periods, all occurring on Christmas Day.
After jostling her way into a gig as a celebrity bodyguard, the boisterous daughter of a powerful triad boss shakes up a TV star's life and finds love.
Searching for a fresh start, a nurse practitioner moves from LA to a remote northern California town and is surprised by what – and who – she finds.
A group of local women band together to save a terrified young girl from marriage, launching a hilarious strike against their frustrated husbands.
After a woman is severely beaten at home, her strong-willed friends take a stand against their husbands to seek justice for domestic abuse victims.
A boozy ex-cop turned hit man thinks he's losing his marbles when a cartoon unicorn only he can see urges him to rescue a girl kidnapped by Santa.
Traditional girl Pie is initially uncomfortable with her tomboyish new roommate. But as time goes on, she finds herself increasingly attracted to her.
When Queen Poppy realizes that Bridget and the Bergens don't have any holidays, she hatches a plan for Branch and the Snack Pack to help create one.
Two former high school sweethearts unexpectedly reunite in their old hometown, where they rediscover their magical bond and face a shared regret.
Follow the journey of Satnam Singh Bhamara as he works to fulfill his dream of becoming the first India-born player to be drafted into the NBA.
The comic innovator delivers a surreal set blending experimental songs, jokes about grits, guns and drugs, and other improvised comedy adventures.
Danish teen Emma moves to Paris hoping to become a top model, but her dreams soon unravel when her affair with photographer Shane turns obsessive.

column4: A Christmas Prince: The Royal Baby
column8: Christmas brings the ultimate gift to Aldovia: a royal baby. But first, Queen Amber must save her family and kingdom by unwrapping a monarchy mystery.
Tired of the constant comments on her relationship status, perpetually single Johanne starts a 24-day hunt for a boyfriend to bring home for Christmas.
Join director Martin Scorsese as he sits down with stars Robert De Niro, Al Pacino and Joe Pesci for an intimate, intriguing look inside "The Irishman."
A fast-spreading disease that turns victims into blood-sucking fiends pits two best friends against each other in a fight for humanity's future.
In mid-1970s Australia, two small-town teenage boys befriend an enigmatic middle-aged surfer, who urges them to see the thrill in facing their fears.
Spirited sister-brother duo Cleo and Cuquín try on different professions each day to help their other siblings solve problems and enjoy new adventures.
After 15 years behind bars, a kindhearted ex-drug dealer returns to Brooklyn looking for a fresh start, only to discover things have changed. A lot.
Cheeky comic Craig Ferguson keeps it casual as he discusses '70s porn, Japanese toilets and his mildly crime-filled days as a talk show host.
Two tech-savvy teens plot to fool a cranky old neighbor into believing his house is haunted, but their cruel prank soon takes some unexpected turns.

column4: Bill Burr: I'm Sorry You Feel That Way
column8: Bill Burr escapes the zombie apocalypse, explores how rom-coms ruin great sex and explains how too many childhood hugs may be the downfall of man.
After his crew breaks up, a gifted but insecure hip-hop dancer teaches at a top ballet school in Paris, where he falls for an aspiring ballerina.

column4: The Prince of Tennis ~ Match! Tennis Juniors ~
column8: A tennis whiz beats the odds to excel on the court while juggling school and inspiring teammates. Based on the hit manga series by Takeshi Konomi.
After an argument with her dad, a young woman from a family of macho truck drivers is kicked out of the home and must make her own success as a trucker.

column4: God's Not Dead: A Light in Darkness
column8: After a fire breaks out at his church, a pastor faces a legal battle against university leaders who wish to push the congregation off the campus.
Russell Brand gets loquacious in London as he ruminates on the state of the world and marvels over how his life changed the moment he became a father.
When a German baker travels to Jerusalem in search of his dead male lover’s family, his growing involvement with them may expose his truth.
When he defies his cruel father and leaves New Caledonia to play rugby in France, young Soane learns hard lessons about life, love and success.
Bill Murray rounds up an all-star cast for an evening of music, mischief and barroom camaraderie in this irreverent twist on holiday variety shows.
A reporter interviews three convicts on death row for a documentary but as their stories emerge, so do her own true motivations for soliciting them.
The decision by India's supreme court to establish caste-based reservations for jobs in education causes conflict between a teacher and his mentor.
After losing their first child in an accident, a couple moves to a palatial home, where their young daughter comes under the spell of an eerie spirit.
A family’s harmonious existence is interrupted when the young son begins showing symptoms of anxiety that seem linked to disturbing events at home.
Stood up by her groom at the altar, a young woman finds help and healing from another man – until her ex-fiancé returns, hoping to win her back.

column4: Albert Pinto Ko Gussa Kyun Aata Hai?
column8: As the police investigate his disappearance, a young man heads to Goa to carry out an act of vengeance fueled by years of pent-up anger toward society.

Abandoned in a park by their father, Amar, Akbar and Anthony grow up independently and have no knowledge of one another. They're reunited as adults when, by coincidence, they all give blood at the same hospital.
Seeking refuge in a Hindu temple after the tragic death of the girl he loved, a Muslim youth is caught by the police, who mistake him for an enemy.
Twenty years after their debut, join the beloved members of Arashi on a new journey as they showcase their lives, talents and gifts to the world.
After futile attempts to better their lives with honest work, three broke friends opt for a more dubious means of making money: kidnapping for ransom.
A dysfunctional middle-class family is transformed by the attentions of their talented new chef – until he vanishes along with their valuable jewels.
A young man challenges traditional customs by standing up to the father of the woman he loves, who has promised her to a wealthy expatriate.
A rookie lawyer with an emasculating past in baseball can break into the legal world only if he manages a law firm's ragtag company softball team.
A theater group lands in trouble when its new actress takes her own life, two of its members are framed for murder and no one is who they appear to be.
