After a couple moves into an apartment, the wife’s increasingly disturbing behavior unravels chilling secrets about their new home’s past.
Raj, the son of strict, wealthy parents, falls in love with Bobby, the daughter of a poor Christian fisherman – a romance his parents oppose.
This remake of the classic 1976 horror flick finds misfit Carrie getting revenge on all the cool people who've bullied her over the years.
When a secretary saves her tycoon boss's life, his family hears wedding bells. Problem is, she's already in love – with his younger brother.
When a rash of murders unfolds, 6-year-old Andy knows that his toy doll Chucky is the killer, but neither his mom nor the cops believe him.
Jealous of the high regard in which his new wife holds their brother-in-law, a botany professor stages an elaborate prank that will even the score.
A surgeon’s perfect life is rattled when his daughter is taken hostage in their own home and he's given 24 hours to pay a hefty ransom.
Tipped off about buried money in Goa, four ne’er-do-well friends go on the hunt, chased by a police officer who wants the treasure for himself.
Pierce Brosnan's final outing as 007 finds James Bond facing off against a North Korean terrorist who's in league with a British diamond merchant.
A man who's a lookalike for a slain mob kingpin is asked by the police to impersonate the gangster and infiltrate his underworld organization.
After accidentally killing a young mobster, a guilt-stricken police officer searches for the parents who never came forward to claim their son's body.
Framed for his older brother's murder, a boxer seeks violent revenge against the true killer who's torn his family apart.
Giving up his life of crime for love, a gangster struggles with a moral dilemma when tragic events and enduring enemies take him back to the underworld.
When circumstances at work compel Ram to pretend to have a twin, his lie works – until the boss wants his daughter to marry Ram’s fictitious brother.
Pierce Brosnan takes his first turn as debonair secret agent James Bond, who investigates the destruction of a Russian satellite weapons base.
Between thwarting crooks and wooing the belle next door, four pranksters get in over their heads when they bamboozle their way into a couple’s bungalow.
In this stylish comedy, a mother-daughter con team makes money the old-fashioned way: They use their feminine wiles to swindle it.
The bond between two crooks and best friends is threatened when one learns that the other's father had a hand in his own tragic past.
When a pair of friends uncover a weed Bible, their magical stash gets stolen, sending them on a pot-fueled quest through Atlanta to find it.

column4: Jaan-E-Mann: Let's Fall in Love... Again
column8: To avoid alimony payments, an aspiring actor schemes for his ex-wife to marry an unlikely suitor, but soon realizes he may not be ready to lose her.
Incarcerated for a crime he didn’t commit, a young man must navigate the crowded, cut-throat environment of prison as he awaits trial.

column4: Jis Desh Men Ganga Behti Hai
column8: Falling in with a band of outlaws during a holy pilgrimage, a country boy tries to change their violent ways ahead of a showdown with the authorities.
A bank manager and his wife, still grieving over their daughter who died in a fire, become pawns in a bank heist with ties to corruption and fraud.
Separated at birth, a pair of identical twins unexpectedly reunite as adults and embark on a madcap mission to take down a common enemy from their past.
Jailed for robbing his brother’s unscrupulous employer, a simpleton has a transformation while in prison, emerging with a violent mission for revenge.
Secretly in love with his neighbor, a mild-mannered clerk is heartbroken when his much bolder, more charming friend wins her heart instead.
A strict matriarch's regimented household is upended by the arrival of a spunky relative who challenges the rules.
A speech and hearing-impaired couple persists through unforgiving obstacles to be accepted by society and live a life of dignity.

column4: Kuldip Patwal: I Didn't Do It!
column8: Accused of killing a politician, a local grocer’s fight to prove his innocence reveals his lifelong struggles with injustice leading up to the incident.
After lying to his girlfriend, orthopedic surgeon Samir must conjure up a pretend wife in this musical comedy.
A loving husband and father's joyful family life is rocked to its core upon the discovery that he has a young son borne from a past extramarital affair.
Samir must overcome a hostile horoscope, a hot temper and a determined rival to win the heart of Rani, the love of his life.

column8: It's Christmas, and BoJack wants nothing to do with it. Then Todd shows up with a giant candy cane and an old "Horsin' Around" Christmas episode.

column4: Don't F**k with Cats: Hunting an Internet Killer
column8: A twisted criminal's gruesome videos drive a group of amateur online sleuths to launch a risky manhunt that pulls them into a dark underworld.
Love, loss and transformative luck intersect in this musical drama about two struggling artists experiencing life at full volume in Los Angeles.
In her first special since 2003, Ellen revisits her road to stardom and details the heartfelt – and hilarious – lessons she's learned along the way.
In a dystopian, near-future United States, a deportation caseworker who has begun to question authority tries to safeguard a woman and her young son.
A one-eyed boy and plus-sized girl form a deep connection. But following a brief separation, they reunite as different people.

column4: Mike Epps: Don't Take It Personal
column8: Mike Epps tears up the stage at L.A.'s historic Orpheum Theatre in a special packed with blistering impressions and unapologetically raunchy swagger.
Amid an avalanche of stars, Pee-wee straps on his ice skates and glides into the holiday season with Christmas cards, carols ... and Charo.

column4: Ronny Chieng: Asian Comedian Destroys America!
column8: Ronny Chieng ("The Daily Show," "Crazy Rich Asians") takes center stage in this stand-up special and riffs on modern American life and more.
A woman who's about to give birth finds her maternal instincts kicking in when she's abducted, imprisoned and brutalized by a vicious gang.

column4: Prince of Peoria: A Christmas Moose Miracle
column8: Teddy's never missed the Festival of Lights, but the bowling alley’s been snowed in! Not to worry – Emil insists the Christmas moose will save the day.
A New Jersey detective whose family was killed by an international gangster teams up with a Bangkok cop on a quest to bring down a criminal empire.
An overly eager elf improves Santa's sleigh, but when he crash lands far from home, three odd critters pitch in to send him back to the North Pole.

column4: My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks
column8: Rainbow Dash, Applejack, Pinkie Pie, Rarity and Fluttershy plan to perform with their new band at the Canterlot High musical showcase.
After leaving Iowa with stars in her eyes, Ali arrives at a Los Angeles burlesque lounge with dreams of taking the stage with her soaring voice.
Eleven emerging Bangladeshi filmmakers present a collection of gritty shorts centered on the capital city and the people living in its margins.
In 1920s Denmark, married artists embark on a journey of unconditional love when the husband announces his intentions to live life as a woman.
With interviews from experts on both sides of the debate, this film questions the routine practice of non-religious infant circumcision in the U.S.
A visually impaired pianist’s world careens into a series of shocking twists after he unintentionally lands at the murder scene of a former film star.
Hidden away by her mother, the Floral Goddess, the naïve Jinmi is drawn to Xufeng, the Heavenly Emperor's son. Yet forces conspire against them.

column4: Dragons: Dawn of the Dragon Racers
column8: The "How to Train Your Dragon" adventure continues when a hunt for lost sheep turns into a fierce, fun-filled competition.
Join your DreamWorks friends for these four holiday specials, featuring Shrek and Donkey, Hiccup and Toothless, and the wacky animals from Madagascar.
In the 1980s, a crusading journalist uncovers secret CIA funding for Nicaraguan rebels, but the powers that be silence his investigation.
A showbiz family revolving around its teen celebrity son desperately tries to hang on to fame and success in this savage satire of Hollywood.
After a brief college romance, Emma and Dexter pursue separate dreams, but meet on the same day each year to compare their progress in life and love.
Bruce Springsteen shares personal stories from his life and acoustic versions of some of his best-known songs in an intimate one-man show.
As his esteem grows in the world of physics, Stephen Hawking's body is ravaged by ALS, forcing his increasing dependence on his devoted wife, Jane.
A maverick leader and a clever young general take on Japanese pirates amid bureaucratic intrigue in Ming Dynasty China.
Six teenage groms come together one summer to share a dream: to work at the world-renowned Surfer's Paradise Resort on the legendary Sunset Island.
A young Barack Obama forges his identity while dealing with race, divergent cultures and ordinary life as a New York City college student.
On his path to becoming Pope Francis, Father Jorge Bergoglio pursues his religious vocation in a country ravaged by a brutal military dictatorship.
Bowling alley worker Amy and nonconformist Raquel kick some serious demon butt while also facing their inner demons as they navigate their early 20s.
Explore the icky world of rats and witness how their talent for surviving in almost any environment has led to catastrophic events throughout history.
After years of estrangement, four sisters gather in the wake of their mother's death, which may or may not have been a suicide.
American journalist Theo Padnos retraces the Middle Eastern journey that led to his 2012 kidnapping and brutal torture by an al-Qaida faction.
A ruthless corporate headhunter battles his rival for a promotion while dealing with a family crisis that threatens to derail his career.
Sent on the same deadly international mission by their rival religious factions, two men's madcap antics along the way take them hilariously off course.
Catching the eye of a wealthy gentleman, spunky Ha-won gets hired to live with his three immature grandsons so she can whip them into shape.
A paragliding mishap drops a South Korean heiress in North Korea – and into the life of an army officer, who decides he will help her hide.
For a group of charismatic undergraduates, the jolting revelations from a campus blog turn surviving university life into a serious matter.
Inseparable childhood friends Akash, Sameer and Siddharth are just out of college. Nothing comes between them – until they each fall in love.
While hosting a shipboard holiday for relatives and friends, a wealthy but dysfunctional family must face the ugly truths under their flawless facade.
A ruthless crime boss and drug lord is nabbed and held captive by the authorities, who send his naïve look-alike to infiltrate the man's gang.
With Asia under his complete control, criminal mastermind Don turns to Europe, battling the mob bosses of each nation along the way.
Four young male friends tackle the challenges and unexpected catastrophes of growing up clueless in this music-packed Bollywood teen drama.
A tycoon accuses three strangers of killing his daughter but mysteriously dies before he can expose them, sparking a tangled hunt for the real culprit.
Miho Nishizumi tries to escape her family's tradition of tankery by enrolling at a new high school. Instead she gets back into the sport with friends.
With a short life expectancy, a young girl uses faith and her vivid imagination to navigate adversity and create a story that impacts all around her.
This offbeat comedy-drama follows six quirky newlywed couples as they set off on a bus from Mumbai to Goa on their honeymoons.
The remarkable true story of Gift Ngoepe, the first African to play for Major League Baseball, is recounted in this inspiring documentary.
Single at 34, Isoken is maneuvered by her mother toward a relationship with a black entrepreneur but finds herself drawn to a white photojournalist.
Unlucky in love and bullied at work, an office drone is resigned to his dead-end life until it’s transformed by mysterious calls from … himself.
After dropping out of the army, a spoiled teenager reenlists and proves his mettle by becoming an officer just as war breaks out.
When Vikram gets tapped to play the male lead in a Bollywood film, he can't believe his luck. But it may ruin his relationship with his girlfriend.
A divorced couple decides to continue sharing a home but their already-delicate cohabiting scheme unravels when they begin dating other people.
Four friends hoped that their rock band would be a hit. After breaking up, the band members reunite and take another shot at fulfilling their dream.
When Daphne's TV show does a segment on real monsters, the gang fires up the Mystery Machine and heads to Moonscar Island, where zombies await.
Aliens fleeing their planet land on Earth, pose as teenagers and fight off mutant space monsters by joining forces to become a powerful giant robot.
Set in the jumbled landscape of Mumbai, this mystery drama centers on a police inspector who's trying to cope with the collapse of his marriage.

column4: Tom and Jerry: The Magic Ring
column8: When a young wizard leaves Tom to guard his priceless magic ring, Jerry gets the ring stuck on his head, igniting a series of slapstick antics.
New filmmaker Téo Frank travels the U.S. to create this documentary about underground hip-hop artists doing exceptional work outside the music industry.
Three friends on an adventurous road trip/bachelor party in Spain learn some lessons about themselves and each other that will change them forever.
Spine-chilling stories of malevolent spirits unfold in villages, jungles and haunted buildings across India.
Two pairs of contestants go head-to-head for several rounds, deciphering puzzles and messages comprised of emojis for a chance at a $10,000 prize.
Venturing into the woods, high schooler James discovers an intelligent robot that he must save from the hands of a businessman with an evil scheme.
Comedian Ben Gleib hosts this game show in which teams of two compete to solve increasingly tough brain teasers. Faster answers mean more money.
When a tour guide in Japan goes blind after seeing her fiancé’s infidelity, she befriends a fellow Filipino keen to coax her out of the darkness.
In this game show hosted by Olympian Apolo Anton Ohno, contestants compete by completing 60-second challenges using common household items.

column4: Once in a Lifetime Sessions with George Ezra
column8: English singer-songwriter George Ezra performs his standout songs and speaks about his transformation from aspiring bassist to pop star.

column4: Once in a Lifetime Sessions with Kasabian
column8: Between shots of live performances, Tom Meighan and Sergio Pizzorno of the English rock band talk about the 20-plus years of making music together.

column4: Once in a Lifetime Sessions with OneRepublic
column8: Exclusive interviews, live performances and studio recording sessions offer an intimate look at how OneRepublic became the successful band it is today.

column4: Once in a Lifetime Sessions with Snow Patrol
column8: In addition to concert scenes and studio recording sessions, this documentary presents exclusive interviews of the five men from the Irish rock band.
An eclectic group of fans of 1966's "The Good, the Bad and the Ugly" attempt to restore the cemetery set in Spain where the movie's climax was filmed.
In each episode of this "Skin Wars" spinoff hosted by RuPaul, talented artists from various fields compete in body art for the first time.
Britain's most ineffective but caring teacher takes his class to Cornwall for one last school trip, where anything could happen –
Not Provided
Shyam wakes to discover he's suspected in a murder that one journalist believes may have ties to a mysterious gangster.
Actor Donald Faison hosts this game show in which contestants must arrange numerical-based trivia tidbits from largest to smallest for various prizes.
An architect and his wife move into a castle that is slated to become a luxury hotel. But something inside is determined to stop the renovation.
In the wake of Jesus Christ's crucifixion, his apostles dedicate themselves to spreading his message, risking their freedom and their lives.
In this anime adventure series for kids, the forces of good and evil "blade it out," battling each other with enchanted spinning tops.
A Grim Reaper, a detective and a woman who foresees death get ensnared in matters of life and death – and dark mysteries of twenty years past.
Menaced by a psychopath who's got the local cops scared, waitress Lillian turns to a mysterious old logger to help her turn the tables on her stalker.
Small-town residents mistake an Orson Welles radio broadcast for news about an alien invasion and are emboldened to act as they await an apocalypse.
One filmmaker’s quest to expose the human rights violations faced by India’s LGBTQ community was a project of passion seven years in the making.
Writer and stand-up comedian Cheuk Wan-chi cracks wise at the follies of single womanhood and takes on politics in Hong Kong with nuance and flair.
To inherit her father's company, socialite Ellen must first visit his small hometown, where she learns the value of hard work and helping others.
In this Bangla thriller inspired by a true story, the discovery of a charred corpse in the woods leads to a high-profile murder investigation.
Follow Todd Standing, Dr. Jeff Meldrum and other researchers into the wilderness, where they try to capture definitive proof of Sasquatch's existence.
After finding his mom killed, Satoru's time-traveling ability takes him back 18 years for a chance to prevent her death and those of three classmates.
Take in the true account of drug kingpin "Freeway" Rick Ross's empire and how the CIA helped him fuel America's  devastating crack cocaine epidemic.
A Punjabi woman who works on a farm must endure the difficulties of living in an oppressive class-based society and a dysfunctional community.
In this Hindi version of the Tamil blockbuster, a Tamil gang leader in Kuala Lumpur seeks justice for crimes committed against him and his family.
This documentary pays tribute to the young cadets who gave their lives to defend Mexico against U.S. forces during the battle of Chapultepec Castle.
Four stories by writer Sadaat Hasan Manto culminate in a single gruesome drama that's set during the partitioning of the Indian subcontinent.
An Indian business owner struggles to keep his company afloat amid global competition while trying to make up for lost time with his family.
A young man and his parents ponder the reasons behind the recent breakdown of a relationship he was in – and the possibility of reconciliation.
A man's drunken romp in a gorilla suit gets him mistaken for Bigfoot, drawing media attention and tourist dollars to his struggling small town.
A heartbroken wildlife photographer throws himself into his work, only to find himself experiencing strange transformations.
Teens of Korean descent who were born and raised in other countries travel to Seoul to learn about their cultural heritage at a summer camp in 1986.
Passions flare and alliances form when neighbors Ana and Miguel each start an affair with former lovers, right under their spouses' noses.
Six fearless surfers travel to the north coast of Iceland to ride waves unlike anything they've ever experienced, captured with high-tech cameras.
In this genre-bending tale, Errol Morris explores the mysterious death of a U.S. scientist entangled in a secret Cold War program known as MK-Ultra.
The lives of three dissatisfied brothers running a family bridal shop turn topsy-turvy when one of them has to care for his ex-girlfriend's baby.
When a huge marijuana shipment falls prey to thieves, the aftermath touches players from all ranks of the drug trade between Morocco and Europe.
Two women at a cosmetics company compete for love and success. One uses her brain and diligence, while the other works her beauty and charm.
British strongman Eddie Hall wants to be the strongest man in the world. This documentary reveals the grueling life choices that fuel his obsession.
Follow an 11-year-old boy as he goes from ordinary child to colorful competitor in his quest for a big win at India’s biggest kite-flying festival.
A couple’s five-year marriage is put on the line when each of their first loves comes back hoping for another shot at romance.
This relatable relationship drama explores the real-life trials and joys of married life through the lens of 11 different wives.
When her husband goes to jail for bankruptcy, a woman takes her two daughters to live with her father, who severed ties with her years ago.
To fulfill her mother's dying wish, middle-class Khirad marries elite Ashar. But those who disapprove plot to turn Ashar against his wife.
The Ice Tribe prince journeys to a sacred mountain to vanquish evil but soon finds himself at war with the Fire Tribe, led by his long-lost brother.
Two renowned culinary families led by legendary food icons battle for the position of greatest chef, while protecting their secret kimchee recipes.
Seung Yeon decides to chase her dream of becoming a K-pop star and audition for a popular group. There's only one catch: It's a boy band.
When a gifted patissier with a gloomy past meets a bright and easygoing café owner, he begins to shed his thorns and learns to love again.
An arranged engagement between a village girl and her city cousin shows signs of true love, but an indiscretion decades ago could doom their romance.
When a Bedouin patriarch takes a second bride, his first wife chafes against her changing status while his daughter chases her own dreams of autonomy.
Strong-willed, middle-class Kashaf and carefree, wealthy Zaroon meet in college, but before love can take root, they each have some growing up to do.
Comic book artist Emma draws her ideal man: Edward, the director of a film about a novelist named Michelle, who's writing a book about Emma.
Real events are dramatized in the unthinkable story of a resilient teenager held prisoner by a seasoned predator on a remote farm in the 1980s.
The Tomorrowland music festival marks its 10th anniversary in Belgium, the U.S. and Brazil, with all the diverse excitement of the annual event.
During the Japanese colonial period, married playwright Kim U-jin falls in love with soprano Yun Sim-deok, one of Korea’s notable New Women.
Exposing a rarely seen perspective on the drug wars, ex-Special Forces commando Jason Fox interviews dangerous traffickers and cartel members.
Director Alfonso Cuarón delivers a vivid, emotional portrait of domestic life and social hierarchy set against Mexico's political turmoil of the 1970s.
The Biblical story of Samson becomes this sword-and-sandals epic about an Israelite warrior whose God-given brawn is undone by a beautiful temptress.
This docuseries follows English soccer club Sunderland through the 2017-18 season as they try to bounce back after relegation from the Premier League.
Comedians Jimmy Carr, D.L. Hughley and Katherine Ryan tackle the world's woes with help from a rotating crew of funny guests and an actual expert.
This documentary adaptation of John Grisham's only nonfiction book raises troubling questions about two murder cases in Ada, Oklahoma, in the 1980s.
Ex-con Cal McTeer's return to her hometown of Orphelin Bay blows the lid off a generations-long conspiracy of silence around murder, drugs and Sirens.
This revealing documentary explores how the high-stakes world of Amateur Athletic Union basketball has professionalized youth sports in America.
After faking his death, a tech billionaire recruits a team of international operatives for a bold and bloody mission to take down a brutal dictator.
A newly engaged couple's romantic vacation in Jamaica turns into a mischievous adventure that tests their union in wild and unexpected ways.
When a couple leaning toward divorce meets with a pastor for counseling, an unexpected development shakes up their marriage.
An unapologetic lothario sets out to seduce three ex-flames – but gets an unexpected education in love along the way.
Engrossed in her career, a young woman reluctantly yields to her father's plan to set her up on 10 dates to find a suitable husband.
Haunted by nightmares and her father's disappearance, Heather goes on the hunt for him – and discovers a disturbing truth about her own identity.
An idealistic cop joins an underground police unit and battles ghoulish forces threatening the balance between the human and the supernatural realms.
After his father passes, the heir to a retail empire returns to take over the family business but faces a controversy involving laundering and murder.
In the wake of World War II, 11 Allied judges are tasked with weighing the fates of Japanese war criminals in a tense international trial.

column4: Jack Whitehall: Christmas with My Father
column8: Jack Whitehall invites his notoriously stuffy father onstage in London's West End for a Christmas comedy extravaganza, complete with celebrity guests.
To pay for an epic blunder, three yakuza brothers are forced to alter their bodies, form a girl group and break into the underground J-Pop idol scene.
In this documentary short, a diverse group of men and women discuss their personal journeys as they prepare for the U.S. citizenship test.
Judd Apatow returns to stand-up comedy after 25 years, riffing on living with three women, amusing moments from his career and much more.
Comedians Steve Coogan and Rob Brydon gorge on local delicacies and celebrity impressions as they reunite for a hilarious road trip through Spain.
A guilt-ridden doctor in a Belgian town tries to uncover the identity of a woman who died after being turned away from her office.
As viceroy Lord Mountbatten arrives in Delhi to oversee a transfer of power from Britain to India in 1947, war looms between religious factions.
This fascinating documentary examines the life of performing killer whale Tilikum, who has caused the deaths of several people while in captivity.
The expressive Ricardo O'Farrill uses his astute comedic sensibilities to tease Christmas traditions, and not even Santa Claus escapes unscathed.
When Santa gets arrested for trespassing after crashing his sleigh, it's up to a father-son team to spring him from jail and save Christmas.
They are fiercely competitive athletes, determined to become champions on one of the world's toughest golf courses. And they're still in grade school.
After succumbing to her terminal illness, a teenager posthumously narrates her parents’ tenacious relationship in this drama based on a true story.
After witnessing an assassin's slaughter, a young girl holes up in a farmhouse with a suicidal vet, who must use wits and guts to fend off the killer.
The world's got a lot of problems, but Vir Das has a lot of answers as he discusses travel, religion, his childhood and more in this stand-up special.
Following life-changing traumas, two girls from different backgrounds fight to discover the identities of their biological parents.
A family Christmas gathering at an isolated Australian estate turns into the holiday from hell after a mysterious stranger turns up at the door.
Four young women head to a country house for an idyllic weekend retreat. But what lies in store for them is far from the dreamy getaway they imagined.
A comedy troupe of four friends on the autism spectrum prepares for a final show before its members go their separate ways.
When his outlaw dad is kidnapped, Tommy “White Knife” Stockburn sets off across the West on a rescue mission with five brothers he never knew he had.
As two jobless brothers search aimlessly for careers worthy of their hard-to-please mother’s praise, they cluelessly tackle countless gigs.
Comedian Michelle Wolf takes on outrage culture, massages, childbirth, feminism and much more (like otters) in a stand-up special from New York City.
Developers looking for a location to build a resort on Saipan stumble into a subterranean bunker from WWII where an evil force lies in wait.
In the Australian outback, an Indigenous cop on a missing persons case unearths a trafficking ring and runs afoul of political-industrial interests.
Beyond her larger-than-life persona, this documentary reveals the woman behind the famed event planner, and her legacy as a cultural icon and activist.
The complex historical figure of Leon Trotsky comes to life in this epic biography that depicts the tumultuous life of the Russian revolutionary.
A series of incidents in Afghanistan set complicated political and personal events in motion for a returning Norwegian Special Forces officer.
Passion is an understatement. Meet the folks who wanted a Major League Soccer club in Philadelphia so badly, they became fans before it even existed.
Despite her vain stepmother and mean stepsisters, an aspiring singer works as an elf at a Christmas tree lot and finds her own holiday miracle.
After a run-in with Richard Grieco, dimwits Doug and Steve gain entry to a swanky nightclub in this comedy based on a "Saturday Night Live" sketch.
The world's most shagadelic spy continues his fight against the diabolical Dr. Evil, who's teamed with a new foe: 1970s villain Goldmember.

column4: Austin Powers: International Man of Mystery
column8: A swingin' fashion photographer by day and a groovy British secret agent by night, superspy Austin Powers must foil the sinister schemes of Dr. Evil.

column4: Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me
column8: When diabolical genius Dr. Evil travels back in time to steal superspy Austin Powers's "mojo," Austin must return to the swingin' '60s himself.
When two sisters travel from Canada to Punjab to visit their maternal family, they discover an opportunity to mend a broken bond with their grandmother.
A small-town dreamer is sure he's landed on a gold mine after accidentally filming a murder but is sucked into a violent tale of greed and deception.
A socially awkward teen bonds with a group of misfits who plot to abduct the school's arrogant rich kid – until their kidnapping scheme turns deadly.
From romantic pursuits to their friendship, a trio of young men navigate the complexities of relationships while sharing a London apartment.
A pimp with aspirations of grandeur wants to make it as a rapper but discovers that fame isn't all it's cracked up to be in this indie drama.
This documentary examines the influence of Hong Kong's martial arts cinema on filmmaking from the Shaw Brothers to modern-day Hollywood blockbusters.
An Indian man in Canada marries a local citizen to legalize his immigration status. The only problem? His girlfriend isn't thrilled about his new wife.
Guilt-ridden over his involvement in a fatal car accident, a young ex-pat returns to Punjab, falling for a woman who carries traumas of her own.
A Punjabi man attempts to build a life in London in hopes of impressing his girlfriend’s mother, who insists her daughter marry a man outside of India.
This provocative film sheds light on actor-comedian Martin Lawrence's roots, his rise to fame and his walk on the wild side.
Little Mila turns playtime into a series of fun and educational adventures with her magical pet Morphle, who transforms into anything she dreams up!
When a blood-spattered altar boy is found running from a murder scene, his conviction seems certain – but his attorney is determined to win the case.
A young villager moves to Chandigarh and falls for his bubbly neighbor, but their love story is affected by several heartbreaking twists of fate.
Decades after Detroit singer-songwriter Rodriguez disappeared following the commercial failure of his albums, two fans try to track down their idol.
A renowned corporate attorney at a prestigious firm gambles on a dropout with a photographic memory but no law degree to help on high-stakes cases.
In a remote Alaskan town reeling from a sudden triple murder, a former rodeo champ befriends a lone newcomer with a violent occupation.
This biopic follows pro golfer Ariya Jutanugarn's journey to the LPGA tour, from child prodigy to her number-one ranking in the world.

column4: The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl
column8: A 10-year-old dreamer's imaginary friends – mighty Sharkboy and fire-producing Lavagirl – come to life to seek his help battling a nefarious baddie.
A single man searches for his soulmate through a series of dates with 25 contestants ready to romance him for a chance at love.
Two rookie Boston cops are sent deep undercover – one inside the gang of a charismatic Irish mob boss and the other double-crossing his own department.
When a move to an exclusive seaside community sends her mother and twin brother into a downward spiral, teenager Medina finds solace in surfing.
A get-rich-quick scheme goes awry when a group of friends stumbles onto a dangerous conspiracy and wind up getting mistaken for the bad guys.
Navigating creative pressures and personal upsets, French rapper Nekfeu sets out on a global quest for musical inspiration in this documentary.
A young prosecutor is assigned a career-making case involving a colleague but soon starts to question the motivations behind the charges.
In one of history's greatest last stands, a battalion of 21 Sikh soldiers fights to defend their outpost from attack by over 10,000 Afghans.
After meeting under awkward circumstances, a glamorous businesswoman and a tradition-bound policeman begin a relationship that changes their lives.
A contract killer skilled at staging lethal accidents fears he may be a victim of his own strategy when an accomplice dies in a mysterious mishap.

column4: Ayotzinapa, el paso de la tortuga
column8: Delving into the disappearance of 43 college students in Mexico, this documentary seeks to give justice and a voice to the victims and their families.
After Amalie's dad goes bankrupt, the young dancer's affluent life collapses. But she finds a new beat to follow after meeting hip-hop dancer Mikael.
In Victorian London, 12-year-old business magnate Ciel Phantomhive thwarts dangers to the queen as he's watched over by his demon butler, Sebastian.
When a cop loses his vision, his detecting skills stay sharp. Luckily, a rookie officer recognizes his extraordinary powers of deduction.

column4: Bobby Robson: More Than a Manager
column8: Explore the life and times of legendary soccer manager Bobby Robson, whose keen mind for the game was matched only by his devotion to his teams.
After their 99th breakup, a career woman and her carefree partner open a cafe where customers can put up souvenirs of past relationships.
Three petty criminals find themselves in a pickle when police wrongly charge them with the murder of an important politician.
In Kuala Lumpur, an abused domestic worker tries to escape to Indonesia, while an idealistic cop insists on fighting corruption  – at a heavy price.
A financial analyst succumbs to a love triangle with a hard-drinking architect and a promiscuous investment bro, who soon becomes her boss.
Zixin is about to marry Qihong, but her gallivanting ex returns to wreak havoc as mistaken identities and love triangles stir up the lovers' paradise.
When a man is arrested on arrival in America because authorities mistake him for a wanted gangster, a new friend tries to help him prove his innocence.
With help from a 102-year-old goblin dwelling beneath their haunted apartment building, two siblings deal with ghosts and take on spooky mysteries.
When master criminal Helios steals a mobile WMD, rival agents from Hong Kong, South Korea and China must join forces to recover the device.
This fast-paced action flick tells the dark story of Hellboy, a charismatic demon who's put on Earth by the Nazis to terrorize the rest of the world.
A Hong Kong intelligence officer tasked with finding undercover agents whose identities have been erased finds herself in the paths of rival triads.
A spinoff of Rohit Shetty's action franchise, this animated series follows brave kid cop Little Singham’s adventures as he defends his town from evil.

column4: Little Singham aur Kaal ka Mahajaal
column8: When Kaal, the vilest demon on earth, threatens to destroy his village, child cop Little Singham must use his strength and smarts to fight back.
While keeping his identity secret, a real estate billionaire tries to woo an outspoken croupier who talks gamblers out of losing their money.

column4: Man vs Wild with Sunny Leone
column8: The adventures of Bear Grylls get a unique spin as Bollywood star Sunny Leone hosts the show famous for revealing Bear's wilderness survival skills.
In this "Oddbods" special, Bubbles's latest invention, the Naughty-or-Nice Machine, zaps Santa Claus, jeopardizing the whole Christmas holiday season.
Two former triads are tapped to run in an election for leader of the underworld, but both want normal lives. Each must outwit the other to lose.
Retired, restless and constantly butting heads with his son, a former stuntman escapes on a road trip that becomes a journey to find his first love.
Backed by a crew of unlikely allies, newly sober paraplegic Gabriel Cordell teams up with his nephew for a grueling wheelchair trek across America.
Four man-children in an elite tactical unit gallivant around Macau for a weekend of debauchery that gets them in trouble with the law.
When a restaurant owner in Cyprus returns to Beijing to sign divorce papers, a drunk woman he encounters triggers a string of mishaps.
Weighed down by a dark secret, IRS agent Ben Thomas tries to improve the lives of seven strangers in need of a second chance.
In this take on the classic tale, a captive circus mermaid transforms the lives of a skeptical journalist and his wide-eyed young sister.
Bo thinks her holiday gift-giving isn't good enough, so she heads north to study under Santa Claus – only to find he's missing.
Captain Atomic – once a superhero, now a sock puppet – can only activate his powers with the help of Joey, his new partner and biggest fan.
A 23-year-old girl who's married to a man more than twice her age is forced to contend with the predatory nature of a male-dominated society.
Couples on a tiny budget try to ensure that the day of their wedding turns out to be the magical experience they always dreamed it would be.
After discovering that she was adopted as an infant, a young woman embarks on a perilous quest to connect with her biological mother.
Featuring archival footage and personal recordings, this documentary offers candid insight into the life of the beloved princess.
On a cruise for gay men, five passengers of different nationalities take a break from their families and cultures to party and reflect on life.
Oh takes it upon himself to introduce Christmas joy to his fellow Boovs. Unfortunately, his well-meaning mission nearly destroys the city.
Driven by the lessons he learned from his mother, and the values of the Sikh religion, a man sets out on a mission to serve humanity.

column4: Forbidden Games: The Justin Fashanu Story
column8: This documentary chronicles the tragic, true story of Justin Fashanu, the first – and only – openly gay man to have played professional soccer.
In a plot to bait the snake-goddess Nagin for her immortality-granting essence, George States journeys to India and abducts her reptilian lover.
Elite publishing sales rep Kantaro wraps up his client visits in record time so he can secretly pursue his quest to indulge in the tastiest of sweets.
When a teenager discovers he's not really human, he ventures out to a remote island to explore his roots and confronts a series of wild challenges.
A middle-aged wife and mother of two shocks her traditional, multigenerational Georgian household when she announces she's going to live by herself.
Wimpy blue cat Oggy would like nothing more than to snooze, but he's constantly bothered by the three ugly cockroaches who have invaded his home.
The son of poor farmers leaves his village to seek his fortune in Kuala Lumpur, where he meets a young woman who's also trying to better her life.
Captured by Nazis and sent to Auschwitz, a Jewish musician is assigned to soothe other prisoners marching to their deaths in the gas chambers.
The chaotic ramblings of a young architect's mind take hold of his life as he leaves behind his past in India to work in Prague.
When a palatial wedding venue turns out to be haunted, one of the families hosting the wedding hires a fearless Sikh to deal with the ghost.
This high-octane thriller tells the story of a man on a mission to reclaim what was taken from him and the agent who's determined to stop him.
Mexican journalist and UFO investigator Jaime Maussan travels the world collecting evidence and firsthand accounts of extraterrestrial phenomena.
This documentary explores the growing trend of marijuana decriminalization in the U.S. and the use of cannabis in medicine, art, fine dining and more.
In the near future, with civilization a thing of the past, a man puts his family in peril when he reluctantly lets outsiders into his compound.
Legendary journalist Gay Talese unmasks a motel owner who spied on his guests for decades. But his bombshell story soon becomes a scandal of its own.
Zig, an island-bound hyena, will do anything to get his paws on Marina the mermaid, but her devoted pal Sharko always comes to her rescue in time.
This documentary celebrates the 50th anniversary of the Harlem sports program that has inspired countless city kids to become pro basketball players.
After randomly receiving a handsome political bribe, a sweet, poor elderly woman decides to treat herself a shopping spree, which doesn't go smoothly.
A young boy, upset by his parents' divorce, becomes infatuated with his grandmother's neighbor, an entrancing dancer he watches through a window.
To win the heart of his true love – a high-society girl – a hapless commoner plots to change his identity and avoid his embarrassing friends.
A young man who's learned nothing about his father from his single mom has a freak accident that sends him back to 1989, the year before he was born.
Ya-nuo's been raised as a boy. Now at age 25, she's caught the eye of a triad leader's sister. But what happens when she reveals her true gender?
Iconic artist and master of relaxation Bob Ross demonstrates the process of creating wintry scenes in these episodes dedicated to the season.
After falling through a wormhole, a space-dwelling teen mecha pilot awakes to find himself amid the inhabitants of a strange planet called ... Earth.
In this fact-based drama, politically motivated cops in Andhra Pradesh set out to frame four Tamil laborers for a crime, torturing them to no avail.
A young boy is wanted for a crime he has no recollection of committing and must go on the run, hunted by two powerful kings and their forces.
An unconventional high school philosophy teacher upsets a few parents and staff, romances others and inspires all his pupils, including his gay son.
As the new kid, a shy high school senior finds himself tormented by all his peers except one. But his new friend has a dark, infectious outlook.

column4: Nura: Rise of the Yokai Clan: Demon Capital
column8: By night, teenage Rikuo becomes a form of demon called yokai, preparing to fulfill his destiny as the head of his legendary yokai clan.
A developmentally disabled man obsessed with the Fonz, guns and all things kinky poses a challenge for his arrogant brother when he moves in with him.
Ten years after a once-promising student graduates, she finds herself working at a cosmetics company run by the boy with the worst grades in school.
Richard Pryor's classic 1979 concert film has him discussing a wide range of topics, including race, the police and his favorite target – himself.
Three teenaged best friends on the planet Telluria begin an incredible journey of adventure as they fight against the most evil being in the universe.
This documentary crime series charts the rise of the Irish Mob in America, from urban immigrant poverty to political power and wealth.
An unemployed Bollywood session violinist in Mumbai finally lands a small gig, but it's what happens on his way home that proves truly transformative.
Nate's special Yo-Kai Watch is missing. He travels back in time to meet the watch's inventor, his grandfather. Together, they must restore history!
A young "fabric geek" lands a job at an upscale Japanese lingerie company – and quickly discovers she'll need help to survive.

column4: My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Friendship Games
column8: Rainbow Dash, Applejack and friends compete against Crystal Prep Academy and their lead athlete, this world's Twilight Sparkle, in sporting events.
This documentary recounts a 1994 incident in Honolulu in which a circus elephant attacked and killed its trainer, then ran loose on the city streets.
As preparations for the Winter Feast build, Po is caught between his obligations as the Dragon Warrior and his family holiday traditions.

column4: Colin Quinn: Red State Blue State
column8: Stand-up comedian Colin Quinn calls out the hypocrisies of the left and the right in this special based on his politically charged Off-Broadway show.
A couple’s caustic, increasingly jarring interactions over a Mumbai evening strain their relationship until it threatens to break at its fraying seams.
After 20 years in space, Rocko struggles to adjust to life in 21st century O-Town and makes it his mission to get his favorite show back on the air.
Three teens living in the same São Paulo favela pursue their dreams while maintaining their friendship, amid a world of music, drugs and religion.
An enigmatic conservative Christian group known as the Family wields enormous influence in Washington, D.C., in pursuit of its global ambitions.
Four clever school kids start their own detective agency and vlog about their adventures, becoming fast friends in the process.
Traveling the U.S., host John Weisbarth and expert Zack Giffin are helping families prep for the tiny lifestyle and create hypercustomized mini homes.
A look into the journey of influential strength coach Louie Simmons and the Westside Barbell gym he founded, evolving the sport of powerlifting.
A policewoman whose childhood friend disappeared in Patagonia years ago starts a new search to find answers, and soon finds her own life in danger.
Traversing disciplines from physics to psychology, nine scientists share ideas and seek common ground by delving into deep existential questions.
After discovering that their secret military prison is under attack by terrorists, a ragtag group of inmates does their best to neutralize the enemy.
Reinstated to eradicate the worst crimes in the city, a detective requests the release of three convicts to enlist their help in catching the felons.
Beautiful executive assistant Zeina reluctantly teams up with the self-assured Tarek to chase down an elusive dollar bill worth $1 million.

column4: Judy Moody and the Not Bummer Summer
column8: In this family film, never-dull third-grader Judy Moody embarks on a summer adventure with her brother, Stink, and always-up-for-fun Aunt Opal.
Two classmates from elementary school reunite as next-door neighbors and discover their relationship was – and still is – defined by food.
With the help of her neighbors, a divorced woman residing in a one-person-household apartment complex learns to balance living alone and eating well.
Equipped with nothing more than a GED and strategies for the game of go, an office intern gets thrown into the cold reality of the corporate world.
Possessed by the ghost of a lustful virgin, a timid assistant chef becomes confidently libidinous, drawing the attention of a haughty culinary star.
All hailing from various parts of Korea, a group of college students go from being complete strangers to a big happy family at a Seoul boarding house.
As a teen, Shi Won was obsessed with a boy band. Now 33 years old, Shi Won and her friends are reviving their memories as their school reunion nears.
This compelling documentary follows the 2012 Steubenville, Ohio rape case, putting social media and high school football culture in the spotlight.
Unwed and pregnant, a young woman flees her abusive home in 1950s Georgia and takes refuge at a mysterious convent with a terrible secret.
In 1980s Japan, one determined man turned every crushing setback into opportunity. His name was Toru Muranishi, and he revolutionized his industry.
An unassuming San Francisco chef becomes the latest in a long line of assassins chosen to keep the mystical Wu powers out of the wrong hands.
Siblings separated as children who no longer recognize each other are pitted against each other in a war involving drugs, crime and betrayal.
Doomed by misunderstandings, two middle-school classmates miss their shot at love – but a twist of fate brings them together years later.

column4: Denis Leary: No Cure For Cancer
column8: In the stand-up performance that made him a legend, comedian Denis Leary caustically holds forth on nonsmokers, vegetarians and other undesirables.
When a woman is accused of killing her lover, a renowned lawyer is hired – but the more they try to  untangle the truth, the more convoluted it becomes.
In a time of turbulence for the free market system, one economist explores how it has lifted billions out of poverty, and might just save us all.
Southern charmer Theo Von offers up a twisted take on his dating mishaps, meeting Brad Pitt, chasing down fugitive chimpanzees and more.
To avenge his father's death, a young man leads an army into battle against a cruel tyrant in this Hindi conclusion to the historic saga.
To avenge his father's death, a young man leads an army into battle against a cruel tyrant in this Malayalam conclusion to the historic saga.
To avenge his father's death, a young man leads an army into battle against a cruel tyrant in this Tamil conclusion to the historic saga.
Villagers in the kingdom of Mahismati rescue a baby who is destined to embark on a heroic quest in this Hindi version of S.S. Rajamouli's epic.
Villagers in the kingdom of Mahismati rescue a baby who is destined to embark on a heroic quest in this Malayalam version of S.S. Rajamouli's epic.
Villagers in the kingdom of Mahismati rescue a baby who is destined to embark on a heroic quest in this Tamil version of S.S. Rajamouli's epic.
Two strangers meet by chance on a trip to Thailand and form a connection when they realize their former romantic partners ended up getting together.
A couple's new dream home morphs into a nightmare after they learn that an evil and lustful spirit resides in their basement.
A rebellious daughter accompanies her mother on a medical mission where she falls for the handsome politician's son assigned to be her chaperone.
In a witty solo show, Brent Morin serves up infectious laughs on the agony of puberty, hot guy problems and the time a girl dumped him for a magician.
Nothing is sacred in this show from Australian comic Jim Jefferies, whether it’s the mother of his child, auditioning disabled actors, or gun control.
When a confident college professor is courted by four eligible and well-established men, she struggles to decide who she likes the best.
A steroid peddler explains how he went from an unlicensed anti-aging expert to the point man for the biggest scandal in baseball history.

column4: Sebastian Maniscalco: Why Would You Do That
column8: Sebastian Maniscalco delivers an expressive stand-up at the legendary Beacon Theatre on Whole Foods, family nicknames and dodging obnoxious neighbors.
Jake, Izzy, Cubby and Skully face off against the scheming Captain Hook in a race to find special treasures hidden all around Never Land.

column4: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Avengers Reassembled!
column8: When Ultron seizes control of Iron Man's armor, the Avengers race to save their friend and stop an evil plot to take over the world.

column4: Alarmoty in the Land of Fire
column8: While vacationing at a resort, an ornery and outspoken man is held captive by a criminal organization.
A man begins to regret his choices when his brother decides to join him as a member of the same terrorist organization.
What is anime? Through deep-dives with notable masterminds of this electrifying genre, this fast-paced peek behind the curtain seeks to find the answers.
A mother and young son escape into their own imaginations to ignore the reality of their lives in rural Mexico.
These uncanny tales reveal a world where individuals face the tragic consequences of social pressure, parental oppression and family dysfunction.
An avid gamer is magically transported to ancient China, where he must become a warrior in order to save the princess from an evil warlord.
An American travels to Hong Kong in hopes of winning a lucrative – but potentially deadly – all-female underground fighting tournament.
In a dangerous area of the Mekong River, a drug raid ending in 13 deaths arouses the suspicions of a narcotics officer who sets out to find the truth.
The security chief at a top-level medical facility must fight to ensure that revolutionary cancer research doesn't fall into the wrong hands.

column4: David Cross: Making America Great Again!
column8: Cross skewers Donald Trump, religious taboos and American swagger in a provocative night of comedy at the Paramount Theatre in Austin, Texas.
When an overscheduled girl befriends an eccentric aviator, he regales her with tales about the adventures of an unusual boy who lives on an asteroid.
An orphaned bird tags along with a flock on their long migration to Africa and becomes a hero when his newfound "family" runs into trouble.
Graduate students Krish and Ananya hope to win their parents' approval before they marry, but the two families clash over their cultural differences.
A martial artist faces his biggest test when he has to travel to Bangkok to rescue the woman he loves from the clutches of his romantic rival.
Faking his death to escape the realities of his uneventful life worked out well for Brij Mohan – until he was sentenced to death for his own murder.
Memories in a bowl of steaming noodles, a fading beauty finding her way and a bittersweet first love – all in these stories of city life in China.

column4: Alan Saldaña: Mi vida de pobre
column8: Mexican comic Alan Saldaña has fun with everything from the pressure of sitting in an exit row to maxing out his credit card in this stand-up special.
Top scientists and paleontologists examine dinosaur fossils located throughout Canada, while searching for elusive new species.
An American filmmaker and cyclist unwittingly wades into a global scandal when a Russian scientist leaks shocking details of a vast doping conspiracy.
On a relentless quest to avenge his sister's murder, a man from Cape Town infiltrates a sprawling network of lowlifes and elites in Los Angeles.

column4: Wet Hot American Summer: Ten Years Later
column8: A decade after their wild summer as junior counselors, the gang reunites for a weekend of bonding, hanky-panky and hair-raising adventures.
A bright and spirited seven-year-old girl uses her vivid, dreamlike imagination to navigate everyday adventures alongside her real and imaginary BFFs.
In 14th-century Barcelona, a serf's determined climb to wealth and freedom incurs the disdain of the noble class and the suspicion of the Inquisition.
What could have been a sad journey turns joyful for Rahul when he falls in love with a woman en route to submerging his grandfather's ashes.
Explore the psychological machinations and immoral behavior that define the most nefarious types of criminals.
Slick lawyer Sung fears he's been cursed with bad karma and considers giving up his practice – until he's approached by a widow accused of murder.
An eager young rookie joins the ragtag small-town police force led by his dad as they bumble, squabble and snort their way through a big drug case.
Two young buddies seek love in Hawaii, and upon returning home in disappointment, soon entangle themselves in a messy identity swap.
A physicist uses the laws of thermodynamics to describe romance and relationships, but his theories prove faulty when it comes to his own love life.
Female intelligence agents infiltrate the disparate aspects of a Colombian cartel in an attempt to take down the drug lords and their associates.
In the summer of 1998, middle child Harshu balances school, family, friendship and other challenges of growing up.
This is the astonishing true story behind a moment in TV history: the live 1961 broadcast of Nazi mass-murderer Adolf Eichmann's trial in Jerusalem.
Eager to flaunt their success in front of old bullies and teenage crushes, two best friends spend a wild night at their middle school reunion.
Part-timer Carole meets rich girl Tuesday, and each realizes they've found the musical partner they need. Together, they just might make it.
When an unattractive man gets engaged to a beautiful woman, their families oppose the union and the priest set to perform the ceremony is kidnapped.
When a young soccer fan and his idol forge an unexpected friendship, the connection teaches them both lessons about life and their love of the game.
Whether styling superstars or elevating A-list homes, couple Jason Bolden and Adair Curtis of JSN Studio connect famous clientele with the chicest looks.
Romance, rivalry and radical mystery collide as a group of teens attend a remote island sleepaway camp in this suspenseful, supernatural drama.

column4: The Dark Crystal: Age of Resistance
column8: As power-hungry overlords drain life from the planet Thra, a group of brave Gelfling unite on a quest to save their world and fight off the darkness.
A near-death experience spurs a feared drug lord to leave behind his life of crime and infidelity, to the disbelief of everyone close to him.
Desperate to keep her husband’s secret, a devoted politician’s wife struggles to stave off threats that could ruin their promising new life.
Teens in America dedicate themselves to the Asian game of Go, which originated in ancient China, drawing meaningful life lessons along the way.
After living in America for years, a teenage girl moves back to the Netherlands and is quickly singled out as a misfit by the popular clique at school.
In 1980s Galicia, Spain, a young fisherman becomes a prosperous cocaine smuggler by providing Latin American suppliers with a European entry point.
Death row inmates convicted of capital murder give a firsthand account of their crimes in this documentary series.
After she's left at the altar, a workaholic advertising executive ends up on her Caribbean honeymoon cruise with her estranged father.
A top-ranked college marching band’s members fight to keep their spots, memorize routines, tend to their social lives – and slay the competition.
When an FBI-trained cop returns to her Navarre hometown to catch a killer targeting local teens, she must also face personal demons from her past.
Mistakenly accused of kidnapping, a veteran soldier leaves a trail of broken bad guys in his wake as he tries to rescue a teen sex trafficking victim.
When a San Francisco exec wins a New Zealand inn, she ditches city life to remodel and flip the rustic property with help from a handsome contractor.
In Catholic 19th-century France, professor Léon Rivail attends a séance and is moved to found spiritism, putting him in the authorities' sights.
A British juvenile offender's violent temper gets him transferred to an adult prison, where he encounters his estranged father.
Bear buddies Bucky and Bjorn play games, go on far-out adventures and learn about wondrous new things together.
Former U.S. Labor Secretary Robert Reich makes a compelling case about the serious crisis the U.S. faces due to the widening economic gap.
When cheerleading champs the Rebels are challenged by an edgy new squad, they take on teams from all over the world in a virtual cheer battle.
Small-town import Ryan Hamilton charms New York with folksy comic observations on big-city life, hot-air ballooning and going to Disney World alone.

column4: Travis Scott: Look Mom I Can Fly
column8: While crafting his Grammy-nominated album "Astroworld," Travis Scott juggles controversy, fatherhood and career highs in this intimate documentary.
In the wake of her husband's betrayal, a novelist and mother moves to an old building, where she receives a music box and encounters a strange spirit.
A fiery young woman accepts help from a spy agency to avenge her lover's murder. In return, she must prove herself as one of their top recruits.
After reluctantly joining a dating app, a 35-year-old widow accompanies an easygoing poet on a trip to visit three of his exes.
When an Intelligence Bureau officer’s phone-tapping day job leads him to a serial killer, he must track down and thwart the murderer’s next steps.
When teenage Ray begins transitioning from female to male, his single mom and grandmother must cope with the change while tracking down his father.
This documentary takes a deep dive into the benefits, dangers and lingering questions around Kratom leaf as an alternative to opioid painkillers.

column4: Chicken Soup for the Soul's Being Dad
column8: Nine dads around America with different family structures, backgrounds and jobs navigate the joys and challenges of fatherhood.
A hedonistic soccer mom takes a voyage of self-discovery when she tries to reconnect with her son by returning his pet rock to a Mediterranean island.
Dave Chappelle takes on gun culture, the opioid crisis and the tidal wave of celebrity scandals in a defiant stand-up special filmed in Atlanta.
A messaging app unites a mute prostitute, an unruly rich girl and a stormy young woman, three Hong Kong teens living in pain and excess.
On the run from authorities, a troubled man recalls the mysterious events – and the strange drifter – that inspired his unusual transformation.
Pregnant and overwhelmed, Diana hires a caretaker for her son with severe autism. But she soon begins to fear the new nanny has sinister intentions.
Determined to fall in love, 15-year-old Adele is focused on boys. But it's a blue-haired girl she meets on the street who really piques her interest.

column4: Jeff Foxworthy and Larry the Cable Guy: We’ve Been Thinking...
column8: Grammy-nominated comedians Jeff Foxworthy and Larry the Cable Guy bring their distinctive brand of humor to a packed crowd in Minneapolis.
The lives of a budding DJ, his loyal pal, a hopeless romantic, a jaded has-been and a troubled couple intersect at an electronic dance music festival.
After 25 years of searching, a lonely dentist finds his long-lost daughter but learns that she suffers from a rare medical condition.

column4: Hank: Five Years from the Brink
column8: From Joe Berlinger, director of the "Paradise Lost" trilogy, comes this documentary about controversial former U.S. Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson.
This edgy drama follows 19-year-old Ari, a gay Greek-Australian whose roiling ethnic- and sexual-identity struggles lead to a wild, 24-hour odyssey.

column4: InuYasha the Movie: Affections Touching Across Time
column8: A powerful demon has been sealed away for 200 years. But when the demon's son is awakened, the fate of the world is in jeopardy.

column4: Maria Bamford: The Special Special Special
column8: Spend an evening with gleeful, oh-so-awkward Maria Bamford via her cozy, shot-at-home comedy special, which has a two-person audience: her parents.
The second half of Lars von Trier's epic follows Joe as her reignited sex addiction destroys her family and thrusts her toward a surprising new trade.

column4: Behind "The Cove": The Quiet Japanese Speak Out
column8: After a documentary about the Japanese whaling industry garnered international attention, an amateur filmmaker decides to tell the rest of the story.
What starts as a passionate one-night stand quickly turns sinister when Clare learns she's locked inside Andi's apartment with no way out.
Light Turner finds a supernatural notebook and uses it to mete out death, attracting the attention of a detective, a demon and a girl in his class.
Desperate to escape her tyrannical father, a rebellious teen befriends a deaf drug pusher who's saving up his money for cochlear implants.
A disenfranchised 16-year-old girl connects to an older man on the internet and after a brief one-sided affair descends into obsession and anorexia.
In 1806, ambitious magician Norrell leads a revival of practical magic in England and ignites a fierce rivalry with bold young conjurer Strange.
Too hungover to report as a witness in a criminal trial the day after his birthday party, a young man and his pals do some unexpected soul-searching.
When a successful young rap star has an affair with an obsessive fan, his life is turned upside down when she kidnaps him.
Shirtless comic Bert Kreischer relays personal secrets and stories about being a cool – if not always responsible – dad in this stand-up special.
One man makes a fateful decision to get involved with a Colombian drug cartel in this series based on a novel by Andrés López López.
Drug trafficker Pepe Cadena navigates the treacherous waters of warring cartels in Mexico and Colombia while avoiding capture by the DEA and police.
When a new prisoner at a military detention center exhibits eerie behavior, a young interrogator’s search for the truth becomes a battle for survival.
In this low-budget short film, two best buddies meet up for a night of booze-fueled fun before one of them moves to Vancouver.
Bickering siblings Shi Miao and Shi Fen tackle friendship matters, school drama and the pitfalls of growing up with little parental supervision.
An aspiring rapper and his best friend/manager have one night to bounce back from embarrassment and make their dreams of hip-hop stardom come true.

column4: The Drunk and on Drugs Happy Funtime Hour
column8: A variety-show production trips up big time when the cast members take their roles to new heights, and the line between fact and fiction blurs.
Runaway teen lovers June and Harry find themselves swept up in a dangerous and confusing new world when June begins to display mysterious abilities.

column4: The Power of Grayskull: The Definitive History of He-Man and the Masters of the Universe
column8: This colorful documentary explores the origins and impact of He-Man, a character whose power stretched well beyond a toy line and children's TV show.
In this zany comedy, a man is torn between the girl he loves and the respective women his warring mother and grandmother have chosen for him to marry.
After a young man charms the girl he loves into accepting his proposal, an accidental swap on their wedding day leads him to marry the wrong bride.
Mayday's Life Tour concert unfolds as five fading superheroes are summoned to save the world from an extraterrestrial enemy that detests sound.
Old-school auto collector Mike Hall, his pal Avery Shoaf and son Connor Hall go the extra mile to restore retro cars – and hopefully turn a profit.
In rural India, a detective's investigation of seven confounding suicides uncovers revelations about the myths and mindsets of the rest of the village.
Actress Robin Wright plays herself in this surreal drama about a film star who agrees to have her digital image recorded for reuse in future films.
Just months after a tragic loss, detective Sofia Karppi investigates the murder of a woman with ties to a Helsinki construction company.
Friends Proog and Emo live in a capricious, seemingly infinite machine with a sinister purpose in this experimental computer-animated short.
Twin siblings live under a curse in their ancestral home, but one of them is tempted to defy house rules, angering the spirits keeping them hostage.
Talking squarely to the hip-hop generation, musicians, athletes and others outline the benefits of exercise, a healthy diet and spiritual wellness.
In a world where an app alerts people if someone in the vicinity likes them, Kim Jojo experiences young love while coping with personal adversities.
Unabashed comedian Lynne Koplitz offers a woman's take on being crazy, the benefits of childlessness and the three things all men really want.
High schooler Sadie Mitchell believes the world is about to end – literally. Before it does, she sets out to kiss a boy and win back her best friend.
In this documentary, hopes soar when a Chinese company reopens a shuttered factory in Ohio. But a culture clash threatens to shatter an American dream.
As a series of murders hit close to home, a video game designer with post-traumatic stress must confront her demons, or risk becoming their victim.
As a series of murders hit close to home, a video game designer with post-traumatic stress must confront her demons, or risk becoming their victim.
As a series of murders hit close to home, a video game designer with PTSD must confront her demons, or risk becoming their victim.
Elite street racers from around the world test their limits in supercharged custom cars on the biggest, baddest automotive obstacle course ever built.
When an internet-obsessed teen develops a rare illness that forces her to move to a remote town, she must navigate her relationships without technology.
When she falls in love with the author of a novel she adores, bohemian Bitti enlists the help of a local printer to find her new object of affection.
A detective arrests a doctor for crimes targeting medical professionals but later finds the real culprit in a tale of revenge, corruption and magic.
After her stepdaughter is sexually assaulted at a party, a furious mother sets out to destroy the lives of the four perpetrators who walked away free.
Despite public humiliation and resistance, an entrepreneur markets a hygienic, low-cost sanitary pad that even India's poorest women can afford.
On her first day of marriage, a woman leaves her husband upon learning his home lacks a toilet, sparking a quixotic quest to acquire modern sanitation.
Four young Asian-American rappers strive to achieve success on their own terms in a musical genre that often treats them as outsiders.
Sparks of both passion and contempt fly when a self-sufficient architect is forced to work with a snobbish industrialist.
A field hockey-playing pizza delivery boy finds himself transformed from slacker to zombie slayer during an outbreak of the undead in Kuala Lumpur.
Two huge soccer fans must go on a rambunctious road trip to fix a big match between Malaysia and Thailand, or they'll draw the ire of a loan shark.
Noted UFO expert Dr. Steven Greer interviews witnesses and presents classified documents concerning the existence of extraterrestrials.
In the crime-ridden slums of New York in the 1860s, vengeful orphan Amsterdam Vallon joins the cutthroat gang of his father's killer, Bill the Butcher.
Years spent recording footage of creatures from every corner of the globe is bound to produce a bit of drama. Here's a behind-the-scenes look.
Honest, introspective comic Simon Amstell digs deep and delivers a uniquely vulnerable stand-up set on love, ego, intimacy and ayahuasca.
Spunky leopard cub Leo and his loyal tiger pal Tig team up for fun and adventure as they explore the forest and learn about ancient legends.
With the digital revolution just around the corner, the employees of Bibideaux camera store strive to stay relevant amid unstoppable change.
A movie-loving 10-year-old and her blind little brother trek to meet Indian superstar Shah Rukh Khan for help in getting the boy an eye operation.
Follow the Chinle High basketball team in Arizona's Navajo Nation on a quest to win a state championship and bring pride to their isolated community.
Nestled in a faraway cloud is a rainbow-colored world called Care-a-Lot, home to the magical Care Bears who each have a special talent.
When a vicious war against Catholics is waged in Mexico in the 1920s, a retired general joins the militia fighting to preserve religious freedom.
Best friends Léa and Camille explore the notion of healing while traveling to Latin America in search of a cure for a terminal disease.
Waxing nostalgic about the bittersweet passage from childhood to puberty, four childhood girlfriends recall the magical summer of 1970.
Feeling forgotten on Mother's Day, three best friends leave the suburbs and drive to New York City to surprise their adult sons.
When a chemical plant's poor conditions cause tragedies, an employee leads a protest against the company’s callous owner and local politicians.
Spiced liberally with black comedy, this Bollywood drama follows the lethal love life of a woman who marries numerous men – only to find them flawed.
Eight feisty boys befriend young drifter Fatka. When a mean politician threatens Fatka's way of life, the boys band together in honor of their pal.
A lesbian housewife, feeling trapped in a stale marriage, begins visiting female prostitutes and soon seeks excitement by becoming a sex worker.
A suburban couple hires a new sitter to watch their three kids for the night, unaware that the young woman isn't who she claims to be.
A small-town girl finally realizes her dream of becoming a famous supermodel but soon finds there's a price for her glamorous new life.
A young artist falls for an aristocratic young woman whose bitter mother has trained her in the art of breaking hearts.
Fiza's brother disappears during Mumbai's horrifying 1993 riots. Each day, Fiza and her widowed mother hope that he will return.
In the wake of the plane crash that claimed the lives of 71 people, the Brazilian soccer club Chapecoense seeks to rebuild the team that made history.
After an onstage disaster leaves an illusionist paralyzed, he channels his magic into a hit radio show. Years later, he fights for the right to die.
Shahid Kapoor delivers a searing performance in this Bollywood take on Hamlet that unfolds amid Kashmiri culture and history.
City girl Veera is kidnapped on the eve of her wedding, but as her captors take her through the countryside, Veera finds herself feeling emancipated.
This Bollywood spoof recounts the ups and downs of an assistant film director who loathes romance and a designer who adores all things sentimental.
A remote village situated neither in India or Pakistan becomes its own republic after inmates at the local mental asylum bust loose and take over.
A cranky control freak must rely on his comically dysfunctional family to pull off a scam on a greedy land shark who's stolen his prized property.
A financially troubled Indian man heads to Singapore to find employment, while his pretty wife stays behind in a move that could cause trouble.
A courageous villager moves to the ancient city of Mohenjo Daro, where he falls for the daughter of a priest and does battle with a tyrant.
Two rebellious, hot-headed teenage brothers get caught up in gang life, which has dangerous repercussions for their family and friends.
When the American-educated scion of a powerful Indian family returns to the subcontinent, his first taste of power starts him down a corrupt path.
An idealistic English filmmaker casts a group of student actors in her docudrama about India's revolution against British rule in the 1920s.
A con man uncovers a deadly secret and must save his lady love, the little girl who insists she's his daughter and the small-town locals from the mob.
Meeting while on vacation, Ved and Tara sense a connection but vow to keep their real identities a secret. Years later, their paths cross again.
A flamboyant con artist and his band of gleeful robbers gamble with fate when smugglers hire them to swipe antiques from a speeding train.
Mini isn't eager to wed the rich suitor who's been chosen for her, so she stages her own kidnapping and runs off with a man who works for her father.
Three cheating husbands end up paying the price for their infidelities when their spouses hire a private detective – who falls for one of the wives.
A charming allegory based on a novella by Ruskin Bond, this visually stunning film from India explores themes of greed, loneliness, longing and loss.

column4: Lavell Crawford: Can a Brother Get Some Love?
column8: "Last Comic Standing" runner-up Lavell Crawford lords over a hometown crowd at St. Louis's Orpheum Theatre, raking in the love – and the laughs.
Four high school seniors steal an important college entrance exam and go on vacation to "study," but accidentally lose the exam while partying.
Four friends from a humble technical school compete against the elite students of a prestigious university in a robot-building contest.
When an earthquake hits Chile, rescue workers must put aside their differences to save the country from a businessman's evil scheme.
While living a comfortable life with his wife and child, a germophobic man realizes his estranged brother may have committed a terrible crime.
During World War II, a Chinese railroad worker leads a group of brave resistance fighters against the forces of Japanese occupation.
On a journey from Brazil to the Las Vegas championships, professional bull riders risk it all to earn money, respect and titles.
Superstar DJ Steve Aoki reflects on the driving force behind his career: his ambitious father, Benihana founder and perennial daredevil Rocky Aoki.

column4: Alejandro Sanz: What I Was Is What I Am
column8: A retrospective look at the life and career of Grammy-award winning Spanish musician Alejandro Sanz.
In this mix of live action and CGI, rascally Peter Rabbit faces a tough new foe in his ongoing battle for the veggies in Mr. McGregor's garden.
Pet rescue expert Rocky Kanaka and renovation specialist Rob North travel across North America, transforming animal shelters to help homeless pets.
Daredevil, Jessica Jones, Luke Cage and Iron Fist join forces to take on common enemies as a sinister conspiracy threatens New York City.
An inspirational profile of an inner-city high school football team's valiant effort to reach the school's first-ever playoff game.
In a future with a strict one-child policy, six septuplets must avoid government detection while searching for their missing sister.
From baffling people on the street to orchestrating elaborate tricks, Justin Willman blends good-natured magic with grown-up laughs.
In the probing documentary "Party Monster," DJ Fingablast investigates what became of his childhood hero, DJ Slizzard.

column4: Same Kind of Different as Me
column8: A wealthy couple whose marriage is on the rocks befriends a local homeless man who changes their perspectives in this inspiring true story.
Designer Genevieve Gorder and real estate expert Peter Lorimer show property owners how to turn their short-term rentals into moneymaking showstoppers.
An aspiring writer with no imagination seeks inspiration for his novel by manipulating the lives of his neighbors so that he can write about them.

column4: To All the Boys I’ve Loved Before
column8: When her secret love letters somehow get mailed to each of her five crushes, Lara Jean finds her quiet high school existence turned upside down.
An online community of amateur sleuths use technology to solve crimes – and make quirky friends – in their quest for justice.
Daring comedian Yoo Byung-jae connects criticism he's received from the general public to some of the most touchy issues in current Korean society.

column4: Cop and a Half: New Recruit
column8: A world-weary detective is forced to team up with a 12-year-old who thinks she's a cop in order to solve a case that's baffled police.
